<DIV2 TYPE="prologue">

<PB REF="00000031.tif" N="[3]">
<MILESTONE UNIT="O" N="1,1-2,7">
<HEAD>(PROLOG.) HER ON&YOGH;YN&ETH; URES HALIES F&AElig;DER RE&YOGH;OLAN SANCTES BENEDICTES.<NOTE PLACE="foot">SANCTES BENEDICTES] <ABBR>scs</ABBR> Benedict' <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;ehur &eth;u min bearn beboda &thorn;ines lareowes &amp; onhyld<MILESTONE N="52a" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;inre hurte eare, &amp; &thorn;ines arf&aelig;stan f&aelig;der myna&yogh;un&yogh;a lustlice underfoh &amp; coflice &yogh;efyll, &that; &thorn;u mid &thorn;ire hyrsumnysse &yogh;eswince to Gode &yogh;ecyrre, &thorn;e &thorn;u &aelig;r fram buge mid aswindunge &thorn;inre un&yogh;ehirsumnesse. Eornestlice nu ic sende mine spece to &aelig;lc &thorn;are mannum, &eth;e hir a&yogh;enum lustes ascuna&eth; &amp; mid &thorn;am stren|gastum &amp; &thorn;am beorhtestum hyrsumnysse wepnum drihtene Criste, so&eth;um kinc&yogh;e hyrsumian wile, &aelig;rest &eth;inga swa hwylc god<NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;rest] Aerest <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> swa &thorn;u beginst, &that; hit &eth;urh drihten to fulfremedum &aelig;nde cuman mote, mid singalum gebede geornfullice gewilna.</P>
<P>&THORN;at ure heofonlica f&aelig;der, &eth;e us him to bearnum tel&eth;, n&aelig;fre &eth;urh ure yfelan deda ne geunrotsie, him is on &aelig;lcne timan to hirsumienne mid &thorn;an godum &eth;e he us geunnen haf&eth;, &thorn;il&aelig;s &thorn;e he us ahw&aelig;s ben&aelig;me, &that; is fram his eadignysse ascyrige, swo swo fader de&thorn; his bearn, &eth;onne he hum gram by&eth; for heora gyltum &amp; his &aelig;hte heon ne an, ne &that; an, &thorn;at he<NOTE PLACE="foot">heon ne an] <I>von sp&auml;terer Hd. zu</I> he onne am <I>corr.</I></NOTE> us &aelig;hte bed&aelig;le, ac &thorn;at he us, &eth;e him to wuldre fylian nella&eth;,<NOTE PLACE="foot">ac, c <I>auf Ras., worunter</I> n.</NOTE> swa swa e&yogh;eful lehauerd mid urum yfelum dedum gegremed<MILESTONE N="52b" UNIT="folio"> to eceum wite ne sylle.<NOTE PLACE="foot">sylle, y <I>aus</I> u <I>corr.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Uton eornestlice on sumne timan arisan &thorn;urh halig&aelig;s gewrites munegunge, &thorn;e &thorn;us cwe&eth;: "Nu is time, &thorn;at we of slep&aelig; arisan", &that; is, &thorn;at we synnan &yogh;eswcan &amp; on<NOTE PLACE="foot">on <I>&uuml;. d. Z.</I></NOTE> godum wor|cum 
<PB REF="00000033.tif" N="5"><MILESTONE UNIT="O" N="2,7-3,17"> wacole syn; mid openre gymene godcundes andgyttes we eac gehyran wat d&aelig;gwamlice seo godcunde stefne mynega&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">wat] hat, h <I>oben anradiert Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; clypa&eth; &thorn;us cwe&eth;ende: "Gif ge tod&aelig;g Godes steemne gehire,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Godes] gode <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> nelle ge elcyende aheardian eowre heortan"; &amp; eft &thorn;us cwy&eth;: "Se &thorn;e habbe earen to hlystenne, gehyre hw&aelig;t se halige gast to ealle &thorn;an, &thorn;e to Godes rice gela&eth;ede synde &thorn;us cwe&eth;: Cu|me&eth; ye, mine biernes, &yogh;ehyre&eth; me; Godes eye ic eow tece;<NOTE PLACE="foot">ye]ye <I>oder</I> we, <I>das</I> y <I>od.</I> w <I>rad.</I> &Verbar; &yogh;ehyre&eth;] ehyre&eth;, <I>davor Ras. 1. B.</I> (y? w?)</NOTE> yrnad ofstelice, &thorn;a wile &thorn;e ye lifes leoht habbet, &thorn;il&aelig;s &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">ofstelice] opstel. <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; ye] we <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> dea&eth;es &thorn;ystre eow gel&aelig;ccen".</P>
<P>And drihten on mycelre m&aelig;nige smea&eth; &amp; scrudna&eth;, <I>hw&aelig;t</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">m&aelig;nige, i <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I> &Verbar; <I>hw&aelig;t</I>] <ABBR>hw</ABBR>
<I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;a feawa syndon, &thorn;e his willen wyrcen wyllen, &amp; &thorn;us axiende cwy&eth;: "Hwa is manna, &thorn;e liues wylnie &amp; gode dages ysun wylle?" Gyf &thorn;u &thorn;is gehyrende andswarest: ic eom se &thorn;e &thorn;es wilna&eth;, God almichtin &thorn;us to &thorn;e cwy&eth;: "Gyf &thorn;u abben wylle so&eth; lif and ece, heald &thorn;ine tunge fram yfelre spece &amp; &thorn;ine<NOTE PLACE="foot">lif <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> lippe no&thorn;ing focenlices ne specen; abuh fram ywele and do god; sech sibbe and folge hyre. &thorn;o ye &thorn;us do&eth;, mine eagen<NOTE PLACE="foot">ye] &yogh;e &thorn;e <I>Hs.</I> &yogh;e&thorn;- <I>auf R. v. sp&auml;trer Hd.; unter &yogh; scheint &thorn;, unter &thorn; vielleicht</I> w <I>gestanden zu haben.</I></NOTE> bu&eth; ofer eow &amp; mine eare &aelig;t eower gebedu, &amp; &aelig;r ge me<NOTE PLACE="foot">eow <I>auf R. v. sp&auml;tr. Hd.</I> &Verbar; eower] eo&thorn;er <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> to clupian, i cwe&eth;e: Efne nu ic eom gearue to eower nude".<MILESTONE N="53a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">i cwe&eth;e] <I>Zwischen</I> w <I>und</I> e <I>&uuml;b. d. Z. ein</I> c <I>eingeschoben v. sp&auml;tr. Hd.</I> &Verbar; gearue] geaure <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> Hwet is lustlicor, leofe swustre, to gehyrenne, &thorn;onne &thorn;eos la|&thorn;iende Godes stefene? Efne nu drihten &thorn;urh his mildhertnesse us liues wegas &aelig;tywe&eth;. We eornestlice mid clennesse modes &amp; lichaman &amp; mid geleafan &amp; godre werce bigenge &amp; mid ha|ligra m&aelig;gene heuene his wegas geornlice faren &amp; geernian, &that; we hine, &thorn;e us to &thorn;an wege gela&eth;ode, on his riche geseon mote. Nato&thorn;&aelig;shwon his rices eardung by&eth; gefaren bute mid gymene &amp; gehealdsumnesse goddere deda; ofst &amp; hradung godre weorce is to &thorn;an rice weges fereld.</P>
<P>Ac uten oxien urne drihten &thorn;urh &thorn;es witegan muneginge &thorn;us cwe&eth;ende: "Drihten, hwa mot wunian on &thorn;inre eardung|stowe<NOTE PLACE="foot">mot] mod <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; hwam is rest geunne on &thorn;inre holie dune?" We ge|hyre&eth; &aelig;fter &thorn;issere &aelig;scen drihten andswariende &amp; &thorn;one wei his eardunge &thorn;us techende: "Se on rihtne wei fer&eth; to mine 
<PB REF="00000035.tif" N="7"><MILESTONE UNIT="O" N="3,18-5,4"> riche, &thorn;e bute leahtre besmitenesse wunad &amp; rihtwise weorc bege&eth;, &amp; se &thorn;e so&eth; on his hurte &thorn;eng &amp; facenlices nan &thorn;ing on his mu&eth;e ne clype&eth;, &amp; se &thorn;e his nyhstan nan &thorn;ing yfeles ne dyde, &amp; se hosp &amp; edwt on his nixten ne setten, &amp; se &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">edwt] edyt <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;ane awrgede dufel, &aelig;lches uweles lareow fram his hurten awrp&eth; mid ealre his lare &amp; for naht hine tel&eth; &amp; ealle his ge|&thorn;ohtes<NOTE PLACE="foot">awrp&eth;] ayrp&eth; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> and hopan on God besett, &amp; &thorn;o &thorn;e God ondreda&eth; &amp; hi<NOTE PLACE="foot">besett] besect <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;urh hyre godan deda ne anhebbe&eth;, ac drihten, &thorn;e &thorn;a god on<MILESTONE N="53b" UNIT="folio"> heom woruhte, weor&eth;ia&eth; &amp; m&aelig;rsia&eth;, &thorn;us mid &thorn;an wtgen cly|piende:<NOTE PLACE="foot">wtgen] <I>Zw.</I> w <I>und</I> t <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I> i <I>von sp&auml;tr. Hd.</I></NOTE> "Na us, drihten, na us, ac &thorn;ine nama syle &thorn;u wuldor"; swa eac Paulus &thorn;urh his mere bodunge him sylfe nanes lofes<NOTE PLACE="foot">his] <I>auf d. Rande v. sp&auml;tr. Hd.</I></NOTE> ne tilode, ac eal &thorn;at lof Gode bet&aelig;hte, &thorn;e him snoternesse &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">ne <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I> &Verbar; bet&aelig;hte, <I>das</I> 1. t <I>&uuml;. d. Z.</I></NOTE> wisdom sealde, &thorn;us cwe&eth;ende: "&ETH;urh Godes gyfe ic eom &that; ic eom"; eft se sylfe Paulus cwy&eth;: "Se &thorn;e wuldrige, wldrige on God<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I> &Verbar; wldrige <I>auf dem Rande nachgetragen.</I></NOTE> almihtige and no on hine silfne". Be &thorn;am ylcan andgyte se<NOTE PLACE="foot">no on] no <I>auf d. Rande v. sp&auml;tr. Hd.</I>, on <I>aus</I> non <I>rad.</I></NOTE> helend cwy&eth; on &thorn;an haligen godspelle, &thorn;us clypiende: "Se &thorn;e gehurd &thorn;as mine word &amp; mid werce hi gefyl&eth;, ic hine lete wisne man gelicne, &thorn;e ofer fasten stone bytlode; flodes coman<NOTE PLACE="foot">bytlode] bylode <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; windes blowan &amp; &that; hus swy&eth;lice gespurnan, &amp; hit ne afell, for&thorn;i &thorn;e hit gesta&eth;elod w&aelig;s ofer f&aelig;stum stane."</P>
<P>Ealle god wyrcende &amp; on his halgen gefillende &amp; trymi|gende drihten anbida&eth;, hw&aelig;&eth;er we mid wercum his lare gefillen willan. For bote ure synna &thorn;yses lifes dagas us to fyrste<NOTE PLACE="foot">bote] bete, <I>das</I> 1. e <I>oben anradiert.</I></NOTE> gel&aelig;tene synd, swa cwy&eth; se apostel: "Nast &thorn;u, &that; Godes ge|&thorn;yld<NOTE PLACE="foot">swa] Sya <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e l&aelig;tt to d&aelig;dbote?" So&eth;lice, mildheort drihten &thorn;us cwy&eth;: "Ne wilnige ic &thorn;&aelig;s synfullan dea&eth;es, ac &thorn;&aelig;t he gecurre &amp; lif age". &THORN;o we eornestlice drihten axoden be &thorn;am wuni|unge his eardingstowe, we gehyrdan, hw&aelig;t &thorn;a bebodu synd, &thorn;e we &thorn;a eardungstowe mid geearnian sculon; mid gefylled|nesse godre &thorn;enunge we weor&eth;a&eth; heofene rices yrfeardes.<MILESTONE N="54a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">heofene rices] -ne ri- <I>auf R.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>We for&eth;i heortan &amp; ealne lichaman to &yogh;ecampe &yogh;e&yogh;earwian &amp; to hyrsumnesse hali&yogh;ere &yogh;eboda. &that; we &thorn;urh tyddernesse m&aelig;nsces &yogh;ecyndes &thorn;urhteon ne ma&yogh;on, we urne drihten &yogh;erlice<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000037.tif" N="9"><MILESTONE UNIT="O" N="5,4-6,3"> biddan, &thorn;at he us &thorn;urh his &yogh;yfe &yogh;efultumi&yogh;e to &yogh;elaste his beboden. And &yogh;uf we hellewites biternesse forbu&yogh;an willa&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">we hellewites] we, <I>darauf Rasur von</I> lle, <I>danach</I> wites; <I>auf dem Rande v. sp&auml;tr. Hd.</I> helle.</NOTE> &amp; to ecum life becuman, &thorn;a wile &thorn;e we moten &amp; on &thorn;ysum licaman wuniad &amp; ealle &thorn;as forspecenan &thorn;in&yogh; &thorn;urh liues lih|tin&yogh;e &yogh;efyllan ma&yogh;on, is to radienne &amp; to efstenne &that; us on ecnesse to life gefurdrie.</P>
<P>To&thorn;i &thorn;onne ic eornoslice settan wille bysena &amp; bi&yogh;en&yogh;as<NOTE PLACE="foot">settan] sectan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;yses drihtenlican &thorn;eodomes. &THORN;eah ic hw&aelig;t teartlices, hw&aelig;t|hwe&yogh;e stidlices on &thorn;yse re&yogh;ule, &thorn;e is ures f&aelig;reldes latteow to Criste, &yogh;esette &amp; &yogh;ete&aelig;ce for &yogh;esceades rihtin&yogh;e &amp; for synne bote &amp; so&eth;re sibbe &yogh;ehealdsumnesse, ne beo &thorn;u for&eth;i aforht ne afered, ne &thorn;urh yrh&eth;e &thorn;inre h&aelig;le we&yogh; ne forl&aelig;t; &eth;&aelig;s we&yogh;es an&yogh;in, &thorn;e to Criste let, ne m&aelig;&yogh; beon be&yogh;unnen on fruman buten sumre an&yogh;sumnesse, ac &thorn;a &yogh;e&thorn;in&yogh;&eth;e halin&yogh;re m&aelig;&yogh;ene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">an&yogh;sumn., <I>das</I> 1. s <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> &amp; se &yogh;ewuna &thorn;yssere hali&yogh;en drohtnun&yogh;e, &thorn;e &yogh;ede&eth; leafluht &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ede&eth;] &yogh;e&eth;e&eth; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ea&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;e earue&thorn;e &amp; an&yogh;sumlic &thorn;uhte; se wei is rum &amp; for&eth;|heald, &thorn;e to dea&eth;e and to hellewite let, &amp; se is nearu &amp; sticol, &thorn;e to life &amp; to heofena rice l&aelig;t; he is us &thorn;eah to &yogh;efarenne mid rumheorte mode &amp; mid &yogh;ode &amp; &yogh;l&aelig;de &yogh;e&thorn;ance &amp; mid &yogh;ewyllednesse &YOGH;odes bebode, swa &that; we on munstre &thorn;urhwunien<MILESTONE N="54b" UNIT="folio"> on Cristes lare &amp; t&aelig;cin&yogh;e, &thorn;at we him &yogh;eefenl&aelig;cende mid &yogh;e&thorn;ylde<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eefenl&aelig;cende] &yogh;eefenl&aelig;cen <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> earfodnesse &amp; ehtnesse &thorn;olian, &thorn;at we his riches &yogh;emenesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;emenesse] &yogh;em-nesse, <I>dazwischen Zeilenschluss und an den Rand nach</I> &yogh;em- <I>von moderner Hd.</I> e.</NOTE> &amp; his blisse &yogh;efean mid him a&yogh;en mote.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000041.tif" N="13"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="9,1-10,6">
<HEAD>I. HER SEI&ETH; URE HLAFORD SANCTE BENEDIHT HU FELE<NOTE PLACE="foot">sce Benedihc <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> MYNECENA KYNN SYNDAN.<MILESTONE N="55a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Feower cynne mynecene beod. &THORN;at forme minecene cin is mynsterlice, &that; wuno&eth; inne mynstre &amp; healde&eth; gastlic &yogh;ewn<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ewn <I>aus</I> &yogh;eun <I>corrig.</I></NOTE> under re&yogh;ele wissunge o&eth;&eth;o under abdesse tecunge. &THORN;et o&eth;or mynecene cyn is ancr&aelig;ne, &thorn;at is westensetlena, n&aelig;ng &thorn;are &thorn;e mid radlic&aelig;re hy&yogh;unge &that; westen &yogh;esec&aelig;d, ac &thorn;are &thorn;e &thorn;urh langsumere fandunge munstrelicere drohnunge habbo&eth; &yogh;eleornod, &thorn;at hi onstondende mit Godes fultume &thorn;urh swustren &yogh;etrym|nysse <NOTE PLACE="foot">Godes] goder <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on&yogh;ean &thorn;ane deofol &amp; heor&aelig;s fleasc&aelig;s leahtres &amp; heore<NOTE PLACE="foot">yfele] &yogh;efele <I>oder</I> &yogh;ef&aelig;le, das mittlere e undeutlich.</NOTE> yfele &yogh;e&thorn;anc winnan cunnan.</P>
<P>&ETH;ridde mynecene cyn is mid ealre atelucest, &thorn;o beod sylf|demen &yogh;eclyped, &thorn;o ne bu&thorn; nodor na &thorn;urh reules wissunge, na<NOTE PLACE="foot">bu&thorn;] buh <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; &thorn;urh, r <I>auf Ras.</I> (<I>worunter</I> h?).</NOTE> &thorn;urh lareowe t&aelig;cunge afondede swa swa gold on heor&eth;e, ac<MILESTONE N="55b" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;fter leades &yogh;ecynde on costnunge &yogh;emylta&eth;, &yogh;yt mid heore<NOTE PLACE="foot">leades] leader <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> werce &thorn;are worolde tryw&eth;a h&aelig;l&eth; &amp; leo&yogh;a&eth; God &aelig;lmihti&yogh;e mid mynecene hywunge; &thorn;a wunia&eth; twam &amp; dreom togedere &amp; wilon<NOTE PLACE="foot">twam <I>f. Hs.</I> &Verbar; togedere] togodere <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &aelig;nlypie na on Godes heorde belocene, ac on a&yogh;ene lustum<NOTE PLACE="foot">Godes] goder, r <I>anrad. Hs.</I></NOTE> beswikene; heomon is for &aelig; heore idelre wilnunge lust; swa hwilc idel swa heomon to &yogh;e&thorn;once yrn&eth; &amp; heomon &yogh;ecoren by&eth;, &that; hi talia&eth; hali&yogh;, &amp; swa hwet swa heomon oflica&eth;, &thorn;eah hit hali&yogh; sy, hi hit l&aelig;t&aelig;&eth; unalifod. &THORN;al feor&eth;e mynecene cynn is &that; is widscri&eth;el &yogh;enemned, &thorn;a ealle heore liflade &yogh;eond mis|sendlice &eth;eode faro&eth; &amp; twam &amp; &thorn;reom da&yogh;um &yogh;eond missen|licare mann&aelig; husum wunia&eth;, &aelig;fre unsta&thorn;olf&aelig;ste &amp; wori&yogh;ende,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hus&umacr;, <I>vor</I> s <I>ein</I> r <I>rad.</I> &Verbar; wori&yogh;ende, &yogh; <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> &aelig;&yogh;enum lustum &amp; heore &yogh;itsunge unalyfodlic&aelig; fylia&eth; &amp; hyr|sumiad; on eallum &thorn;ingum hi synd wyrsan &thorn;enne &eth;a seolf|deman, &eth;e on anre wune&yogh;unge stilnysse healda&eth;; be heore ealre earme drohnunge selre is to swi&yogh;enne, &thorn;onne embe to<NOTE PLACE="foot">swi&yogh;enne, &yogh; <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> specenne.</P>
<P>We &eth;a for&thorn;i forl&aelig;ten &amp; to &thorn;am strengustum mynstercynne mynec&aelig;na &yogh;ecyrran &amp; mid Godes fultume heore drohtnunge &yogh;eendebyrden.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000043.tif" N="15"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="10,7-11,20">
<HEAD>II. HWYLC SCEAL SEO ABBODESSE BEON.<NOTE PLACE="foot">SEO ABBOD. BEON <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eo abbodesse, &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;s wyr&eth;e sy, &thorn;at heo &thorn;&aelig;s munster<MILESTONE N="58a" UNIT="folio"> wealde, heo sceal a &yogh;emunan, hwet heo &yogh;ecweden is &amp; &thorn;&aelig;s ealderscypes naman mid dedum &yogh;efyllan. Cristes &yogh;espelia heo is &amp; on &thorn;an mynstra Cristes stede healt &amp; for&thorn;y his a&yogh;enum<NOTE PLACE="foot">on <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> naman &yogh;eci&yogh;ed is, swa swa se apostel se&yogh;&eth; &thorn;us cwe&eth;onde: "Ge onfengan &thorn;ane gast bearne &yogh;ewisin&yogh;e, on &thorn;an we clypio&eth; abba, &thorn;at is f&aelig;der, abbodesse, &thorn;at is modor &yogh;enemned."</P>
<P>Hit for&eth;i n&aelig;fre ne &yogh;ewur&eth;e, &thorn;at abbodesse en&yogh; &thorn;ing l&aelig;re od&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">od&eth;e] od&eth;o <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;esette, od&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">od&eth;e] od&eth;o <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hate, buton Godes bebode; ac hyre h&aelig;s &amp; lare, &thorn;esme godcundre rihwisnysse, on hyre underdyddra modum beo &yogh;estryd&eth;; sy heo &aelig;fre &yogh;emyndi&yogh;, &thorn;at mycel smea&yogh;unge<NOTE PLACE="foot">sy <I>auf Ras.</I> (?) &Verbar; &yogh;emyndi&yogh;, d <I>auf Ras.</I> (<I>eines</I> t?).</NOTE> by&eth; on &thorn;an e&yogh;efullan Godes dome, &aelig;&yogh;&eth;er &yogh;e embe hyre lare, &yogh;e embe hyre under&eth;ydre hyrsumnysse. Wyte hyre to so&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">underdy&eth;re <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &that; heo by&eth; &yogh;ewitnod swa swa &yogh;emel&aelig;s heorde, &yogh;if &thorn;es hiredes ealdor, &that; is drihten, to litle note &amp; nytwyr&eth;nisse on his hurde on&yogh;yte. Heo eft on &thorn;am dome sicar bi&eth; &amp; sacles, &yogh;ef heo mid ealre &yogh;emene &thorn;a un&yogh;ehursume heorde &yogh;eheold &amp; heora seocum, &thorn;at is synfulle d&aelig;dum ealle lacnunge &yogh;e&yogh;earewude, &thorn;us mid &thorn;am wite&yogh;a cwe&eth;ende: "&THORN;ine rihtwisnysse, drihten, ic on minre heorte ne bedi&yogh;lode, &thorn;ine sodf&aelig;stnesse &amp; &thorn;ine halwendnysse ic s&aelig;de, hi &thorn;eah forhoi&yogh;ende me forsawon"; &eth;urh &thorn;i &thorn;onne<MILESTONE N="58b" UNIT="folio"> wite &amp; de&eth; rixa&eth; on &thorn;a un&yogh;ehyrsum hyrde hire &yogh;ymenne.<NOTE PLACE="foot">for|hoi&yogh;ende, <I>davor Ras. v. 1-2 B.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Eornestlice, &thorn;eo &thorn;e &thorn;one meren naman habbodesse under|fehe&eth;, heo sceal mid twifealde lare &thorn;a wyldan &amp; tyn, &thorn;e hyre under&thorn;eodde synd, &thorn;et is, &thorn;et heo ealle gode &thorn;ing &amp; hali&yogh;e|nesse mid godum d&aelig;dum swy&eth;or t&aelig;ce, &thorn;onne mid wordum l&aelig;re, &thorn;at &thorn;a and&yogh;etfullan mid worda lare to Godes willan &yogh;e|myne&yogh;od syn &amp; &thorn;a unand&yogh;ytfullan mit godum dedum &yogh;etrymede<NOTE PLACE="foot">unand&yogh;ytf.] unad&yogh;. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> syn &amp; gel&aelig;rede. Ealle &thorn;o &thorn;ing, &thorn;e heo hire under&thorn;yddan for|beode, sceaw&yogh;e mid hyre dede, &thorn;at hi ne beon to donde; gif hu &thorn;onne wel l&aelig;r&eth; &amp; yfele mid weorce bysna&eth;, heo by&eth; for|&thorn;earlice aworpen, &amp; drihton durh his wite&yogh;a to hyre synfulan<NOTE PLACE="foot">wite&yogh;a] <I>davor Ras. 1 B.</I> &Verbar; synfulan] sylfre <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000045.tif" N="17"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="11,20-13,14"> &thorn;us clypa&eth;: "Forwi atelst &thorn;u mine rihtwysnesse &amp; nimst mine bebode on &thorn;ine mu&eth;e? &THORN;u so&eth;lice hatodest rihte lore &amp; wurpe mine word b&aelig;fte &thorn;e". "&ETH;u &yogh;esawe &thorn;at streow on &thorn;inre swuster<NOTE PLACE="foot">&ETH;u] &ETH; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ea&yogh;e &amp; ne &yogh;esea&yogh;e &thorn;one beam on &thorn;ine a&yogh;ene ea&yogh;e." &THORN;at is on and&yogh;yte: &thorn;u ascunedust &thorn;a l&aelig;stan &yogh;yltas on &thorn;irum &yogh;in&yogh;rum &amp; &thorn;a m&aelig;stan noldest on &thorn;e sylfan.</P>
<P>Ne sy na fram abodesse hada to&yogh;escead on mynstre &yogh;e|heldan, &thorn;at is, ne sy nan fram hyre &yogh;ewyr&eth;od for &yogh;ebirdum,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ewyrdod <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> od&eth;e for ylde, od&eth;e for &aelig;ni&yogh;um o&thorn;rum &thorn;ingum, buten for Godes e&yogh;e anum &amp; for so&eth;es wisdomes &yogh;esceade. Ne sceal heo nane<MILESTONE N="59a" UNIT="folio"> swy&eth;or lufian, &thorn;enne o&eth;re, buton &thorn;e heo on godum dedum &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e heo] &thorn;eo <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on hyrsumnysse beteran on&yogh;yte; ne sceal heo &thorn;a &aelig;&thorn;elborene settan beforan &thorn;are &eth;eowborena, &yogh;ef seo &thorn;euborene &aelig;r on &thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">settan, set- <I>auf Ras.</I> &Verbar; seo] se <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mynstre was, buton heo for hwilcum &yogh;escade hit do, &that; is, &yogh;yf &thorn;eo &aelig;&thorn;elborene mid godcundum crefte &thorn;u un&aelig;&eth;elborena ofor|&eth;yh&eth;, sy heo &yogh;emedemod fur&eth;ur be hyre &yogh;eearnunge &thorn;onne &thorn;eo un&aelig;&thorn;elborena; na be &yogh;ebyrdum anum &thorn;is is to healdenne,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;eo, &thorn; <I>unten anradiert oder verwaschen.</I> &Verbar; is <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> eac be eall&aelig;s mynstres &aelig;ndebyrdnysse, &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;eo beo fur&eth;or &yogh;eleten on stalle &amp; on setle, &thorn;eo &thorn;u fur&eth;ur on &yogh;eearnunge sy tofore &YOGH;ode; sy hycere &yogh;ebyrde od&eth;e &yogh;ecyrrednesse swyce heo<NOTE PLACE="foot">&YOGH;ode] &yogh;ede <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; swyce] syyce <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> sy, buten hwylc &thorn;onne o&eth;re mid &yogh;eearnunge ofer&thorn;eon, beon hi on stede &amp; on setle, swa swa hyre &yogh;ecyrrednesse bi&eth;, for&eth;am &yogh;e &thorn;eow &yogh;e fri&yogh;, ealle we synd on Criste an &amp; under anum Gode &yogh;elicne &thorn;eudom we underfen&yogh;en, for&thorn;an &thorn;e mid Gode nis<NOTE PLACE="foot">for&thorn;an, f <I>aus</I> &thorn; <I>corrig.</I></NOTE> anfan&yogh;enesse nanre hade, &thorn;at is nanes riceteres, ne ylde, buten<NOTE PLACE="foot">anfan&yogh;. <I>&uuml;b. d.</I> 1. a <I>ein</I> o <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eearnun&yogh;e anre. Ealle heo sceal &yogh;elice lufian hyre under|&thorn;eoddan &amp; heom ealle sceal beon an steor &amp; an lar &aelig;fter heore<NOTE PLACE="foot">heore <I>auf dem Rande nachgetr.</I></NOTE> earnunge andefne.</P>
<P>Abbodesse sceal &aelig;fre healde on hyre lare sanctes Paules cwyde, &thorn;es apostles, on &thorn;an he cwyd: "&thorn;rea &amp; witne &amp; halsne<NOTE PLACE="foot">cwyd, danach <I>ein</I> e <I>rad.</I></NOTE> &amp; cid"; heo sceal men&yogh;en re&eth;nesse wi&eth; &thorn;o li&eth;nesse, heo sceal &yogh;edon, &that; hyre rednesse &aelig;tteowye moderlice &amp; &aelig;rfeste lufe, &that;<MILESTONE N="59b" UNIT="folio"> is &thorn;a unstillan &amp; &thorn;a heardhurtan heo sceal &thorn;rea&yogh;ian &amp; t&aelig;le, &amp; &thorn;a &yogh;ehyrsumen &amp; &thorn;a myldan &amp; &thorn;a &yogh;e&thorn;yldian heo sceal wit|nian <NOTE PLACE="foot">wicnian <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; halsyan, &thorn;at hy bet &amp; bet don &amp; &thorn;a &yogh;emelease &amp; &thorn;a 
<PB REF="00000047.tif" N="19"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="13,15-14,17"> oferhogiendan heo sceal &aelig;&yogh;&eth;er &yogh;e mid wordum &yogh;e mid dedum swngan. Ne sceall heo na yldian &amp; hiwian, swylce hit hyre uncu&eth; sy, ac sona swa heo hw&aelig;t unrihtes on&yogh;yte, heo hit sceal sone mid ealle grundlunde towerpe &amp; fordon; heo sceal<NOTE PLACE="foot">heo] He <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;e&thorn;encan &thorn;&aelig;s preostes freccednesse Heli of Sylo. &ETH;a &yogh;ode, &yogh;yf hw&aelig;t misdo&eth;, &aelig;t &thorn;am forme gylte &amp; &aelig;t &thorn;am o&eth;re, styre<NOTE PLACE="foot">hw&aelig;t] hy&aelig;t <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mid wordum; &thorn;a &thorn;e wi&eth;e beod &amp; hearde &amp; prute &amp; un&yogh;ehur|sume, anan swa hi&yogh; misdo&eth;, heo sceal mid swingunge o&eth;&eth;o<NOTE PLACE="foot">heo sceal <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> mid sume odre licamlice clensunge stiran, &amp; witon &thorn;at hit is &yogh;ewriton: "&thorn;am dyse&yogh;um ne mei man mid worde sturien, &amp; eft &thorn;at &yogh;ewrit sei&yogh;&eth;: "Smit &thorn;in bearn mid &thorn;are &yogh;yrd, &amp; swa &thorn;u<NOTE PLACE="foot">sei&yogh;&eth;] rei&yogh;&eth; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> miht ahredde his saule fram dea&thorn;e".<NOTE PLACE="foot">ahredde] <I>das</I> 1. e <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>&AElig;fre seo abbodesse mot beon &yogh;emyndi&yogh;, &thorn;at heo is abbo|desse,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&AElig;fre, &AElig; <I>die Initiale</I> E, <I>dannach ein halbes</I> a <I>mit dem folgenden</I> f <I>verbunden.</I></NOTE> &aelig;fre beon &yogh;emyndi&yogh; hwet heo &yogh;eclypod sy, &amp; wite &that;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;fre] &aelig;fne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;are, &thorn;e mare is b&aelig;teht, more me wyle habbon of hyre. Heo<NOTE PLACE="foot">mare is b&aelig;teht, more] -re is b. mo- <I>auf d. Rande nachgetr. v. 1. Corr.</I></NOTE> hah to understonden, hu &aelig;rfodlic &amp; hu grislic &thorn;ing heo under|fangon hafod, &that; heo nyme &yogh;ieme of o&eth;re mannum saule &amp; fele cynne mod mot hyran &amp; abu&yogh;an, suman mid olecunge &amp; suman mid &thorn;r&aelig;tunge &amp; suman mid wissungum; &amp; &aelig;fter &aelig;lc&aelig;re &yogh;ewne<MILESTONE N="60a" UNIT="folio"> &amp; &yogh;ewitta he mot hyre sylua swa to heom eallum hywian and dihtan, &that; heo na &yogh;e&thorn;olia &thorn;e heorde, &thorn;e is hire beateht, litlia<NOTE PLACE="foot">hire] &thorn;ire <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> o&eth;&eth;o losia, ac &thorn;at heo mage blissian on hyre goddere heorda wexunga.</P>
<P>Beforen weallum &thorn;ingum, &thorn;at heo ne beo recceleas, ne litel ne telle of &thorn;are saule h&aelig;l&thorn;e, &that; hyre beo&thorn; beotehte, &amp; ni<NOTE PLACE="foot">h&aelig;l&thorn;e] h&aelig;lpe <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; beo&thorn;] beoht <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mon mare gyeme of eor&eth;lice &thorn;ingum, &thorn;e aga&eth; &amp; atfealla&eth;, ac &aelig;fre &yogh;e&thorn;ence, &thorn;at he underfeng saule to gyemenne, for hwam hu sceal &yogh;ewistale upa&yogh;ifen. &THORN;eh hit &yogh;elimpe, &thorn;at heo lytle &aelig;hte habbe, ne beo heo &thorn;as dryri, ac &yogh;emune, &that; hit &yogh;wryton<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;emune] &yogh;emne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> is: "&AElig;rest seced Godes rice &amp; his rihwisnesse &amp; eallu &thorn;os<NOTE PLACE="foot">eallu] eall&umacr; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;ing scullen beon y&thorn;&yogh;eat&aelig;" &amp; eft &that; &yogh;ewrit se&yogh;e&eth;: "N&aelig;ng ne ateorede &thorn;an, &thorn;e of Gode beo&eth; ofdr&aelig;&eth;". Wite eac se abbo|desse, &thorn;at heo &thorn;e saulan haue&thorn; underfangan to witienne, &yogh;eare|wi&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">haue&thorn;] haueht <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hi seolfe to &yogh;ifonne andsware for heom, &amp; wyte hu eac 
<PB REF="00000049.tif" N="21"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="14,17-16,6"> to so&eth;e, &that; for hure ealre sawlan, &thorn;e bu&eth; under hyre anwealde, on domesd&aelig;&yogh; heo sceal hi bitellen &amp; ryht a&yogh;ylden for heom eallum &amp; eac &thorn;ar to eacen wi&eth;uton ealcum twynun&yogh;e for hire a&yogh;enre sawle. And on &thorn;as wise &aelig;fre hu hyre ondrede, swa swa se hyrde de&eth;, &thorn;enne he is sceap his hlaforde sceal beteace; &thorn;&aelig; wile &thorn;e he is cari, &thorn;&aelig;t o&thorn;re ne misdon, he becum&eth; &thorn;e werrer of him sylfe, &amp; &thorn;enne he &thorn;urh his teacungen o&thorn;ren heol|pod,<NOTE PLACE="foot">o&thorn;ren] <I>auf d. Rand dies. Hd. nachgetr.</I></NOTE> himsylfe is &yogh;emacod cleane on &thorn;eawen.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>III. HWENNE ME SCEALL LA&ETH;IAN &THORN;A &YOGH;ESWUSTREN<MILESTONE N="61a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">hrenne <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; &yogh;eswustwen <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> TO REDE.</HEAD>
<P>Swa oft swa &aelig;ni&yogh;e micela &thorn;ing synd to donne on &thorn;an mynstre, se abbodesse &yogh;ela&eth;i&yogh;e togedere eall &thorn;one &yogh;eferscyepe &amp; segge hyreself, hw&aelig;t &thorn;ar beo to donne. And &yogh;ehyre &thorn;onne hyre sustre r&aelig;dd &amp; smea&yogh;e b&aelig; hyre sylfro, and don la hwet<NOTE PLACE="foot">hyre] byre <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; &amp; <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> hyre &thorn;ince betst. &ETH;arfore we habbo&eth; &yogh;es&aelig;d, &that; ealle beon &yogh;e|clypod<NOTE PLACE="foot">betst] becst <I>oder</I> beest, <I>doch eher das erstere. Hs.</I></NOTE> to reade, for&thorn;an &thorn;e oft God &thorn;are &yogh;ingeste &yogh;eswytolo&eth;, &thorn;at selest is to donne.</P>
<P>Swa deh &yogh;ifon &thorn;a sustran red mid ealre under&eth;ydnysse &amp; eadmodnesse, &thorn;at nan ne dyrstl&aelig;c&aelig; mid anwilnesse to heal|dene hwet, swa heom &thorn;ince, ac swy&thorn;ost hit ga &aelig;fter &thorn;are<NOTE PLACE="foot">swy&thorn;ost] swy&thorn;orst <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; &aelig;fter] after &aelig;ft <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> abbadesse wille, &amp; &thorn;at &that; hyre betst licie to donne, ealle hyre<NOTE PLACE="foot">betst] becst <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> beon &yogh;ehyrsume. Ac swa swa hit &yogh;erysa&eth;, &thorn;at &thorn;a &yogh;ingran &thorn;am yldrum hyran, swa eac bycum&eth;, &thorn;at se abbodesse w&aelig;rlice and mid ryhte reade&yogh;ige ealle &thorn;ing.</P>
<P>On eallum &thorn;ingum ealle fylie &thorn;es re&yogh;ules wissunge, ne nan ne beo swa &eth;riste, &thorn;at fram hym abu&yogh;e; nan on &thorn;am mynstre hire a&yogh;enre heorte will fylia. Ne nan beo swa &eth;riste, &that; heo<NOTE PLACE="foot">fylia] f&yogh;lia <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on&yogh;ean &thorn;a abbodasse wi&eth;inne mynstre od&eth;e widuton wi&eth;orlice flite; gif hit ani de&eth;, hu ah &thorn;arfore &thorn;olian &thorn;a re&yogh;ullice wrec&aelig;. Wite se abbodesse &thorn;eah, eal &that; heo do, &thorn;at heo hit do mid 
<PB REF="00000051.tif" N="23"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="16,6-17,20"> Godes e&yogh;e &amp; &thorn;es regoles healtrumnysse, for&thorn;am &thorn;e buton tweon, heo sceal ealre hire dome riht a&yogh;yldon beforan &thorn;an rihwisan<MILESTONE N="61b" UNIT="folio"> deman on domesd&aelig;&yogh;.</P>
<P>Gyf &thorn;onne &aelig;ni&yogh;e l&aelig;sse &thorn;ing sy to donne on &thorn;es mynstres neodan, don bi &thorn;are hildestren swustrene rede, swa swa hit is &yogh;ewritan: "Ealle &thorn;ing do mid rede, &amp; &aelig;fter &thorn;&aelig;re d&aelig;de ne reo|we&eth; hit &thorn;e nefre."</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>IV. HER HIT SPEC&ETH; HWYLCE SCEOLON BEON &THORN;A TOOL TO GODE WEORCA.<MILESTONE N="62b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Erest man sceal lufian ure hlaford God &aelig;lmihti mid &aelig;alre heorte, mid ealre saule, mid eallum m&aelig;&yogh;ne, &amp; &thorn;ar&aelig;fter ure nyhstan swa swa us sylfen.</P>
<P>&ETH;ar&aelig;fter ne slean man; ne unriht h&aelig;me; ne stele; ne fylie yfoles lustas; ne bere lease &yogh;ewitnesse; wyr&eth;ian eallum men, &amp; &thorn;at heo nelle, &thorn;at man do hire, ne don o&eth;re. Widsac&aelig; swa hi sulfa, &thorn;&aelig;t hu fyl&yogh;a Crist; wyldon hire lichame; softnissan n&aelig;ng beocleoppe; f&aelig;sten lufian. Earman wreccan hy&thorn;egian,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Earman] earmman <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> nacodum scride, unhalne neosie, deadne byrian, &yogh;esw&aelig;nctum helpan, &thorn;&aelig;ne sarienne frefrian.<NOTE PLACE="foot">sarienne] sarien <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; frefrian <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Fram &thorn;yssare woroldum d&aelig;dum macian hine uncu&eth;. Na &thorn;ing<MILESTONE N="63a" UNIT="folio"> beforan Cristes lufe setten. Wr&aelig;&eth;&eth;e n&aelig;ng fulfille, on &thorn;es time ne &yogh;e&thorn;ence, ne healde faken on herte, ne &yogh;ife lease sibbe, ne so&eth;e lufe forl&aelig;ten. Ne sceal non swerie, l&aelig;ste hyre &yogh;elympe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">fol&aelig;ten <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;at hu forswerie; so&eth; of heorte &amp; of mu&eth;e for&thorn;ringan. N&aelig;ng &yogh;elde yfol for yfele; ne don teone, &amp; &yogh;ef heo bu&eth; hyre &yogh;edon, &thorn;ildelicen forberan; hire fynd lufian; &thorn;a &thorn;a hi wergia&eth;, n&aelig;ng cursian a&yogh;ean, ac &thorn;e swy&eth;or bletsyan; ehtnysse for rihtwis|nysse<NOTE PLACE="foot">for] <I>danach Ras. eines</I> r.</NOTE> &thorn;olian. N&aelig;ng beon ofermod&yogh;, ne druncen&yogh;eorn, ne ofer|&aelig;te, ne slaw, ne slap&yogh;eorn, ne gneornende, ne teolende. Hire tohopan heo sceal habbon on God; &thorn;&aelig;nne heo hw&aelig;t godes &yogh;eseic&eth; on hire, &yogh;ecnawe hit of Gode &amp; n&aelig;ng of hyre sylfre; &thorn;at yfol &thorn;at heo de&eth;, &aelig;fre wite, &thorn;at heo hiresylf hit macu&eth; &amp; hire sylfre hu hit wite. Of domesda&yogh; beon ofdrad and of 
<PB REF="00000053.tif" N="25"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="17,20-19,5"> hellewite agrisan; &that; ecean lif mid ealre gastlicere &yogh;yrnfulnisse &yogh;yrnan; dea&eth; ealce de&yogh; habbon orwene beforan hyre e&yogh;an.<NOTE PLACE="foot">de&yogh;, <I>das &yogh; radiert.</I> &Verbar; e&yogh;an, <I>das</I> a <I>aus einem</I> e <I>corrig. oder um|gekehrt.</I></NOTE> Hyre lifes dedan &yogh;eman on elce tyde; on &aelig;lce stede wytan &yogh;ewis &that; God hy &yogh;esyc&eth;; &thorn;o yfole &yogh;e&thorn;anc, &thorn;e cume&eth; to hyre hurte, anan an Crist toslean &amp; hyre gastlice lareowe hi&yogh; ope|nian.<NOTE PLACE="foot">an <I>fehlt Hs.</I> &Verbar; hi&yogh;] im, <I>davor Ras. cines B.</I> (h?) <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> Hire mu&eth; fram yfolre &amp; fram unwrestere spece healdon;<NOTE PLACE="foot">un|wrestere] unwrost., o <I>anradiert, sodass es zu</I> c <I>ward, also</I> unwrcstere <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> fele specen nang lufie, ydele word &amp; becomelice to leahtre<NOTE PLACE="foot">specen, <I>das</I> 1. e <I>&uuml;. d. Z.</I></NOTE> n&aelig;ng specen; michelne hleahter o&eth;&eth;o cinkinde n&aelig;ng lufyen. Hali&yogh;e r&aelig;dinge bli&thorn;elice &yogh;ehyran; on &yogh;ebeden beon &yogh;elome;<MILESTONE N="63b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ehyran] ehyran, <I>davor Ras. eines &thorn;, auch</I> h <I>auf Ras. Hs.</I></NOTE> hyre misd&aelig;dum, &thorn;e heo &yogh;edon hafod, mid tearan o&eth;&eth;o mid bereofunge elche de&yogh; on hyre &yogh;ebeden and&aelig;ttian ure drihte, &amp; hi&yogh; sylue &thorn;arwi&eth; &aelig;freft &yogh;escylde.</P>
<P>Hyres fleaches lustas n&aelig;ng &yogh;efullan; hyre a&yogh;en &yogh;ewill hatian; on &aelig;lle &thorn;ingum &thorn;are abbodesse h&aelig;se beon &yogh;ehyrsum,<NOTE PLACE="foot">h&aelig;se, s <I>aus</I> r <I>rad.</I></NOTE> &thorn;eh heo hyresylf do ho&eth;erlicer, sy &thorn;at heo ne mote, &thorn;enne heo l&aelig;re; beon &yogh;emundi &thorn;are drihtanliccan hese, &thorn;e &thorn;us is &yogh;ecwede:<NOTE PLACE="foot">drihtanliccan] -ccar, <I>danach Ras. von 1-2 Buchstaben Hs.</I></NOTE> "Do&eth; &thorn;at ih &yogh;eou segga&eth;, ac &that; &that; hi&yogh; heomsylf do&eth;, ne wilni&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">ih &yogh;eou] ih&yogh; <I>dann Ras. 1 B., darauf</I> eou <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;e to donne." Nang wilni&yogh;e &that; me hi&yogh; telle hali, &aelig;r hieo hali sy, ac erer beon hali &that; hit sy&eth;nes ma&yogh;e &thorn;e se&eth;licer beon<NOTE PLACE="foot">sy&eth;nes ma&yogh;e] <I>dazwischen Ras. v. 2-3 B.</I> &Verbar; &thorn;e se&eth;l.] &thorn;e se&eth;lices, <I>dazwischen Ras. v. 1-2 B. Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;esed; Godes beboden &aelig;lce dei mid wercen heo sceal &yogh;efellan, &amp; cl&aelig;nnesse lufian; nane man hatian; ande &amp; nu&eth; nang hab|bon;<NOTE PLACE="foot">nane] <I>das</I> 1. n <I>aus</I> m <I>rad.; &uuml;ber dem</I> a <I>ein</I> (<I>Zeichen f&uuml;r</I> n), <I>das aber wieder getilgt ist;</I> -e <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> ne &yogh;eflit lufian; upahefodnysse forfleon; hwyr&eth;ian hure<NOTE PLACE="foot">lufian] <ABBR>l<GAP>fian</ABBR>
<I>Hs.</I></NOTE> uldran; hyre &yogh;ingran lufian on Cristes lufe; for hyre fynd &yogh;ebiddon; wi&eth; &thorn;a wrangsehtan, &aelig;r sunne go to glade, fre|ondscipe macian; &amp; be Godes mildcsa n&aelig;fre ofertriwian.</P>
<P>Efne nu &thorn;is synd &thorn;es gaslices tol &amp; &yogh;ebytle; &yogh;if hi&yogh; &thorn;urh<NOTE PLACE="foot">ofertriwian, <I>das</I> 2. i <I>&uuml;. d. Z.</I></NOTE> us d&aelig;&yogh;es &amp; nihtes un&yogh;eswicenlice wur&eth;o&eth; nu &yogh;efillede &amp; on domesd&aelig;&yogh;e us eft betehte, &thorn;eo mede at ure drihtene us &eth;onne<NOTE PLACE="foot">betehte <I>bis</I> at <I>auf d. Rande nachgetragen vom 1. Cor|rector.</I></NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000055.tif" N="27"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="19,6-20,13"> by&eth; &yogh;egoldon, &thorn;e he himsilf behet, &thorn;at is: "&THORN;at mannes e&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">e&yogh;e, <I>davor ein &yogh; rad.</I></NOTE> ne &yogh;eseh, ne eare &yogh;ehyr(de), ne on mannes hyrte ne astah,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ehyrde] &yogh;ehyr, r <I>anradiert, danach Ras. von 2 Buchst., wie cs scheint</I> &yogh;e.</NOTE> &thorn;e drihte hafod &yogh;e&yogh;eared &thorn;an &thorn;e hine lufie&eth;. &THORN;a stowwen<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e&yogh;eared] <I>zu</I> &yogh;e&yogh;earewed <I>corrigiert vom 1. Corr.</I> &thorn;e <I>&uuml;b. d. Z. nachgetr. v. 1. Corr.</I></NOTE> hwar we ealle &thorn;os &thorn;ing ma&yogh;e sycerlice wyrc&aelig;n, beod &thorn;es<NOTE PLACE="foot">lufied] <ABBR>l<GAP>fied</ABBR><I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mynstres claustren &aelig;nd myd stedefestnesse on &eth;are &yogh;efer|reddene.<MILESTONE N="64a" UNIT="folio"></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>V. BE GEHYRSUMNESSE.<MILESTONE N="64b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Se forme &aelig;admodnysse st&aelig;pe is hyrsumnysse wi&eth;uton<NOTE PLACE="foot">st&aelig;pe] sccepe <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &aelig;lcun&yogh;e. &THORN;eos &yogh;e&eth;afna&eth; heom, &thorn;e na &thorn;ing lewfre heom ne l&aelig;|to&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">lewfre <I>wie es scheint aus</I> leofre <I>corrig. v. 1. Corrector.</I></NOTE> &thorn;onne Crist, for &thorn;am hali&yogh;e &thorn;eowdome, &thorn;e hi&yogh; habbod be|hate, od&eth;o for hellewite ofdr&aelig;d&aelig;dnysse, od&eth;o for &thorn;&aelig;s ecean lifes wuldre. Sona swa heom &aelig;ni &thorn;ing fram heore ealdre beboden byd, hi &thorn;&aelig;t buton elcunge mid weorce &yogh;efremma&eth;, swylce hit fram Gode sylfe &yogh;eboden sy. Be swilcum drihten<MILESTONE N="65a" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;us cwy&eth;: "Of eares hlyste hi&yogh; hyrsumede me"; eft he se&yogh;&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;us <I>aus</I> &thorn;ur <I>rad. Hs.</I> &Verbar; cwy&eth;] c&thorn;y&eth; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> to &thorn;am lareowum: "&THORN;e &thorn;e eow &yogh;ehyr&eth;, he &yogh;ehir&eth; me, &amp; &thorn;e &thorn;e eow ascuno&eth;, he ascunod me".<NOTE PLACE="foot">ascunod] <I>danach ein</I> e <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Eornestlice, &thorn;a &thorn;e swylce synd, sona swa heom beboden by&eth;, heore a&yogh;ene willan aweorpa&eth; &amp; swa hwilce d&aelig;dan, swa hi&yogh; on hande habbo&eth;, unfullworhte l&aelig;ta&eth;<!--eth insertion stopped here--> &amp; mid hwatum hyr|sumnysse fet &thorn;&aelig; beodenden stefne mid weorce &yogh;efol&yogh;iad, &amp; swilce on anre handhwile seo fors&aelig;de d&aelig;s lareowes h&aelig;s &amp; &thorn;a fulfremede &thorn;es leorningmannes weorc mid Godes e&yogh;es cafscipe &yogh;em&aelig;nelice buta &thorn;a &thorn;ing beod &yogh;efillede.</P>
<P>On swilcum wunad seo lufu &thorn;&aelig;s f&aelig;reldes to ecum life, for&thorn;i &thorn;onne hi&yogh; &thorn;one ancgsuman wei&yogh; &yogh;eceorad, be &thorn;am se h&aelig;lend cwyd: "Angsum &amp; nearu is se wei, &thorn;e to life let",<NOTE PLACE="foot">Angsum] <I>zwischen</I> g <I>und</I> s <I>Ras. eines Buchst.</I> (<I>wahrscheinl.</I> c).</NOTE> &thorn;at is, &thorn;at hi&yogh; be heore a&yogh;enum dome ne libbe, ne heore a&yogh;enum lustum ne &yogh;ehyrsumian, ac be frendum mode &amp; h&aelig;se<NOTE PLACE="foot">h&aelig;se, s <I>aus</I> r <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE> donde sy, on mynstre wuniende, &thorn;&aelig;t abbodesse heom wealde 
<PB REF="00000057.tif" N="29"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="20,13-22,2"> &amp; t&aelig;ce a &yogh;ewilniad. Buton tweon, &thorn;a &thorn;e &thorn;yllice beod, hi&yogh; &yogh;eefenl&aelig;cced &thorn;one cwyde, &thorn;e drihten be him sylfe &thorn;us cw&aelig;d:<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eefenl&aelig;cced] <I>aus</I> &yogh;eefonl. <I>rad. Hs.</I> andsware] andware <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> "Ne com ic to donde myne a&yogh;enum willan, ac &thorn;as &thorn;e me sende". &THORN;os sylue hirsumnysse bid Gode andfenge &amp; mannum luftyme, &yogh;if &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ebodene byd &yogh;efremed unforhtlice, unsleaplice &amp; unasolcenlice &amp; buton ceorunge &amp; butan nellendre andsware;<MILESTONE N="65b" UNIT="folio"> seo hyrsumnisse to sode, &thorn;e bid &thorn;am ealdrum &yogh;e&yogh;earewod, heo byd Gode &yogh;edon; he sodlice &thorn;us sylf cwed: "Se &thorn;e eow &yogh;e|hirde, he &yogh;ehyrde me". And mid gode mode &amp; gledum &yogh;e&thorn;once<NOTE PLACE="foot">mid] mud <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> da underdiddan leornestran heore ealdrum hyran scullan, for|&thorn;am "&thorn;eo gl&aelig;de &yogh;efestre God lufad"; witodlice, &thorn;eah hwilc leornestra hyres ealdres h&aelig;se mid weorcum &yogh;efylle &amp; &that; mid<NOTE PLACE="foot">h&aelig;se] <I>aus</I> h&aelig;re <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE> mude beceorad odde mid mode besor&yogh;a&thorn;, ne byd hit Gode andfenge, &thorn;e &aelig;lces mannes heortan &thorn;urhsyhd, &aelig;nd for swylcere<NOTE PLACE="foot">andfenge, d. <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> d&aelig;de hu nane mede &aelig;t Gode ne onfehd, ac &yogh;yt ma on ecum wite mid &thorn;am murcnerum, &amp; gnorniende, &thorn;e Gode mishyrdon, beod &yogh;eset, buton heo mid fulre d&aelig;dbote hit &yogh;ebete.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>VI. HER HIT SPEC&ETH; EMBE SWI&YOGH;E &thorn;AT IS EMBE SILENCE.<MILESTONE N="66a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Vtan don swa swa &thorn;e wite&yogh;a myne&yogh;ad, &thorn;us cwedende: "Ic sede, ic wille healde mine wegas, &thorn;at ic ne gylte &thorn;urh mine tungan; ic sette mine mude weardunge, ic adumbode &amp; becom eadmod &amp; swigede goddere sp&aelig;ce." Mid &thorn;isum wordum<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;isum <I>aus</I> &thorn;irum <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e hali&yogh;e wite&yogh;a &yogh;eswutelad, &thorn;&aelig;t we scullan ydele worda for synnne wite &yogh;swigian: &thorn;anne he for swi&yogh;unge m&aelig;&yogh;ne oft god|dere sp&aelig;ce &yogh;eswac, eornestlice man sceal idelre worde &yogh;eswican.</P>
<P>&THORN;eah fulfremedan leornustran for swi&yogh;unga &yogh;ehealtsumnysse<NOTE PLACE="foot">fulfreme &mdash; <I>Zeilenschluss</I> &mdash; medan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> seldhw&aelig;nne leafe &yogh;eseald sy to specene embe hali&yogh;e spece &amp; gode &amp; fremfulle, for&thorn;i &thorn;e hit is &yogh;ewritan: "On mycelre spece &thorn;u n&aelig; forflihst synna"; &amp; eft is awriten: "Dead &amp; lif is on<NOTE PLACE="foot">Dead, <I>initiales</I> D <I>oder</I> &ETH;.</NOTE> &thorn;are tungan handen". For&thorn;an &thorn;e spece &amp; t&aelig;ce &thorn;are ma&yogh;stre &yogh;edafnad, swi&yogh;ie &amp; &yogh;ehyre &thorn;are leornestre &yogh;erist. And for&thorn;i<MILESTONE N="66b" UNIT="folio"> &yogh;yf hwet to axsyenne sy, &thorn;at beo &thorn;onne &yogh;eaxsod of &thorn;are ealdre 
<PB REF="00000059.tif" N="31"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="22,2-23,14"> mid ealre eadmodnysse &amp; under&thorn;idnisse &amp; mycelre arwyr&thorn;nysse, l&aelig;ste heo mare sp&aelig;ce, &thorn;enne hit fremye. Gabbunge oddo idele worde &amp; &thorn;a, &thorn;e leahter ar&aelig;red, mid ec&aelig;ne loce on &aelig;lcen steden we fordyttod, &amp; to swilcere sp&aelig;ce we ne alyfod, &that; &thorn;eo<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Das zweite</I> we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> leornestre hyre mud undo.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>VII. BE EADMODNUSSE.<MILESTONE N="67a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;&aelig;t godcunde &yogh;ewrit, swustre, us to eadmodnysse myne|gad, &thorn;us clypiende: "&AElig;lc &thorn;e hi ahefd, sceal beon &yogh;eni&thorn;erod, &amp; &thorn;eo &thorn;e hi &yogh;eny&thorn;erod, sceal beon &yogh;ehe&yogh;od". &THORN;urh &thorn;as cly|punge <NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Nach</I> hi <I>Rasur eines Striches oder Buchstaben.</I></NOTE> is &yogh;eswutelod, &thorn;at &aelig;lc upahafenesse aspringad of mo|dinesse cynne; wid &thorn;one un&thorn;eaw hine bewerode &thorn;e wite&yogh;a,<NOTE PLACE="foot">un&thorn;eaw <I>aus</I> un&thorn;ea&thorn; <I>radiert.</I> &Verbar; wite&yogh;a, <I>das</I> w <I>wegradiert Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;us cwe&thorn;ende: "Drihten, nis min heorte onhefd, ne myne ea&yogh;en upabrodene; ne ic ne ferde on michele &thorn;inga, ne ic of wunder|lican <NOTE PLACE="foot">on] om <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;ingan me ne bestag. Ac hw&aelig;t, gif ic eadmodlice ne lett of me sylue, ac mine sawle aheof? swa swa &thorn;&aelig;t suceling,<NOTE PLACE="foot">lett] lect <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e his moder hafod forworpan, forf&aelig;rd &amp; forweornad, ell swylc edlean on mine sawle becume".</P>
<P>For&thorn;i, leofen sustren, &yogh;if we &thorn;&aelig;ne hrof &thorn;are heahlican eadmodnysse ar&aelig;cen willat &amp; to &thorn;ere heofonlican anhefednysse, &thorn;e mid &thorn;ises andwearden lifes eadmodnysse byd &yogh;esti&yogh;an<MILESTONE N="67b" UNIT="folio"> caflyce cuman &thorn;eanced, seo hledre is mid urum dedum to r&aelig;|renne,<NOTE PLACE="foot">caflyce, <I>das</I> a <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e Jacob on sweuene weard onywed, &thorn;urh &thorn;a hym weron &yogh;eswotelede &aelig;&yogh;&thorn;er &yogh;e upsti&yogh;ende englas &yogh;e nudersti&yogh;ende. Nis buton tweon to understondenne se upsti&yogh;e &amp; se nu&thorn;ersti&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">understondenne <I>aus</I> understondonne <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> on nan o&thorn;re wisan, but&aelig;n &thorn;et heofona rices upsti&yogh;e mid ead|modnysse &yogh;eernod byd &amp; mid ofermodnysse forworht. Seo ar&aelig;r&aelig;de lhedre tacnad ure lif on &thorn;issere worelde, &thorn;&aelig;t mid eadmodere heortan &thorn;urh urne hlaford ar&aelig;red is to hefene; &thorn;are hl&aelig;ddre twa sydan tacniad urne lycame &amp; ure sawle; on &thorn;an sydum mystlic&aelig; st&aelig;pas of &aelig;admodnysse &amp; of &thorn;eawf&aelig;stnysse seo godcunde la&thorn;unge to sti&yogh;ende upp mid hafod &yogh;ef&aelig;stnod.<NOTE PLACE="foot">la&thorn;unge, <I>zw.</I> &thorn; <I>und</I> u <I>ein</I> i <I>radiert.</I></NOTE>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7b" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000061.tif" N="33"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="23,15-25,7">
<HEAD>VIIb. BE &THORN;AN TWELF STEEPEN OF EADMODNESSE; &THORN;IS IS &THORN;E FORMA ST&AElig;PE.</HEAD>
<DIV3 N="7b1" TYPE="step">
<P>Se forma eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe is, &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ehwa Godes e&yogh;e<MILESTONE N="68b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">st&aelig;pe] s&yogh;epe <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> habbe &amp; &aelig;tforan his ea&yogh;ena &yogh;esyh&thorn;e &aelig;fre sette &amp; ne sy for|&yogh;yttel ac &yogh;emyndi ealre &thorn;are &thorn;inga, &thorn;e ure drihten bebead, &amp; on hwylce wise &thorn;a, &thorn;e God forseod, for heore synne reosed into helle; &amp; &thorn;at ece lif, &thorn;e heom is &yogh;e&yogh;&aelig;rewed, &thorn;e beod of Gode ofdred, &aelig;fre mid hyre mode behealde &amp; &yogh;e&thorn;ence.</P>
<P>And &thorn;us sme&yogh;ende &yogh;ehealdan hi&yogh; on elce tyman fram<NOTE PLACE="foot">And] f., <I>daf&uuml;r Ras. v. 1-2 Buchst. Hs.</I></NOTE> hyre synnum &amp; leahtrum &aelig;&yogh;&thorn;er &yogh;e &yogh;e&thorn;ohta, &yogh;e sp&aelig;ce, &yogh;e &yogh;e|sy&thorn;a, <MILESTONE N="69a" UNIT="folio"> &amp; fram ealle yfelum d&aelig;dum, &amp; eac heora fleasclican lustes caflice forwurpe; wite manne &yogh;ehwilc, &thorn;at he bid &aelig;fre<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>zwischen</I> &aelig;fre <I>und</I> &yogh;esewen <I>Rasur eines</I> a.</NOTE> &yogh;esewen fram drihtne on heofonum on &aelig;lcne tyman; on &aelig;lcere stowe his d&aelig;de bed &yogh;esawene fram godcundre &yogh;esyhde &amp; on<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;esawene, s <I>aus</I> r <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> &aelig;lcene tyman fram englum bebodede; &thorn;at God on ure &yogh;e&thorn;oh|tum andweard is, se wite&yogh;a &yogh;eswutelad &thorn;us cwe&thorn;ende: "God asmead &aelig;&yogh;&thorn;er &yogh;e manne heortan &amp; eac heore &aelig;ddre"; eft he cwyd: "God wat mannum &thorn;encunge, &thorn;at hi&yogh; beod wace";<NOTE PLACE="foot">wat] <I>aus</I> &thorn;at <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> eft he cwed: "Drihten, &thorn;u on&yogh;eate mine &yogh;e&thorn;ohtes feorrene", &amp; "Mannes &yogh;e&thorn;onc &thorn;e &yogh;eandet". To&thorn;i &thorn;&aelig;t heo carefull sy ymbe hyre &thorn;weoran &yogh;e&thorn;ohtas, &aelig;fre sy nytwyrda swuster &thorn;us mid hyre heortan clypie: &thorn;onne ic beo unawemmud beforan Gode &yogh;yf ic me &yogh;ehealde fram mynre unrihtwisnesse.</P>
<P>Vre a&yogh;en willa us is forboden, &thorn;onne hal&yogh;e &yogh;ewrit &thorn;us<NOTE PLACE="foot">hal&yogh;e] hal <I>danach Ras. eines</I> &yogh;, <I>danach Zeilenschluss Hs.</I></NOTE> clypad: "Gecyr fram &thorn;inum lustum"; eft: on &yogh;ebede we hel|siad <NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> urne drihten, &thorn;at is willa on us beo &yogh;emacod. Ernestlice, we synd &yogh;elerede be &yogh;ewyrhton, &thorn;&aelig;t we urne a&yogh;ene willan ne weorcean, &thorn;onne we &thorn;&aelig;t forbu&yogh;ad, &that; &that; hal&yogh;e &yogh;ewrit us sei&yogh;&thorn;, &thorn;us cwe&thorn;ende: "Sume we&yogh;as syndon, &thorn;e mannum synd rihte &yogh;e&thorn;uhte, &thorn;are &aelig;nde &thorn;eah besencd on helle grunde"; &amp; eft we<MILESTONE N="69b" UNIT="folio"> sculen forbu&yogh;&aelig; &that; &that; is &yogh;esed beo &thorn;am &yogh;emelease: "Hi synd &yogh;ewemmode &amp; ands&aelig;te &yogh;ewordene an hyre a&yogh;en luste".
<PB REF="00000063.tif" N="35"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="25,8-27,1"></P>
<P>Wite we eac to so&thorn;en, &that; drichten &aelig;fre byd anweald on<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radiert.</I> &Verbar; <I>Zwischen</I> &aelig;fre <I>und</I> byd <I>ein</I> a <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> urum fl&aelig;sclicum lustum, &amp; hym ures an&yogh;ynnes nan &thorn;ing di&yogh;le beod; &thorn;at &yogh;eswutelod se wyte&yogh;a, &thorn;us to Gode clypienda: "Be|foran &thorn;e, drihten, is eal min willnung". Toscuniende is for&thorn;i yfel wyllung, for&thorn;an &thorn;e dead is &yogh;eset biside lustes inf&aelig;re; her of &thorn;at hal&yogh; &yogh;ewrit sp&aelig;cd, &thorn;us cwe&thorn;ende: "Ne far &thorn;u &aelig;fter &thorn;inum lustum".</P>
<P>Nu &thorn;onne &yogh;if Godes ea&yogh;an behealded &thorn;a godan &amp; swa yfelen, &amp; ure drihten of heofene locad uppe mannum bearn, &thorn;et he &yogh;eseo, hwe&thorn;er hera &aelig;n&yogh; and&yogh;yttol sy &amp; God secende,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;et] &that; et <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; &aelig;n&yogh;, <I>das</I> &yogh; <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; fram &thorn;am englum, &thorn;e ofer us beod &yogh;eset, ure d&aelig;dan da&yogh;es and nihtes God &aelig;lmihtin, ure scyppendum, beod &yogh;ecudde &mdash; on &aelig;lce tyma is to warienne, swa swa &thorn;e wite&yogh;a se&yogh;d on &thorn;an sealme, &that; we ne buh&yogh;ende into yfele &amp; unfremfulle &yogh;emacod<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radiert</I>.</NOTE> on suman timan beon of Gode &yogh;esewe, &amp; us &thorn;eah on &thorn;isne<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;isne] &thorn;irne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> tyman ary&yogh;e, for&thorn;am &thorn;e he milde is &amp; abidad, &thorn;&aelig;t we to beteran &yogh;ecyrran, segge to us eft on &thorn;are odre worolde: "&thorn;as &thorn;ing &yogh;e dyden, &amp; ic swi&yogh;ode".</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b2" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Oder.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e oder eadmodnesse st&aelig;pe is, &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ehwa his a&yogh;ene wil|lan <MILESTONE N="70a" UNIT="folio"> ne lufie, ne hyre a&yogh;ene lustes &yogh;efylle, ac mid dedum ures drihtenes stefne &yogh;eefenl&aelig;ce, &thorn;e &thorn;us be him silfe cwed; "Ic ne com to donde myne o&yogh;ene willan, ac &thorn;&aelig;s &thorn;e me sende". Eft &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ewrit seyd: "Gewill hafed wite, &amp; neade wuldorbeah &yogh;e&yogh;earwad", &thorn;at is, &that; &yogh;ehwa hi sylfe to &YOGH;ode nyde &amp; hyre a&yogh;ene lustes aweorpe.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b3" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>&THORN;ridde.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e &thorn;ridde eadmodinesse st&aelig;pe is, &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ewilc for Godes lufan mid ealre &yogh;ehyrsumnysse hyre ealdrum abu&yogh;e, fyliende urne drihte, be hwam &thorn;e apostel &thorn;us cwed: "He becom &yogh;ehyr|sum anan to dea&thorn;e".<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Zwischen</I> to <I>und</I> dea&thorn;e <I>Rasur von</I> &thorn;an.</NOTE></P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b4" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Feor&thorn;e.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e feor&thorn;e eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe is, &yogh;if heo on &thorn;are sylfan<MILESTONE N="70b" UNIT="folio"> hyrsumnesse on heardum &amp; on wy&thorn;erweardum &thorn;ingum &amp; on 
<PB REF="00000065.tif" N="37"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="27,1-28,17"> &yogh;ehwilcum teonrednum &yogh;e&thorn;yld lufian &amp; ne awaci&aelig;, na ne hyre<MILESTONE N="71a" UNIT="folio"> sta&thorn;el ne forl&aelig;te, ne awe&yogh; ne &yogh;ewite fram Gode, swa swa<NOTE PLACE="foot">sta&thorn;el] st&thorn;el <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ewrit sei&yogh;&thorn;: "Se &thorn;e &thorn;urhwunod od &aelig;nde, he beod &yogh;eheal|d&aelig;n"; eft is &yogh;ecweden on hal&yogh;e &yogh;ewrite: "Sy &yogh;estrangod &thorn;in heorte &amp; for&thorn;yldi&yogh;a &thorn;inna drihten" &that; is, &thorn;ole eal, &thorn;at God be &thorn;e &yogh;e&thorn;afod. And eft is onywed, &thorn;at &thorn;e &yogh;etrywfullan for Godes<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;etrywf., t <I>auf Rasur</I>.</NOTE> e&yogh;e ealle liues wi&thorn;erweardnesse &thorn;oli&yogh;an scule, swa swa &thorn;&aelig;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">scule <I>aus</I> reule <I>radiert</I>.</NOTE> &yogh;ewrit be heore &thorn;olemodnysse &thorn;us cwed: "For &thorn;e, drihten, we synd ealne dee&yogh; to dea&thorn;e &yogh;ew&aelig;hte; we synd to dea&thorn;e &yogh;etealde swa swa &thorn;a snidsceapp"; hi &thorn;eah sicera be &thorn;am tohopan<NOTE PLACE="foot">be] beo <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;es godcundes edleanes, &thorn;us &aelig;fterfilyendlice mid blysse cly|piad: "Ac on eallum &thorn;is &thorn;ingum we oforswi&thorn;don &thorn;urh &thorn;ane,<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radiert</I>.</NOTE> &thorn;e us lufede", &thorn;at is drihton; eft bi &thorn;are ylcan &thorn;olemodnesse on hal&yogh;e &yogh;ewrite is &thorn;us &yogh;ecweden: "Drihten, &thorn;u us afondedest,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ecweden] &yogh;ecwenden <I>Hs.</I> &thorn;u] &thorn;a <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;u us ameredest mid fyre, swa swa seolfer byd amered; &thorn;u us bel&aelig;ddest on grin, &thorn;u &yogh;esettest &yogh;edrefednesse on urne rigge";<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;edrefedn.] &yogh;erfednesse, <I>dar&uuml;ber ein Kreuz, das &uuml;ber vielen</I> Correcturen <I>steht und hier unbeachtet geblieben ist.</I></NOTE> eft &thorn;&aelig;t ylce hali&yogh;e &yogh;ewrit fordan &yogh;eswutelode, &that; we under ealdre &yogh;ymene beon sculon, &thorn;us cwe&thorn;ende: "&thorn;u settest menn ofor hyre heafde". Ge eac Godes bebeod on earfo&thorn;lican &thorn;ingan &amp; on<NOTE PLACE="foot">heafde] heaheafde <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; <I>Zwischen</I> on <I>und</I> earfo&thorn;l. <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile von sp&auml;trer Hand ein zweites</I> on.</NOTE> teonfullen &thorn;urh &thorn;olebyrdnysse &yogh;efyllod, &yogh;if hi beod &yogh;esmitan on &that; an hleor, wend ford &thorn;&aelig;t o&thorn;er; &thorn;am &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;ne cyrtel be|nymd, l&aelig;ted to &thorn;&aelig;ne mentel; &yogh;yf hi beod &yogh;enidd to gande<MILESTONE N="71b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;am <I>aus</I> &thorn;ann <I>radiert</I>.</NOTE> forberd &amp; ehtnesse &thorn;olad for rihtwisnysse &amp; &thorn;a, &thorn;e hi cursi&yogh;od, bletsiad.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b5" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Fifta.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e fifta eadmodnyssa stape is, &yogh;if &thorn;eo mynecena &thorn;urh eadmodre andetnesse hyre abbodysse ne di&yogh;lad ealle &thorn;a yfole &yogh;e&thorn;anc, &thorn;e comed to hyre heorte, &amp; &thorn;a yfele d&aelig;dan, &thorn;e heo d&aelig;d odde di&yogh;ellicen hafod &yogh;edon. Be &thorn;am halie &yogh;ewrite us<NOTE PLACE="foot">halie <I>aus</I> hal&yogh;e <I>corrigirt</I>.</NOTE> myne&yogh;ad, &thorn;us cwe&thorn;ende: "Vnwreoh God ealmihtye &thorn;inne wey,<NOTE PLACE="foot">myne&yogh;ad <I>aus</I> myn&yogh;ad <I>corrigirt</I>. &Verbar; wey <I>aus</I> we&yogh; <I>corrig</I>.</NOTE> &thorn;at is, &thorn;ine d&aelig;de &amp; hiht an hine; &amp; eft hit cwyd: "Andettad 
<PB REF="00000067.tif" N="39"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="28,17-30,6"> to ure drihten, for&thorn;am &thorn;e he is god, for&thorn;am &thorn;e is miltsa is on ecnesse"; &amp; eft cwed se wite&yogh;a: "Minne gylt ic cydde &thorn;e, &amp; myne unrihwisnysse ic ne hydde; ic cw&aelig;d, ic wylle bodi&yogh;e<MILESTONE N="72a" UNIT="folio"> to&yogh;enes me myne unrihtwisnessen min drihten, &amp; &thorn;u me foryefe<NOTE PLACE="foot">drihten <I>auf Rasur</I>. &Verbar; foryefe] forwefe, <I>das</I> w <I>anradiert</I></NOTE> mynre heorten arleasnesse.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b6" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Syxte.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e syxte eadmodnysse steepe is, &yogh;yf &thorn;are mynecene byd &yogh;ecweme, &that; heo unwyrdost &amp; l&aelig;tem&aelig;st beo &yogh;eteald, &amp; to eallum &thorn;am &thorn;ingum, &thorn;e hyre beod bet&aelig;ht to donde, tellan hy syluen yfolne wrihtan &amp; unwyrdna &amp; &thorn;us mid &thorn;am wite&yogh;an clypie:<NOTE PLACE="foot">wite|&yogh;an, e <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile, Hs.</I></NOTE> "To nane &thorn;inge ic eam bycuman, &amp; ic hit nyste; swa swa &thorn;at nyten ic eom &yogh;eworden to&yogh;eanes &thorn;e, &amp; &aelig;fre ic eom myd &thorn;e.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b7" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Seofa&thorn;e.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e seofa&thorn;e eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe ys, &yogh;if &thorn;eo mynecena hi<MILESTONE N="72b" UNIT="folio"> sylue uttran &amp; unweor&thorn;est telle, na &that; an mid hyre mude secge and ec mid hyre heorte f&aelig;stlice &yogh;elife, hy sylue &yogh;eadmede &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">and] an Hs. &Verbar; ec <I>aus</I> &yogh;ec <I>radiert</I>.</NOTE> &thorn;us mid &thorn;an wite&yogh;an cwede: "Ic eam &yogh;ewis wyrm &amp; n&aelig;ng man, manenen edwit &amp; folces &aelig;wyrp". "Anhafen ic eam &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">edwit <I>auf Rasur, wovon der 1. Buchst. ein</I> w.</NOTE> &yogh;enydered &amp; &yogh;esc&aelig;nd"; &amp; eft se wite&yogh;a se&yogh;d: "God is me, drihten &that; &thorn;u me &yogh;eny&thorn;eradest, &thorn;at ic ma&yogh;e leornie &thorn;ine beboda".</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b8" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Eahte&thorn;a.<NOTE PLACE="foot">mynenecena <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; &thorn;ing] &thorn;ng <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e eahte&thorn;a eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe is, &yogh;if &thorn;eo mynecena nan &thorn;ing ne de&thorn;, buten &thorn;at se &yogh;em&aelig;ne mynsterre&yogh;ol t&aelig;cd, oddo &thorn;at &thorn;are heah&thorn;ungenra forbisena l&aelig;rad.<NOTE PLACE="foot">heah&thorn;ungenra] heah&thorn;unge ura <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b9" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Ny&yogh;ede.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e ny&yogh;ede eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe is, &yogh;ef &thorn;eo mynecena hyre tunga forwyrnod to specende &amp; habbon swi&yogh;unga &amp; ne sp&aelig;ce,<MILESTONE N="73a" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;r he beo &yogh;eahsod, for&thorn;an &thorn;at hali&yogh;e &yogh;ewrit swutelod, &that; on maniefealde spece ne byd syn forbo&yogh;en, &amp; for&thorn;i &thorn;e se f&aelig;le talyende man uppon eor&thorn;e ne &yogh;e&thorn;ihd.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e&thorn;ihd] &yogh;e <I>dann ein anradiertes</I> f, <I>dann ein radiertes</I> i (?) <I>hierauf</I> hd. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE>
</P>

</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b10" TYPE="step"><PB REF="00000069.tif" N="41"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="30,7-32,6">
<HEAD>Teoda.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e teoda eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe is, &yogh;if &thorn;eo mynecena ne beo galsmere &amp; r&aelig;d on hleahtre, for&thorn;i &thorn;e hit is &yogh;ewritan: "Se gi|die<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e] he, <I>das</I> h <I>etwas anradiert Hs.</I></NOTE> on his hle&aelig;htre his stefene onhefd".</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b11" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Endlyfta.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e endlyfta eadmodnyssa st&aelig;pe is, &yogh;if &thorn;e mynechena, &thorn;enne heo spece, ly&thorn;elice, buton hleahtre, eadmodlice mid &thorn;eaufulre hefynesse feawe word &amp; &yogh;er&aelig;delice speca, &amp; ne beo oferlud on hire stefene, swa swa hit awriten is: "Se &thorn;e wis is, mid f&aelig;wum wordum he hit swutelad".</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 N="7b12" TYPE="step">
<HEAD>Twelft&aelig;.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;e twelfta eadmodnysse st&aelig;pe is, &yogh;if &thorn;e mynecena na &thorn;at<MILESTONE N="73b" UNIT="folio"> an mid hyre heorte, ac eac mid hyre lycame eadmodnysse eallum &thorn;am, &thorn;e hyre onlociad, &aelig;fre sceawi&yogh;e, &thorn;&aelig;t is on weorce,<MILESTONE N="74a" UNIT="folio"> on &yogh;ebedhuse, on mynstre, on wyrtearde, on we&yogh;e, on felde, oddo swa hwar swa heo sy sittende, standende, oddo gangende, &aelig;fre beo hniwiende mid hyre heafede, hyre &yogh;esihda adun on<NOTE PLACE="foot">hniwiende] hnipiende <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> eor&thorn;an besette. And tellan hy sylfe scyldi&yogh; on &aelig;lcene timan<NOTE PLACE="foot">tellan, e <I>auf Ras.</I> (<I>eines</I> i?).</NOTE> for hyre synnan, &amp; ho&yogh;ien &aelig;fre, swylce hu to &thorn;an e&yogh;fulle Godes dome &thorn;eryhte &yogh;eled sculle beon; &aelig;fre on hyre herte segge to hyre sylfre, &that; &that; se manfulle on &thorn;am godspelle besettum ea&yogh;um<NOTE PLACE="foot">besettum] besectum <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on &thorn;a eor&thorn;an cwed: "Drihten, ic sunfulle ne eom weor&thorn;e, &thorn;at ic mine ea&yogh;an to heofonum ahebbe"; &amp; &aelig;ft mit &thorn;am wyta&yogh;e: "Ic eom &yogh;ebi&yogh;ed &aelig;&yogh;hwar &amp; &yogh;eni&thorn;erod".</P>
<P>Syddan &thorn;eo mynecene eallan &thorn;as eadmodnysse upst&aelig;pes &yogh;estihd, heo cymd sone to &thorn;are sodan Godes lufe, &thorn;e e&yogh;e utan drifd; &thorn;urh &thorn;a lufe ealle &thorn;a &thorn;ing, &thorn;e heo &aelig;r heold n&aelig;ng wid|uton<NOTE PLACE="foot">26-27. utan drifd] ut anrifd <I>Hs.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">heold] heod <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ofdr&aelig;d&aelig;dnesse, ac buton &aelig;n&yogh;e &yogh;eswynce swilce &yogh;ecun|delice for &thorn;are &yogh;ewunsumnysse heo be&yogh;ynd to healdenne, na for hellewites e&yogh;e, ac for Cristes lufe &amp; for &thorn;are sylfre goddere &yogh;ewunsumnesse &amp; &thorn;&aelig;w&aelig;ne licunge. &THORN;e ure drihte on his wyrhte,<NOTE PLACE="foot">his <I>aus</I> &thorn;is <I>radiert.</I></NOTE> sone swo he byd cl&aelig;ne of un&thorn;&aelig;awon &amp; of synnum, bli&thorn;elice swutelod.
</P>

</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000071.tif" N="43"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="32,7-33,15">
<HEAD>VIII. BE CRISTES &THORN;ENUNGE ON NIHT.<MILESTONE N="74b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>On wintres tyman, &thorn;&aelig;t is fr&aelig;m &thorn;an an&yogh;inne &thorn;&aelig;s mon&thorn;es,<NOTE PLACE="foot">is <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e is nouember &yogh;ehaten, fort eastron, &aelig;fter &yogh;esc&aelig;ades fore|sceawunge on &thorn;are eahta&thorn;an tide &thorn;are nihte is to arisenne, &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;a mynecene sum del mare reston &thorn;anne healfe &thorn;e niht, &thorn;&aelig;t seo d&aelig;&yogh;es &thorn;i&yogh;en tofered sy on &thorn;are nihtlican reste &amp; seo h&aelig;te &thorn;ere &thorn;i&yogh;ene ofersle&yogh;en &amp; se ma&yogh;e &yogh;elyht &amp; swa arysen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;elyht, ht <I>auf Rasur von etwas sp&auml;trer Hand.</I></NOTE> &THORN;&aelig;t &thorn;&aelig;re nihte to lafe sy after &thorn;am utsange, &thorn;&aelig;t sy &yogh;enoted<NOTE PLACE="foot">utsange] unstrange, <I>&uuml;ber</I> un <I>von sp&auml;terer Hand</I> ut, <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mid sealmsonge &amp; mid leornunge gastlycere cr&aelig;fte butan sl&aelig;pe.</P>
<P>Fram eastron odd &thorn;a fores&aelig;dan kalendes nouembris swa sy &yogh;emeto&yogh;od &thorn;&aelig;s uhtsanges time, &thorn;&aelig;t a litol wile &thorn;&aelig;r&aelig;fter<NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;fter] &aelig;lter <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> beo &yogh;ehealden, &thorn;at &thorn;a sustren ma&yogh;ie gan ut to &yogh;ecyndrelicere neode, &amp; fylie anan &thorn;one d&aelig;&yogh;r&aelig;dsang, se is to a&yogh;ynnenne, &thorn;onne<MILESTONE N="75a" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;&aelig;s d&aelig;&yogh;es lyht a&yogh;ynd.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>IX. HU FELE SEALMAS SYND TO SEC&YOGH;ENDE ON<MILESTONE N="75b" UNIT="folio"> NIHTLICERE TIDE.</HEAD>
<P>On wyntres timen is se utsang &thorn;us to b&aelig;&yogh;ynnenne; &aelig;rest beo &yogh;eredd &thorn;is fers: "<I>Deus</I> in adiutorium meum intende"; &thorn;onne &thorn;ar&aelig;fter ist o seggenne &thorn;riwwe: "Domine labia mea aperies, et os meum annuntiabit laudem tuam"; her&aelig;fter scel beon &yogh;esed se &thorn;ridde sealm: "Domine quid multiplicati sunt", mid "Gloria patri", &thorn;onne "Uenite exultemus <I>domino</I>" mid ant&aelig;fne oddo abuton ant&aelig;fne is to singenne; fyly&yogh;e &thorn;onne se ambro|sianisce<NOTE PLACE="foot">is] if <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ymne, &thorn;onne six sealmes mid heore ant&aelig;fnen. &AElig;fter &thorn;an sealmun beo &thorn;onne &yogh;esed &thorn;at uerss &amp; &thorn;are abbodesse bletsunge, &amp; sitten &thorn;onne ealle on heore stolum; r&aelig;don &thorn;onne<NOTE PLACE="foot">sitten] rihten, r <I>unten anrad. Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;a swustre embestunde on &thorn;are boc on uppen &thorn;an bocsc&aelig;mele &thorn;reo reddingan &amp; singan &thorn;ry&yogh; reps&aelig;s. &AElig;fter &thorn;are &thorn;riddan r&aelig;|dunge 
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="45"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="33,16-35,8"> &thorn;eo, &thorn;e synga, segge &thorn;ane gloria; son&aelig; swa &thorn;eo singestre &thorn;ane <I>gloria</I> a&yogh;ynn&aelig;d, anan ealle &thorn;a swustren arisen of heore s&aelig;te for arwyr&thorn;nesse &thorn;are hali&yogh;e &thorn;reomnesse. &AElig;fter &thorn;an ut|sangan reden m&aelig;n &thorn;a becc godcundre lare &aelig;&yogh;&thorn;or &yogh;e of &thorn;are ealdon &aelig;, &yogh;e of &thorn;are nywe, &amp; eac heore trahtes, &thorn;e namcu&thorn;e<MILESTONE N="76a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e] &yogh;ec <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> f&aelig;deres &amp; ryhtbelyuedum lar&thorn;eawes &yogh;eworht habbod. &AElig;fter &thorn;is &thorn;reom r&aelig;ddungen mid heore repsan fyli&yogh;an o&thorn;re syx sealmes, &thorn;a syn &yogh;esungen mid "Alleluia"; &aelig;fter &thorn;am filye &thorn;&aelig;t captel of &thorn;are apostele lare, &thorn;at beo &yogh;esed buten bocc, &amp; &that; ferss, &amp; &thorn;eo healsung&yogh;ebun, &thorn;at is "Kyrieleyson", &amp; &thorn;us sy &yogh;een|dod<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;eo] &thorn;reo <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> se nihtlice uhtsang.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>X. HU ME SCEALL SINGE VHTSANG ON SUMERLICHE TIME.</HEAD>
<P>Fram eastron od kalendas nouembris sy at uhtsange &yogh;e|heoldon<NOTE PLACE="foot">at] &thorn;at <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &aelig;alle &thorn;es sealmesanges mycelnisse, &thorn;e we her before<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e we] &thorn;e &thorn;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ecwedon, buton &thorn;am anum &thorn;at on nanre boc ne beo r&aelig;dinge &yogh;ered, for &thorn;am scortum nihtum, &aelig;c for &thorn;am &thorn;reom r&aelig;ddingan an redinge sy &yogh;er&aelig;d buten boc of &thorn;are ealden &yogh;ecydnisse, &thorn;are r&aelig;dinge fyli&yogh;e an scort reps; &amp; ealle &thorn;o odre &thorn;ing sy<MILESTONE N="76b" UNIT="folio"> &yogh;efyllod swa &thorn;e &yogh;es&aelig;d is: &thorn;&aelig;t sy swa, &thorn;&aelig;t n&aelig;fre l&aelig;s sealme<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e] we <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ne sy &yogh;esungen &aelig;t uhtsange &thorn;onne twelf, wi&thorn;uton: "Domine quid multiplicati sunt" &amp; "Venite exultemus <I>Domino</I>".</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XI. BE SUNNAN DEGES VHTSANGE AND HU ME SCEALL<MILESTONE N="77a" UNIT="folio"> ARISEN ON &THORN;A NEHT.</HEAD>
<P>On &thorn;an sunnenda&yogh;e man sceal ra&thorn;or arison to uhtsange. On &thorn;am uhtsange man sceal healdon &thorn;&aelig;t ylca &yogh;emet, &thorn;e we er bufan &yogh;ecwedon, &thorn;&aelig;t is be twelf sealme; syngan man &aelig;rest syx sealmes &amp; &thorn;&aelig;t fers, &aelig;fter &thorn;am, heom eallum endebyrdlice 
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="47"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="35,8-37,2"> sittende, beon &yogh;er&aelig;d feower readinge mid feower repsum; &aelig;fter &thorn;am feor&thorn;e r&aelig;pse, &thorn;enne man synge "<I>Gloria patri</I>", anan arisan ealle mid arwyr&thorn;nesse, &amp; syngan o&thorn;re syx sealmes mid &thorn;reom &aelig;nt&aelig;fne &amp; &thorn;&aelig;t fers. &THORN;&aelig;r&aelig;fter beon &yogh;ered efsona odr&aelig; feower r&aelig;dinge mid heore repsan on &thorn;a ylce endebyrdnesse,<NOTE PLACE="foot">endebyrdn.] ende&thorn;yrdn. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e we bufon cwedon. &THORN;ar&aelig;fter &thorn;ri canticles beon &yogh;&aelig;s&aelig;d of &thorn;are wite&yogh;en bocan, swilce &thorn;y abbodesse hafod &yogh;esette, &thorn;a beon<MILESTONE N="77b" UNIT="folio"> mid "Alleluia" &yogh;esungena. And syddon &thorn;&aelig;t fers &amp; &yogh;eseald &thorn;are abbodesse bletsunge, beon &yogh;er&aelig;d o&thorn;ere feower r&aelig;dunge of &thorn;are niwe cydnesse &thorn;are &aelig;nbyrdnesse, &thorn;e we before cwedon. &AElig;fter &thorn;am fer&thorn;a repsa be&yogh;inn &thorn;eo abbedesse &thorn;ane lofsang: "Te deum laudamus"; &thorn;onne he beo &yogh;eendod, r&aelig;de se preost &thorn;&aelig;t godspell mid arwirdnysse &amp; mid godcunden e&yogh;e, heom eallum standende; &aelig;t &thorn;&aelig;s godspelles endunge andswarie ealle "Amen", &aelig;nd &thorn;ar&aelig;fter be&yogh;inne se preost: "Te decet laus", &amp; &aelig;fter &thorn;are bletsunge sy a&yogh;unne se d&aelig;&yogh;redsang.</P>
<P>Seo endbyrdnesse sunnenda&yogh;ene uhtsanges sy &yogh;elice &yogh;heal|den<NOTE PLACE="foot">uhtsanges <I>aus</I> utsanges <I>corrig.</I></NOTE> on &aelig;lcne tymen, &yogh;e on wintre &yogh;e on sumere, buton hit f&aelig;rlice swa &yogh;elimpe, &thorn;&aelig;t man l&aelig;ter arise, &thorn;onne hit &yogh;ebyri&yogh;e, &amp; man b&aelig;d&aelig;le r&aelig;din&yogh;e odde repsas &yogh;escyrte, &thorn;at ne &yogh;ewur&thorn;e, &thorn;at &thorn;yllic &yogh;ymelest &yogh;elimpe. Sy &yogh;eorne bewarnod, &thorn;&aelig;t hit ne<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eorne, -orne <I>auf Ras., urspr&uuml;ngl. scheint</I> &yogh;erne <I>gestanden zu haben.</I></NOTE> &yogh;esele; &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;if hit &yogh;elimpe, d&aelig;dbete heo on&yogh;en God on &thorn;an &yogh;ebedehuse, &thorn;urh hwylcere &yogh;yemelyste hit &yogh;elamp.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XII. BE SUNNANDEGES DEGREDSANGE.<MILESTONE N="78a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>On &thorn;am d&aelig;&yogh;r&aelig;dsange on sunnend&aelig;&yogh;e &aelig;rest man sceal singen &thorn;&aelig;ne syxandsyxti&yogh;e&thorn;an sealm wi&thorn;uton anteafne for|&thorn;rihte; &aelig;fter &thorn;am beo &yogh;esed se fiftu&yogh;e&thorn;e mid "<I>Alleluia</I>"; &aelig;fter &thorn;am beo &yogh;es&aelig;d se hundsyfenteo&thorn;e &amp; se twaandsyxtu&yogh;e&thorn;a, &thorn;&aelig;r|&aelig;fter &thorn;e bletsungen &amp; se lofsealm, &thorn;onne an redinge of apo|calypsi buten boc, &thorn;onne reps, ymne, fers, se sang of &thorn;an gode|spelle, h&aelig;lsunge, &amp; swa beod &yogh;efellod.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000077.tif" N="49"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="37,3-38,16">
<HEAD>XIII. BE WURUCDAE&yogh;EN D&AElig;&yogh;R&AElig;DSANGE.<MILESTONE N="78b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>On weorcda&yogh;um d&aelig;&yogh;redsanges weordung is &thorn;us to heal|denne, &thorn;&aelig;t is &thorn;at se syxansyxtu&yogh;e&thorn;e sealm, &thorn;at is "Deus mi|sereatur nostri" sy &yogh;ecwedon buton antiefne, sumd&aelig;l dra&yogh;ende, ealswa on sunnenda&yogh;en, &thorn;&aelig;t ealle ma&yogh;en coman to &thorn;an fiftu|&yogh;edan sealme, &thorn;e is mid antefne to be&yogh;eonnenne, &thorn;at is "Mise|rere<MILESTONE N="79a" UNIT="folio"> mei Deus". &AElig;fter &thorn;an odre twe&yogh;ene sealmes beon &yogh;esed &aelig;fter &yogh;ewunelicum &thorn;eaweum, &thorn;at is on monand&aelig;&yogh;e se fifte sealm &amp; se fifand&thorn;ritu&yogh;e&thorn;a, &thorn;at is "Uerba mea", &amp; "Dixit iniustus";<NOTE PLACE="foot">fifand&thorn;ritu&yogh;e&thorn;a] fifandfiftu&yogh;e&thorn;a <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on &thorn;an &thorn;ridde da&yogh;e se twaandfeortu&yogh;e&thorn;e sealm &amp; se syxand|fiftu&yogh;e&thorn;a, &thorn;at is "Judica me Deus", &amp; "Miserere mei <I>Deus</I>, mi|serere mei"; on &thorn;an feor&thorn;e d&aelig;&yogh;e, se &thorn;reoandsyxtu&yogh;e&thorn;a &amp; feor|andsyxtu&yogh;e&thorn;a, &thorn;at is "Exaudi <I>Deus</I> orationem meam cum deprecor" &amp; "Te decet ympnus"; on &thorn;an fiften d&aelig;&yogh;e se syfene|andhundeahtati&yogh;e&thorn;a &amp; se ni&yogh;enandhundeahtati&yogh;e&thorn;a, &thorn;at is "<I>Domine</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">15.-16. syfeneandhundeah|tete&thorn;a] -hundseofente&thorn;a <I>Hs.</I> -hundeahtati&yogh;e&thorn;a] -hundneo&yogh;onti&yogh;e&thorn;a <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> <I>Deus</I> salutis mee", &amp; "<I>Domine</I> refugium"; on &thorn;an syxte d&aelig;&yogh;e se fifandhundseofentu&yogh;e&thorn;a &amp; se anendhundni&yogh;enteo&thorn;a, &thorn;at is "Notus in Judea <I>Deus</I>", &amp; "Bonum est confiteri <I>Domino</I>"; on &thorn;an seterd&aelig;&yogh;e se hundrede&thorn;eandtwaandfeortu&yogh;e&thorn;a, &thorn;at is "<I>Do|mine</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">hundred.] hudr. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> exaudi orationem meam auribus percipe", &amp; se canticle deutronomio, &thorn;at is "Audite celi", se sy tod&aelig;lud on twe&yogh;en glorian. Elles odrum d&aelig;&yogh;um on &thorn;are wucum sy &yogh;esungan an canticle of &thorn;are wte&yogh;an boc, &thorn;e to &thorn;am d&aelig;&yogh;e belympd, swa<NOTE PLACE="foot">wte&yogh;an, <I>das</I> e <I>aus</I> o <I>radirt.</I> &Verbar; belympd] belimpd <I>aus</I> bel&yogh;mpd <I>corrigirt Hs.</I></NOTE> swa hit &thorn;eo romanisce cyrce healde, &thorn;at is on monand&aelig;&yogh;e "Confitebor", on tiwesd&aelig;&yogh;e "Ego dixi", on wodnesd&aelig;&yogh;e "Exul|tauit",<NOTE PLACE="foot">tiwersd&aelig;&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on &thorn;unresd&aelig;&yogh;e "Cantemus", on frid&aelig;&yogh;e "Domine audiui". &AElig;&aelig;fter &thorn;am &aelig;lce d&aelig;&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;ne lofsealme, &that; is "Laudate dominum<MILESTONE N="79b" UNIT="folio"> de celis", sy&thorn;on an r&aelig;ding of &thorn;are apostole lare &yogh;emendlice<NOTE PLACE="foot">of] on <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> buten boc &yogh;ecwe&thorn;on, se reps, hymne, fers, se canticle of &thorn;am godspelle, &thorn;&aelig;t is "Benedictus", &thorn;e helsunge, &thorn;&aelig;t is "Kyrieleison" &amp; hit beod &yogh;efyllod.</P>
<P>Ne sy na &yogh;eendod na&thorn;er ne d&aelig;&yogh;redsang ne &aelig;fensang an nane wise, buton &that; drihtelice &yogh;ebedd, &thorn;at is "Pater noster",<NOTE PLACE="foot">33-34. an nane] anane <I>Hs.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">drihtelice] drhtel. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000079.tif" N="51"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="38,16-40,5"> beo &yogh;esed of &thorn;are abbodesse, &that; ealle &yogh;ehyran for &thorn;an dornan of un&thorn;eawan, &thorn;e beod &yogh;ewunod to aspring&aelig;nne, &thorn;&aelig;t hi&yogh; beon &yogh;enydd &thorn;urh &thorn;&aelig;s ylc&aelig;s &yogh;ebedes beh&aelig;se, &thorn;e hi&yogh; s&aelig;gged: "Drihten,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ebedes] &yogh;ebes <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> for&yogh;if us ure synnan, swa swa we for&yogh;ifod &thorn;an, &thorn;e wid us habbod agylt", clensye hi sylfon of &thorn;illican un&thorn;eowon. &AElig;t &aelig;lcan odrum tidum &thorn;&aelig;s ylc&aelig;s &yogh;ebedes l&aelig;temeste d&aelig;l beo &yogh;esed, &that; fram eallum sy &yogh;eandswerod: "<I>Sed</I> libera nos a malo".<NOTE PLACE="foot">&that; <I>f. Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XIV. HU MAN SCEALL SINGAN ON HAL&yogh;ENAN MESSEDA&yogh;UN.</HEAD>
<P>On Godes hal&yogh;ena freolstydum &amp; on &aelig;alcan odrum masse|d&aelig;&yogh;um, swa swa we habbod &yogh;esed, &thorn;at man sceal don on &thorn;an<MILESTONE N="80a" UNIT="folio"> sunnenda&yogh;e, eallswa beo &thorn;onne &yogh;edon; wi&thorn;utan &thorn;an &that; &thorn;e sealmes &amp; anteofenes &amp; r&aelig;dingan, &thorn;e &yogh;erysod to &thorn;an d&aelig;&yogh;e, beon &yogh;es&aelig;d, &aelig;c &thorn;at ylca &yogh;emett, &thorn;&aelig;t her bufon awriton is, hit beo &yogh;eheldon.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="15" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XV. ON HWYLCE TIME MAN SCEALL SEC&yogh;AN "ALLELUIA".</HEAD>
<P>Fram eastron forte pentecosten sy "Alleluia" buton tod&aelig;led|nesse &yogh;esungon, &aelig;&yogh;&thorn;or &yogh;e on sealmum &yogh;e on repsum. Fram<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Das</I> 2. &yogh;e] we <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> pentecosten od lenctenes an&yogh;ynne, &aelig;lce niht &aelig;t uhtsange sy "Alleluia" &yogh;esungon mid &thorn;an syx &aelig;ftresealmum; &aelig;lcan sunnan|niht wi&thorn;uton lenctane &thorn;a canticlas &amp; d&aelig;&yogh;r&aelig;dsang, primsang, undernsang, midd&aelig;&yogh;sang, nonsang mid "Alleluia" si &yogh;esunge; &aelig;fensang beo &yogh;esed mid antiefene; &thorn;e repses n&aelig;fre ne sy &yogh;e|sungone mid "Alleluia", buton fram eastron od pentecosten.<MILESTONE N="80b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">alle|leua <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; buton] huton <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="16" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XVI. HU ME SCEALL ON DA&yogh; GODES WEORC WYRCEAN.</HEAD>
<P>Vte we don swa swa se wyte&yogh;a cwed: "Seofensydum on d&aelig;&yogh; ic &thorn;e, drihten, herode &amp; &thorn;in lof s&aelig;de". &THORN;&aelig;t h&aelig;li&yogh;e seofen|fealde 
<PB REF="00000081.tif" N="53"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="40,5-41,13"> &yogh;etell byd &thorn;us &thorn;urh us &yogh;efillod, &yogh;if d&aelig;&yogh;redsang, prim|sang, undernsang, midd&aelig;&yogh;sang, nonsang, &aelig;fensang, nihtsang<NOTE PLACE="foot">1-2. primsang, g <I>aus einem</I> m <I>corrig. und rad.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">undernsant <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> beod &yogh;efillod &thorn;urh ures deowdomes &thorn;enunge; fordi bi &thorn;an tydum se wtega sede: "Seofontydum on &thorn;an d&aelig;&yogh;e hic, drichten, &thorn;e herode"; eac se ylca wite&yogh;a be &thorn;an uhtweccum &thorn;us se&yogh;d: "To middere nihte ic aras, drihten, &thorn;e to andettene". Eornestlice, on &thorn;isum tyman herian we urne scyppand for &thorn;an doman of<MILESTONE N="81a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;isum] &thorn;irum <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> his rihtwisnesse, &thorn;at is on &thorn;an d&aelig;&yogh;rede, on prime, on under|nen, on mydde&yogh;i, on none, on efene, on nihtsange, &thorn;at is compli; &amp; on &thorn;are niht arise we &amp; drihtene we<NOTE PLACE="foot">we] &yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> and&yogh;iettan.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XVII. HU FELAN SEALMAS MAN SCEALL TO &THORN;AN DA&yogh;TIDEN<MILESTONE N="81b" UNIT="folio"> SEC&yogh;EN.</HEAD>
<P>Nv we habbad &yogh;efadod &thorn;a endebyrnysse &thorn;es sealmsanges, &thorn;e to uhtsange odde d&aelig;&yogh;redsange &yogh;ebyred; ute nu behawian be &thorn;am odrum tydum. To primsange syn &thorn;ri sealmes &yogh;e|cwedene &aelig;lc on sundran &amp; na under anum "Gloria"; &aelig;r man &thorn;e sealmes be&yogh;ynne, sy ymne &yogh;esungen, &thorn;e to &thorn;ere tyde be|limpe,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;esunsungen <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &aelig;fter &thorn;am ferse: "<I>Deus</I> in adiutorium meum intende". &AElig;fter &yogh;eendun&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re &thorn;reore sealme sy an captel &yogh;ecweden &amp; &thorn;at fers &amp; "kyrieleison", &amp; &thorn;o beon mid &yogh;ebedon &yogh;eendode. On undern &amp; on mide&yogh;i &amp; on non &thorn;at ylce &yogh;ebed &thorn;&aelig;ra ylcan endebyrdnysse sy &yogh;ewurdod, &thorn;at is mid ferse &amp; mid ymne &thorn;&aelig;ra tyda, mid &thorn;reom sealmum, mid r&aelig;dinge &amp; mid ferse &amp; mid "kyrieleison", &amp; swo mid &yogh;ebede beon &yogh;eendode. Gyf it mycel &yogh;efer&aelig;den is, sy hi mid antiefene, &amp; &yogh;yf seo &yogh;eferedden lytel byd, syn hi for&thorn;ricte buton ant&yogh;efena &yogh;esungena. &ETH;es<NOTE PLACE="foot">for|hricte <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &aelig;fensanges lof sy mid feor sealmum &yogh;eendod mid heora anteo|fenum,<NOTE PLACE="foot">feor] feor&thorn;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; syddan sy anes capteles reding &yogh;ecweden, &amp; syddan<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ecweden] &yogh;echeden <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> reps &amp; se ambrosien, &that; is se ymne, &amp; &thorn;at fers &amp; se lofsang on &thorn;an godspelle, &thorn;at is: "Magnificat", halsun&yogh;, &thorn;at is: "Kyrieleison",<MILESTONE N="82a" UNIT="folio"> 
<PB REF="00000083.tif" N="55"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="41,13-42,25"> &amp; drihtenlic &yogh;ebed, &thorn;at is: "Pater noster", &amp; sy swa mid &yogh;ebede &yogh;eendod. Nihtsang, &thorn;at is cumplie, si mid &thorn;rim sealmen &yogh;een|dod; &thorn;e sealmes syn &yogh;esungene for&thorn;rihte butan antiefene, &amp; sydan ymen, &thorn;e to &thorn;&aelig;re tyde belimpe, &amp; anes capteles r&aelig;ding &amp; fers &amp; "kyrieleison" &amp; seo bletsun&yogh;, &amp; swa beo hit &yogh;eendot.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="18" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XVIII. BE HWYLCERE FADUN&yogh;E MAN SCEALL &THORN;A<MILESTONE N="83b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">HWYLCERE] hwylecwe <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> SEALMES SIN&yogh;ON.</HEAD>
<P>Syn &aelig;fre &thorn;a d&aelig;&yogh;lican tida on frumen be&yogh;unnenne mid ferse: "<I>Deus</I> in adiutorium meum intende", and mid "<I>Gloria patri</I>"; &amp; &aelig;fter &thorn;am ymen, &thorn;e to &thorn;&aelig;re tyde belimpe. &AElig;fter &thorn;am feower capitles, &thorn;at is feower todala an&yogh;in &thorn;&aelig;s hundtweon|ti&yogh;edanandeahtete&thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">hundtweonti&yogh;edanandeahte|te&thorn;an] hundtwenti&yogh;edan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> sealmes, &that; is: "Beati inmaculati" od: "legem pone"; on &thorn;am odrum tidum, &that; is on undern &amp; on mid|de&yogh;i &amp; on non &thorn;ri capitles syn &yogh;esungene of &thorn;am forseadan sealme, &thorn;at is on undern fram "legem pone" od "portio mea",<NOTE PLACE="foot">od] dd <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> fram "portio mea" od "defecit", fram "defecit" od "lucerna". On monend&aelig;&yogh;e to prinsonge syn &yogh;esun&yogh;ene &thorn;ri sealmes, &that; is se forma &amp; se oder &amp; se syxte, &thorn;&aelig;t is "Beatus uir", "Quare fremuerunt" &amp; "<I>Domine</I>, ne in furore"; &amp; swa odrum d&aelig;&yogh;um on &thorn;&aelig;re wucan syn fordon &thorn;ry sealmes &yogh;esun&yogh;en od &thorn;one ny&yogh;ontu&thorn;e sealm, swa &thorn;onne &that; se ny&yogh;ede sealm &amp; se seofentude syn todeoled on twe&yogh;en glorian, &thorn;&aelig;t is "Confitebor" &amp; "Diligam te". And swo syn &yogh;efadod, &thorn;at uhtsan&yogh; sy be&yogh;unnen on sunnannihtum fram &thorn;am twenti&yogh;e&thorn;an sealme, &thorn;at is "<I>Domine</I>, in uirtute".</P>
<P>On monand&aelig;&yogh;e to undernsan&yogh;e &amp; to midd&aelig;&yogh;essange &amp; to<MILESTONE N="84a" UNIT="folio"> nonsange syn to &aelig;lcan &thorn;isse tide &thorn;ry capitles &yogh;esungene of &thorn;am ny&yogh;an capitelum, &thorn;e to lafe synd of &thorn;am hundtweonti&yogh;edan|andeahtete&thorn;an<NOTE PLACE="foot">to lafe] to <I>f. Hs.</I></NOTE> sealme, &thorn;at is "lucerna pedibus" od "ad <I>Dominum</I> cum tribularer". Sy &thorn;onne &thorn;us &yogh;eendod se hundtweonti&yogh;eda|&amp;-se-eahteteo&thorn;a sealm on twam da&yogh;um, &thorn;at is on sunneda&yogh;e &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">twam] &thorn;am <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on monend&aelig;&yogh;e, on tywesd&aelig;&yogh;e on undern &amp; on myddey &amp; on non syn &thorn;ri sealmes to ealcen &thorn;&aelig;re tyde &yogh;esun&yogh;ene of &thorn;ysum ny&yogh;on sealmum, &thorn;at is fram &thorn;am hundtweontu&yogh;e&thorn;eandni&yogh;eon|teoda 
<PB REF="00000085.tif" N="57"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="42,25-44,8"> sealmum od &thorn;one hundtweonti&yogh;ean-&amp;-&thorn;an-seofanandtweon|ti&yogh;e&thorn;on; &thorn;a niyon sealmes syn d&aelig;&yogh;hanlice &yogh;eedl&aelig;hte ofer ealle<NOTE PLACE="foot">niyon] niwon <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> wucan &yogh;eond &thorn;a sylfa tida od &thorn;one sunnend&aelig;&yogh;, &that; is "ad <I>Do|minum</I> cum tribularer" od "sepe expugnauerunt"; ymnes and capitle, readinge and fers &amp; halsun&yogh;a syn anum &yogh;emete &yogh;e|healdene eallum d&aelig;&yogh;um, be &thorn;am &thorn;e we &aelig;r cwedon, &amp; swa efre eft be&yogh;unne on &thorn;one sunned&aelig;&yogh; fram &thorn;am undtweonti&yogh;edan-&amp;|tane-eahtetu&thorn;e sealma, &thorn;at is "Beati inmaculati".</P>
<P>Se &aelig;fensang sy de&yogh;hamlice &yogh;eendod mid feower sealme dreame. &THORN;&aelig;s sealmes be&yogh;innan fram &thorn;am hundtwenti&yogh;e&thorn;on|&amp;-&thorn;am-ny&yogh;e&thorn;an; od &thorn;one hundtweonti&yogh;e&thorn;an-&amp;-&thorn;ane-seofenand|feowerti&yogh;e&thorn;an, &thorn;at is fram "Dixit <I>Dominus</I>" od "laudate Domi|num de celis", buton &thorn;am, &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;r betweox ascyrede synd to<MILESTONE N="84b" UNIT="folio"> odrem tydsan&yogh;um, &thorn;at is fram &thorn;am hundtweonti&yogh;e&thorn;onand|seofeonti&yogh;e&thorn;on od &thorn;one hundtwenti&yogh;e&thorn;enandseofenandtwenti&yogh;edon,<NOTE PLACE="foot">-seofeonti&yogh;e&thorn;on] -seofeorti&yogh;e&thorn;on <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;at is fram "Confitemini" od "Sepe expugnauerunt", &amp; buten<NOTE PLACE="foot">fram] <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile nachgetragen.</I></NOTE> &thorn;am hundtwentu&yogh;e&thorn;anand&thorn;reoand&thorn;ritti&yogh;e&thorn;an &amp; &thorn;an hundtwenti|&yogh;e&thorn;anandtwaandfeortu&yogh;e&thorn;an, &that; is "Ecce nunc" &amp; "<I>Domine</I> exaudi <I>orationem meam</I>", elles ealle &thorn;a odre syn to &thorn;am &aelig;fendreame &yogh;esungene. For&thorn;an &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;s sealm&yogh;etales is elles to lit, &thorn;a &thorn;ri meste sealmes sceolen beo todeolede on tweien glorian, &thorn;at is se hundtweonti&yogh;e&thorn;e-&amp;-se-eahteand&thorn;ritti&yogh;e&thorn;a &amp; se hundtwenti|&yogh;e&thorn;e-&amp;-se-&thorn;reoandfeorti&yogh;e&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">is <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; se hundtwenti&yogh;e&thorn;eandfeorandfeor|ty&yogh;e&thorn;e, &thorn;at is "<I>Domine</I> probasti me" &amp; "Benedictus" &amp; "Exaltabo te <I>domine</I>"; se hundtwenti&yogh;e&thorn;a-&amp;-se-syxti&yogh;e&thorn;a, for&thorn;am he litel is, he sceal beon &yogh;e&thorn;ed &thorn;am hundteonti&yogh;e&thorn;an-&amp;-&thorn;am-fifteo&thorn;an &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e&thorn;ed] &yogh;esed <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; hundteonti&yogh;.] hundfeorti&yogh;. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;a twe&yogh;en to anum sealme &yogh;esungene, &thorn;at is "Credidi" &amp; "Lau|twe&yogh;en]<NOTE PLACE="foot"> tw&yogh;e&yogh;en <I>Hs.</I></NOTE>date <I>dominum omnes gentes</I>". To eacan &thorn;&aelig;re endebyrdnysse &thorn;&aelig;ra sealma &thorn;&aelig;s &aelig;fensanges syn odre &thorn;in&yogh; &yogh;efyllede, swa ic bufan &yogh;ewissode, &thorn;at is redinge, repses, ymne, fers, canticles, &thorn;at is "Magnificat".</P>
<P>To nihtsange man sceal &thorn;a sylfan sealmes &aelig;lce niht &yogh;eed|l&aelig;can, &thorn;at is &thorn;one feor&thorn;an &amp; &thorn;one hundny&yogh;eteo&thorn;e &amp; &thorn;one hundtweonti&yogh;edanand&thorn;riand&thorn;ritti&yogh;odan, &that; is "Cum inuocarem",<MILESTONE N="85a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">-and&thorn;ri-] &amp; &thorn;ri <I>zweimal geschrieben.</I></NOTE> "Qui habitat", "Ecce nunc".
<PB REF="00000087.tif" N="59"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="44,9-45,12"></P>
<P>&ETH;us &yogh;efadodre endbyrdnisse &thorn;es d&aelig;&yogh;hamlican sealmsanges, ealle &thorn;a oddre sealmes, &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;r to lafe synd, syn &yogh;elice tod&aelig;|lede to &thorn;am seofen uhtsangum &thorn;&aelig;re wucan, swa &thorn;at &thorn;a mestan<NOTE PLACE="foot">uhtsang.] uths. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> syn tod&aelig;lede on tweien glorian, &thorn;at synd "Noli emulari", "Exur|gat <I>Deus</I>", "Saluum me fac", "Attendite" "Misericordias <I>domini</I>", "Benedic <I>anima</I>", "Confitemini <I>domino et</I> inuocate", "Confitemini" se o&thorn;er, "Confitemini" se &thorn;ridde, &amp; swo to &aelig;lcen uhtsange syn tweolf sealmes &yogh;esungenne. We &thorn;&aelig;s heahlice myne&yogh;ad, &yogh;yf<NOTE PLACE="foot">tweolf] teolf <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; <I>Nach</I> &yogh;esungenne <I>ein neuer Absatz und das Folgende wie ein neues Capitel behandelt, wozu vom Rubricator die Ueberschrift:</I> Seid ure hlaford <I>sancle</I> bene|dihit. &Verbar; We] &thorn;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hwam &thorn;ises sealmessanges fadun&yogh; &amp; endebyrdness mislicad, fadi&yogh;e he sel &amp; endebyrde, &yogh;yf him swa &thorn;ince; swa &thorn;eh &thorn;at he &thorn;as &yogh;yme, &that; &that; hundredandfifti&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;s s&aelig;alteres sealma syn<NOTE PLACE="foot">&that; &that;] &that; he &that; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on &aelig;lcere wucan ealle to &thorn;am tydsangum tod&aelig;lede &amp; &yogh;esungene, for&thorn;i hit is elles to slac mynecene &thorn;eoudom &amp; heore hyrsum|nesse, &yogh;yf hi l&aelig;sse sin&yogh;ad on &thorn;are wucan &thorn;onne &thorn;one saltere eallne mid &yogh;ewunelican cantica; w&aelig; r&aelig;ded, &thorn;at &thorn;a ealdan<NOTE PLACE="foot">w&aelig;] <I>danach Rasur 1 Buchst.</I></NOTE> f&aelig;deres on anum d&aelig;&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;&aelig;t] &thorn;&aelig;t &that; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> stidlice &yogh;efyllen, &thorn;&aelig;t wylle Crist, &thorn;at we asolcene &amp; awacede on anre wucan &yogh;elesten.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="19" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XIX. HU MAN SCEALL SIN&YOGH;ON TOFOREN UREN DRIHTEN.<MILESTONE N="85b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Y&yogh;hwar we &yogh;elyfad, &that; Godes andwyrdnys sy &amp; &yogh;esyhd, &amp; his ea&yogh;an behaldad &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e &thorn;a godan &yogh;e &thorn;a yfelan; &thorn;eah swydest we &thorn;&aelig;s buton &aelig;lcere tweonunge &yogh;elyfan, &thorn;onne we<NOTE PLACE="foot">tweonunge <I>zweimal geschrieben.</I></NOTE> &aelig;t Godes weorce wuniad. Fordi &thorn;onne syn we a &yogh;emyndi&yogh;e, &thorn;es &thorn;e se wyte&yogh;a &thorn;us cwed: "&ETH;eowiad eowran drihtne mid e&yogh;e"; and eft: "Syn&yogh;ad wislice", &amp;: "On engla &yogh;esyhde ic sin&yogh;e &thorn;e". Eornestlice, uton besceawian, hu we wunian on Godes &yogh;esyh&thorn;e &amp; on his engla; &amp; &thorn;onne swa standan &aelig;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; <I>bis</I> engla <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> &thorn;an sealmsange, &thorn;at ure mod &yogh;e&thorn;w&aelig;rl&aelig;ce mid &thorn;&aelig;s mudes clypiunge.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="20" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000089.tif" N="61"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="45,13-46,21">
<HEAD>XX.<MILESTONE N="86a" UNIT="folio"> BE WUR&ETH;NESSE &YOGH;EBEDENE, OD&ETH;E HU MAN SCEAL &YOGH;OD BEDDAN.<NOTE PLACE="foot">BEDDAN <I>scheint aus</I> beodan <I>corrig.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;yf we mid rican mannan hw&aelig;t embe ure neode manian wyllad, &thorn;&aelig;t we ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;cad buton mid micelre eadmod|nysse; micele swidor is to halsienne ealra &yogh;esceafta drihten mid ealre eadmodnysse &amp; mid ealre under&thorn;eodnesse &amp; modes hlutternesse! We na ne wanan, &thorn;at we na &thorn;urh &thorn;a manifeald|nesse ura &yogh;ebeda syn &yogh;ehyrede, ac mid ure heortan hlutter|nesse &amp; mid teara onbryrdnesse ura &yogh;ebeda beod anfonge. Fordi<NOTE PLACE="foot">onbyrdn. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;onne &thorn;at &yogh;ebed sceal beon scort &amp; hlutter, buton hwa mid godcundre onbrirdnesse &yogh;emanod sy, &thorn;at heo hyre &yogh;ebed &yogh;elenge; an metinc&yogh;e &thorn;eah &thorn;&aelig;s &yogh;eferes sy &that; &yogh;ebed &yogh;escyrt, &amp; &yogh;eworh|tum beacna fram &thorn;am ealdre ealle endemes arisan.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="21" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXI. BE MYNSTRES TEODIN&YOGH;EALDRUM.<MILESTONE N="86b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">Yyf] Wyf <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Yyf seo &yogh;efer&aelig;den mycel sy, syn &yogh;ecorene of dan sylue &yogh;esustre, &thorn;a &thorn;e godes &yogh;ewitnesse syn &amp; hal&yogh;re drohnun&yogh;e, &amp; syn &yogh;esette teodin&yogh;ealdre, &thorn;a syn embhidi&yogh;e and cariende embe hyre ealderscipes on eallum &thorn;ingum &aelig;fter Godes beobodum &amp; heore abbodesse hese. Syn &thorn;a ealdres swilce &yogh;ecorene, &thorn;at se abbodesse hyre byrdena on hi tod&aelig;len ma&yogh;e; ne syn hi &yogh;ecorene be nanre endebyrdnesse, ac be lifes &yogh;eearnunge &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">wisdomes, -es <I>aus</I> -os <I>corrig.</I></NOTE> wisdomes lare. Gyf heora hwilc &thorn;urh &thorn;ane truwan hyre eal|derscipes<NOTE PLACE="foot">onhefd] onhefhd <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ferin&yogh;a to&thorn;int &amp; hi&yogh; on modi&yogh;nesse onhefd, &amp; heo on &thorn;am leahtre byd onfunden to fornimende, sy hyre &aelig;ne &yogh;estyred<MILESTONE N="87a" UNIT="folio"> &amp; eft &amp; &thorn;riddan syde; gyf heo &thorn;anne swa ne bete &amp; rihlice, sy heo of dam ealderscipe aworpen, &amp; oder sy on &yogh;esett, &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">ealderscipe] ealdelsc. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;s weorde sy. And &thorn;&aelig;t sylfe we settad &amp; t&aelig;cead be &thorn;ere priore.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="22" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000091.tif" N="63"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="47,1-48,12">
<HEAD>XXII. HU MYNECENE SLAPAN LIGGEN.</HEAD>
<P>Anlipi&yogh;e mynecena &yogh;eond &aelig;nlypi&yogh;e bedd restan. Hi&yogh; bed|reaf<MILESTONE N="87b" UNIT="folio"> onfon &aelig;fter heora drohtnun&yogh;e &yogh;emete &amp; &aelig;fter heora abbod|esse dihte. Gyf hit beon m&aelig;&yogh;e, hi&yogh; ealle on anan hus r&aelig;stan; gyf seo ferreden to &thorn;am mycel sy, &thorn;at hi&yogh; ne m&aelig;&yogh;on, tynum odde tweonti&yogh;um on anum inne &aelig;t&yogh;&aelig;dere restan mid heora ealdra, &thorn;e embe hi&yogh; carian. Leoht on &thorn;an sylfum inne singallice ofer ealle niht byrne od leohtne mor&yogh;en. Hi&yogh; &yogh;e|weddode &amp; be&yogh;yrde reston &amp; nane seax be heora sydan nabban, &thorn;e l&aelig;ste hy on sl&aelig;pe &yogh;ewundede weor&thorn;an, ac &thorn;at hi&yogh; &aelig;fere<NOTE PLACE="foot">hi&yogh;] is <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;earwe syn, &amp; &yogh;eworhtum beacne hi&yogh; buton elcunge arysende caflice &yogh;ewilc odre foresteppe &amp; to &thorn;am Godas weorce efste &mdash;<NOTE PLACE="foot">efste] epste <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;at &thorn;onne sy mid michelre st&aelig;d&thorn;inesse &amp; &yogh;emedfestnesse. Seo &yogh;eo&yogh;ad na &yogh;etan&yogh; lic&yogh;e, ac seo yld &thorn;a &yogh;eo&yogh;ode to lic&yogh;e. To &thorn;am Godes werce arisende, heore &aelig;lc odre myne&yogh;ye, &thorn;at &thorn;a slapele nane beladun&yogh;e nabban.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="23" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXIII. BE AMANSUMUN&YOGH;E &YOGH;YLTE.<MILESTONE N="88a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&YOGH;YLTE] &yogh;ylce <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Gyf hwylc swuster on&yogh;yten byd to&thorn;unden, odde un&yogh;ehir|sum, odde mod&yogh;, odde ceoriende, odde on &aelig;ni&yogh;um &thorn;in&yogh;um wydeward wunienda &thorn;am hal&yogh;um re&yogh;ule, &amp; heora yldrena be|boda oferho&yogh;iend: &thorn;as &thorn;yllice &aelig;fter Godes bebode syn di&yogh;ollice mid wordum &aelig;ne &amp; odre syde &yogh;emine&yogh;od fram heora yldrenum. Gyf heo swa ne bete &amp; hy sylfe ne &yogh;erihte, heo sy &yogh;e&thorn;read openlice beforan eallum. Gyf heo &thorn;onne swa &yogh;it hi sylfe ne &yogh;erihte, &yogh;if heo on&yogh;yt, hu hefitime wite hit is, heo amansumunge underhni&yogh;e; gyf heo &thorn;aonne &yogh;yt widerr&aelig;de byd, heo licamlice wrace mid swin&yogh;elle &thorn;oli&yogh;e.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="24" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000093.tif" N="65"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="48,13-50,6">
<HEAD>XXIV. BE &THORN;AM &YOGH;EMETE HU SCEAL BEON &YOGH;ELEN&YOGH;ED &THORN;EO<MILESTONE N="88b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;AM &YOGH;EMETE HU] <I>fehlt, daf&uuml;r Ras. von etwa 10 Buchst. Hs.</I> &Verbar; &YOGH;ELEN&YOGH;ED <I>aus</I> &yogh;elen&yogh;end <I>rad.</I> &Verbar; &thorn;EO, <I>das</I> o <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile nach|getragen.</I></NOTE> AMANSUMUN&YOGH;A.<NOTE PLACE="foot">amansumma&yogh;a <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Efter &thorn;es geltes &yogh;emete sceal beon &yogh;el&aelig;nc&yogh;et &thorn;&aelig;re aman|sumunge &yogh;emet odde &thorn;&aelig;re stere: standa &thorn;&aelig;ra &yogh;ylta &yogh;emete|&yogh;ung on &thorn;ara abbodesse dome.</P>
<P>&THORN;eahhwedere &yogh;yf hwilc swuster on litlum gyltum byd on|funden, sy heo ascired fram beodes &yogh;emennesse. &THORN;is is mid &yogh;esceade to healdenne &thorn;am &thorn;e ascyrede syn fram &thorn;am &yogh;em&aelig;nen reorde, &that; is &that; hi on chircan ne be&yogh;innan na&thorn;er ne sealm ne<NOTE PLACE="foot">be&yogh;innan] be&yogh;nnan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> antiefene, ne redinge ne r&aelig;den od fulre dedbote; heora &yogh;ererdes<NOTE PLACE="foot">od] of <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;i&yogh;ene heo anan underfo, &aelig;fter &thorn;&aelig;ra sustrene &yogh;ererde &mdash; swilce<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ererde] &yogh;ererdre <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ic &thorn;us cwede: gyf &thorn;o &yogh;esustre on myddei, heo on non, gyf &thorn;a<NOTE PLACE="foot">on non] on <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> swustra on non, heo on efen &mdash; odd&aelig;t heo mid &thorn;es&yogh;elicere diedbote foryfennesse &aelig;t Gode be&yogh;it.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="25" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXV. BE SWY&ETH;E HEFITEME &YOGH;YLTE.<MILESTONE N="89a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Seo swuster, &thorn;eo &thorn;e mid sw&aelig;ra &yogh;ylte heofene byd &yogh;edered &amp; on hefytimum &yogh;yltum byd arasod, sy heo ascyred fram &yogh;e|menre mysan &thorn;i&yogh;ena &amp; eac swa fram &thorn;am ingan&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re hal&yogh;en cyrican. Nan swuster nabbe to hyre nane &yogh;e&thorn;eodredenne, ne on spece ne on nane odre &yogh;emanan; sy heo ana wuniende on<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;emana|nan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> bet&aelig;htre note mid dedbote, &amp; heo beo on wope &amp; on fullre bereowsunge, understande eac &thorn;&aelig;ne e&yogh;fullen cwede, &thorn;e se apostol be swa for&yogh;yltum cwid: Sy &thorn;us &yogh;erad mann sce&ocirc;ccan bet&aelig;ht for fl&aelig;sces forwirde, to&thorn;i &that; se gast on Godes dome &yogh;e|healden sy. Heora metes &yogh;ereord heo ana underfo, &thorn;am &yogh;emete &amp; on &thorn;&aelig;re tide, &thorn;e seo abbodesse understande, &thorn;&aelig;t heore &yogh;e|byri&yogh;e. Ne heo ne sy &yogh;ebletsod fram nanum &thorn;ara, &thorn;e hi&yogh; &yogh;e|mete,<NOTE PLACE="foot">nanum <I>aus</I> manum <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> ne se mete &thorn;e ma, &thorn;e hyre &yogh;eseald byd.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="26" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000095.tif" N="67"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="50,7-51,18">
<HEAD>XXVI. BE &ETH;AM &THORN;E WI&ETH;UTEN &THORN;ARE ABBODESSE LEAFE NEAHLIEHT &THORN;AM AMANSUMODAM.</HEAD>
<P>Gyf hwilc swuster butan heore abbodesse h&aelig;se &yogh;edyrst|l&aelig;cd,<MILESTONE N="89b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">heo] <I>danach ein zweites</I> heo <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;t heo on &aelig;ni wisan &aelig;ni&yogh;e &yogh;e&thorn;eodr&aelig;dene nyme wid &thorn;a amansumedan, odde &thorn;urh &aelig;ni&yogh;e sp&aelig;ce odde &thorn;urh &aelig;ni&yogh;es odres mannes &aelig;rendun&yogh;e, sy heo &yogh;elice &yogh;elimpe amansumod &amp; on &yogh;elicre wrace dedbete.<NOTE PLACE="foot">dedbete] dedbote <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="27" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXVII. HU GLEAW AND CARAFULL SCEALL BEON SEO ABBO|DESSE ABUTEN &THORN;A AMANSUMADAN.<MILESTONE N="90a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eo abbodesse mid ealre embehydnisse cari&yogh;e enba &thorn;o &yogh;yltenda swustra, fordi &thorn;a halan l&aelig;ces ne lacnunge ne biho|fiad, ac &thorn;a untruman. Fordi on eallum &yogh;emete hi&yogh; scullon l&aelig;ce &thorn;eawa on here heordr&aelig;denne notian; hi&yogh; scullan oft dihlice<NOTE PLACE="foot">heordr&aelig;d.] d <I>in</I> heord <I>&uuml;ber der Z. nachgetragen u. zw. irrt&uuml;mlich zwischen</I> r <I>und</I> &aelig;.</NOTE> ealde witan &amp; &yogh;est&aelig;ddi&yogh;e, &thorn;&aelig;t syn stadolfeste swustre s&aelig;ndan,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;est&aelig;ddi&yogh;e] &yogh;esc&aelig;ddi&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &that; &thorn;a unstadolfeste &amp; &thorn;a tweonienda swuster to d&aelig;dbote &amp; to<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; &thorn;a tweon.] &amp; <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> heore agenre &thorn;earfa mani&yogh;ean &amp; hy swa frefrian, &thorn;at heo &thorn;urh micele gnornun&yogh;e ne sy on lyre forswol&yogh;en; si on &thorn;&aelig;re synni|&yogh;an swuster seo sode lufe &yogh;ekyd &amp; &yogh;efestnod, &amp; ealle &yogh;eswustre &yogh;ebidde for hyre.</P>
<P>&THORN;earle swide &thorn;eo abbodesse sc&aelig;l &yogh;yman &amp; mid eallan gleawscipe hogian, &thorn;at nan sceap on &thorn;&aelig;re heorde ne losi&yogh;e, &thorn;e hyre bet&aelig;ht is. Wite heo, &thorn;at heo &thorn;a &yogh;emenne &thorn;&aelig;re heorde untrumra sawla to rihtra lacnunge underfen&yogh; &amp; na for rictere, &thorn;e heo ofer da habbe, &thorn;e hale syndon; heo eac ondrede &thorn;a<MILESTONE N="90b" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;eowrace, &thorn;e dryhten &thorn;urh his wite&yogh;an &thorn;ywd, &thorn;us cwedenda:<NOTE PLACE="foot">wite&yogh;an, e <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> "&ETH;&aelig;t &that; &yogh;e f&aelig;tt &yogh;esawan, &that; &yogh;e curan &amp; &that; wanhal w&aelig;s &amp; al&aelig;fed, &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;e awurpon"; ac seo abbodesse &yogh;eefenlece &thorn;a bysene &thorn;es arf&aelig;sten &amp; &thorn;es mildheorten hyrdes, &thorn;e uppan &thorn;are dune forl&aelig;t 
<PB REF="00000097.tif" N="69"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="51,18-53,9"> ny&yogh;enandhundny&yogh;enti sceapa, &amp; an, &thorn;&aelig; &thorn;&aelig;r losede &amp; dwellode, &yogh;eornlice sohte &amp; funde, &amp; &thorn;as sceapas untrumnesse him to &thorn;am swyde ofreaw, &that; he hit ofer his eaxla l&aelig;de &amp; eft upp to heorde b&aelig;r.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="28" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXVIII. BEE &THORN;AM &THORN;E OFT R&AElig;DLICE BY&ETH; &YOGH;E&THORN;READ AND NA NE<MILESTONE N="91a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&YOGH;E&thorn;READ, r <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> BETE&ETH; FOR HEARDHYRTNESSE.</HEAD>
<P>Gyf hwylc swuster oftlice &yogh;e&thorn;read for hwylcum &yogh;ilte byd, ne heo furdon for amansumin&yogh;e &yogh;ebetan nellan, ne hyre &thorn;eawas<NOTE PLACE="foot">amansumi&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eritlecen, hi m&aelig;n &thorn;rea&yogh;e mid teartran styre, &thorn;at is hyre sy&yogh;e on swin&yogh;&aelig;lla wraca.</P>
<P>Gyf heo &thorn;onne &thorn;urh &thorn;a swin&yogh;elan ne byd &yogh;eriht, ac on modinesse wuniende mid uphafednesse hyre yfele dedan mid leasum talum bewerian wile, &thorn;&aelig;t neofre ne &yogh;ewur&thorn;e, do &thorn;onne &thorn;eo abbodesse swa swa wis lacnystre: gyf heo swe&thorn;un&yogh;e &yogh;e|&yogh;earwode, &amp; godcundra myne&yogh;unga sealfun&yogh;a, hal&yogh;ra &yogh;ewrita lacnunga, &amp; &aelig;t nyhstan amansumun&yogh;e b&aelig;rnet &amp; swin&yogh;ella wita &thorn;urhteah &mdash; &amp; on&yogh;yt, &thorn;&aelig;t ealle hyre ho&yogh;u &amp; gleauscipe naht ne fremed, heo &thorn;onne &yogh;e&yogh;earwye &that; &that; m&aelig;st is, hyre a&yogh;en &yogh;ebed &amp; ealra &thorn;&aelig;ra &yogh;eswustra for hy, &thorn;at drihten, &thorn;e ealle &thorn;ing m&aelig;&yogh; &amp; ealra &thorn;ing wealt, &yogh;eh&aelig;le &thorn;a untrum&aelig;n &amp; &thorn;a leahter|fullan<MILESTONE N="91b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">untrun&aelig;n <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> swuster.</P>
<P>Gyf heo furdor &thorn;urh &thorn;a &yogh;ebeda &yogh;eheled ne byd, noti&yogh;e &thorn;onne &thorn;eo abbodesse cyrfes, &amp; mid isene &thorn;a uncode aceorfe &amp; fram &thorn;&aelig;re h&aelig;le ascyri&yogh;e, &thorn;urh &thorn;es apostles myne&yogh;unge, &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; fram] &amp; <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;us cwe&eth;:<NOTE PLACE="foot">cwe&eth;] che&eth; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> "Afyrsiod &thorn;a yfelan fram eow"; &amp; eft he cwe&eth;: "Gyf &thorn;eo &yogh;etreowleasa &yogh;ewite, heo &yogh;ewite, &thorn;el&aelig;ste an adli&yogh; sceap ealle heorde besmite".</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="29" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXIX. GYF MAN SCEALL EFT UNDERFON &THORN;O SWUSTRE &THORN;A &YOGH;EWENDET UT OF MUNSTRE.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eo swuster, &thorn;e for hyre a&yogh;enum leahtre odde un&thorn;eawe of mynstre ferd odde adreofod byd, &yogh;yf heo eft &yogh;ecyran wile, 
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="71"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="53,9-54,15"> behate erest bote &amp; &yogh;eswicnesse ealra &thorn;&aelig;ra un&thorn;eowa, &thorn;e hu fore utadr&aelig;fod was, &amp; heo swa sy onfan&yogh;en on uteweordre endebyrdnisse, &that; heo &thorn;urh &thorn;at seo afonded, hweder heo mid eadmodnesse &yogh;ecyrre.</P>
<P>Gyf heo &thorn;onne eft for hyre un&thorn;&aelig;awum utferd, odde adre|fed<MILESTONE N="92a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">adrefed] ariefed <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> byd, heo &thorn;&aelig;ah sy underfangen od done &thorn;riddan syde; wyte heo &thorn;onne, ofer &that; &that; hora &aelig;lces inferes forwirned byd &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">forwirned <I>aus</I> for&thorn;irned <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> heo nefre eft to &thorn;am mynstre &yogh;ecyrran ne &thorn;earf.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="30" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXX. BE &YOGH;EON&YOGH;E CILDE AND STY&ETH;E M&AElig;DENE HU MAN HI&YOGH;<NOTE PLACE="foot">CILDE] eilde <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; And <I>fehlt Hs.</I> &Verbar; M&AElig;DENE] medene, <I>unter dem 1.</I> e <I>ein Tilgungs|punkt, &uuml;ber dem</I> e <I>ein</I> &aelig; <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> SCEALL &THORN;REAN.</HEAD>
<P>Elc ylde &amp; andyit scullon habbon on stere a&yogh;ene &yogh;emet;<NOTE PLACE="foot">andyit] andwit <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> fordi &thorn;onne &yogh;eon&yogh;e cild &amp; stide m&aelig;dene odde &thorn;a, &thorn;e hwonlice understanden ma&yogh;e, hu micel wite is &amp; hu hefityme, &thorn;&aelig;t man on mansun&yogh;e sy, &thorn;as &thorn;yllice, &thorn;onne hi a&yogh;yltad, hy man styre odde mid swidlicum f&aelig;stenum, odde mid teartrum swin&yogh;ellum hi &yogh;ewilde, &thorn;&aelig;t hi&yogh; &yogh;eh&aelig;lede syn.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="31" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXI. BE MYNSTRES HORDESTRE HWYLC HEO BON SCEALL.<MILESTONE N="93a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">HORDE|STRE] hordestres <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; HWYLC] hwyle <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Se mynstres heordestre sy &yogh;ecoren of &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;esamnun&yogh;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">mynstres] mystres <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> wis, &yogh;eripedum &thorn;&aelig;awum, syfre &amp; na oferetol, ne drefend, ne teonful, ne lof&yogh;eorn, ac God ondr&aelig;dende; sy heo ealre &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eferedenne swa swa moder.</P>
<P>Heo ho&yogh;ie embe ealle &thorn;ing; ne do heo na &thorn;ing buton &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse h&aelig;se; heolden &thorn;at heora beboda sy. Heo hyre swustre ne &yogh;eunrotsi&yogh;e; gyf hwylc swuster un&yogh;escedlice hw&aelig;s bidde, heo &thorn;eah mid fors&aelig;wennesse hi&yogh; ne unrotsi&yogh;e, ac &yogh;e|sceadwislice mid eadmodnysse hyre yfele bene forwirne. Ge|healde 
<PB REF="00000101.tif" N="73"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="54,16-56,4"> heo a heore &yogh;e&thorn;anc, &that; heo mid goden mode &thorn;eni&yogh;e, &amp; sy &yogh;emindy&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;s, &thorn;e se apostel &thorn;us cwid: "Seo &thorn;e wel &thorn;enad,<MILESTONE N="93b" UNIT="folio"> heo godne wyrdscipe hyre sylfen &yogh;estrynd". Habbe heo care<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;estrynd] &yogh;estryd <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; &yogh;emene untrumra mannan mid ealra embehydi&yogh;nesse &amp; eac swa cildra &amp; cumena &amp; &thorn;earfena, witen heo buten tweon, &thorn;et<NOTE PLACE="foot">witen buten heo tweon <I>Hs., doch durch striche das</I> heo <I>an seine richtige stelle verwiesen.</I></NOTE> heo &aelig;t Godes dome be heom eallum &yogh;escead a&yogh;yldan sceal. Ealle mynstres fata &amp; spede heo sceal beoseon, swilce &thorn;a &yogh;e|halgodan<NOTE PLACE="foot">spede] swede <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; 9. be&yogh;an&yogh;a] befan&yogh;a <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> fata &thorn;&aelig;s weofodes; ne leote heo nan &thorn;ing to &yogh;eme|leste; ne heo uncyste ne be&yogh;an&yogh;a, ne heo lof&yogh;eorn ne sy, ne mynstres &aelig;hta ne uti&yogh;e, ne na myrre, eac ealle &thorn;ing &yogh;em&aelig;tlice do &amp; after &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse hese.</P>
<P>Habbe heo eadmodnesse tofore eallum &thorn;ingum, &thorn;am &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">Habbe] Habbo <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> heo nabbe &aelig;hta to syllenne, sylle gode andswara, for&thorn;an &thorn;e hit is &yogh;ewriten, &thorn;at &thorn;e gode andsware sy ofor &thorn;a selesten<NOTE PLACE="foot">and|sware] andware <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> syllene. Habbe heo under hyre &yogh;emene eal, &thorn;at se abbodesse hyre bitece; &amp; heo furdur ne &yogh;edristelice, &thorn;onne hyre beboden sy. &ETH;a &yogh;esettan bileofene heore &yogh;eswustrum &yogh;ebeode on riht|num tyman buton l&aelig;ate &amp; gnornunge, &thorn;at hi&yogh; ne unrotsian, sy &yogh;emyndi&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;re godcundan clypunge, &thorn;&aelig;t se &yogh;e&yogh;earni&yogh;e "&thorn;e &yogh;e&aelig;bylid &aelig;nne &thorn;&aelig;re l&aelig;stene, &thorn;e on God behic&yogh;ad".</P>
<P>Gyf seo &yogh;eferedden mycel sy, sy heore frofer &amp; fultum &yogh;eseald, &thorn;&aelig;t heo mid heore fultume efne mode &amp; gladum &thorn;e|nun&yogh;a &thorn;a &thorn;in&yogh;, &thorn;e hyre befeste synd, lustbere &yogh;efulle.<NOTE PLACE="foot">lustbere <I>bis</I> &yogh;ebedene <I>von etwas sp&auml;terer Hand auf dem untern Rande nachgetragen</I>, lustbere &yogh;e <I>auf Rasur und noch auf der urspr&uuml;nglich letzten Zeile der Seite.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>On &yogh;edafenum tidum syn &yogh;esealde &thorn;a &thorn;ing, &thorn;e to syllene sund, &amp; syn &yogh;ebedene, &thorn;a &thorn;e to biddenne synd, &thorn;at nan ne<MILESTONE N="94a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">to <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile von derselben sp&auml;tren Hand.</I></NOTE> sy &yogh;edrefod, ne &yogh;eunrotsie on Godes huse.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eunrotsie] &yogh;eunrod sy <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="32" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXII. BE MYNSTRES TOLUM OD&ETH;E O&ETH;ER KYNNES &THORN;YN&YOGH;ES<NOTE PLACE="foot">O&ETH;ER KYNNES] kynnes <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> AND EHTE.</HEAD>
<P>Mynstres &aelig;hte on tolum odde on reafum odde on odrum<NOTE PLACE="foot">on tolum] &amp; tol. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ewilcum &thorn;ingum syn bet&aelig;hte to bewitenne &thorn;am &yogh;eswustrum, 
<PB REF="00000103.tif" N="75"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="56,5-57,13"> &thorn;e heora lif &amp; &thorn;eawas gode &yogh;ecorene syn &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse orsor&yogh;e, &amp; hi&yogh; &thorn;a bet&aelig;ce &thorn;am, &thorn;e hyre notie scullon &amp; hyre eft underfon. Habbe &thorn;eo abbodesse a mid hyra &yogh;ewrit &yogh;elra &thorn;are ehte; &thorn;onne &thorn;eo notu on &yogh;esweostre &yogh;ewrixle byd, sy &that; &yogh;ewis<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ewrixle] &yogh;ewlixle <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> a mid &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse, &thorn;at heo wite, hwet bet&aelig;ht sy &amp; hwet underf&aelig;n&yogh;en.</P>
<P>Gyf heora hwilc fulice odde &yogh;ymeleaslice mynstres &thorn;in&yogh; behweorfe, sy hyre &yogh;estyred; gyf heo bete nelle, underfo heo<MILESTONE N="94b" UNIT="folio"> re&yogh;olice &thorn;reale.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="33" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXIII. GYF MYNECENE SCULON HABBEN SYNDERLICHE &AElig;HTEN.</HEAD>
<P>Heahlicost &amp; swdest &amp; deowast man sceal &thorn;one un&thorn;eaw of mynstre wanian &amp; mid ealle awyrtwalian &amp; fordo, &thorn;&aelig;t non ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;ce, &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; to syllenne odde to nymenne, buton &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse hese, ne hi&yogh; nan &thorn;in&yogh; syndri&yogh;es ne agan, ne nan &thorn;in&yogh; eallun&yogh;a, ne furdon booc, ne weaxbreda, ne &yogh;refe, ne on eallum &thorn;ingum nan &thorn;ing; eornostlice, hwet sceal heo<MILESTONE N="95a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;ing, i <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile.</I></NOTE> a&yogh;an on sundran, &thorn;e furdon heore a&yogh;enne lichaman ne hyre a&yogh;en mod ne sceal a&yogh;an on heora a&yogh;enum &yogh;ewealde? ealre nead&thorn;in&yogh;a heo sceal hihtan &amp; willian fram hyra mynstres moder. Ne heo nan &thorn;ing nabbe buton &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse sylene &amp; &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;a; sy heom ealle &thorn;ing &yogh;emene, swo swo hit awriten is on &thorn;&aelig;re apostole drohtnunge, be &thorn;an mynecene lif is &yogh;eby|senod; ne nan ne &yogh;edyrstlice, &that; heo &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; syndries habbe odde furdon &that; word &yogh;ecwede, &that; heo a&yogh;en habbe.</P>
<P>Gyf hwa on &thorn;isan manfullan &amp; forcu&thorn;estan un&thorn;eawe eni|&yogh;ene lust habbe, sy heo &yogh;emine&yogh;od fram heore ealdrene &aelig;ne &amp; eftsone; gyf heo bete nelle, hi&yogh; man mid swydlicum &amp; licham|licum &thorn;realum &yogh;ewylde.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;realum <I>zweimal geschrieben.</I></NOTE>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="34" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000105.tif" N="77"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="57,14-59,2">
<HEAD>XXXIV. GYF EALLE SCULLEN VNDERFON BEHEF ON<MILESTONE N="95b" UNIT="folio"> &THORN;ING &YOGH;ELICEN.</HEAD>
<P>Syn &yogh;ehwam behefe &thorn;in&yogh; &amp; alyfede &yogh;esealde, be &thorn;am &thorn;e hit on &thorn;&aelig;ra apostle drohnunge awriten is &thorn;isum wordum: "&AElig;lcan anlipium wes &yogh;eseald be &thorn;am, &thorn;e he behofede". Ne on&yogh;ete<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e <I>zu</I> w <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE> we on &thorn;isse clypun&yogh;e, &that; &thorn;&aelig;re &aelig;ni&yogh;era hada andf&aelig;n&yogh; w&aelig;re,<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radirt Hs.</I></NOTE> &that; is &that; &aelig;ni&yogh; be lifes ricetere, ac elc be hyre neode &amp; untrum|nesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">be (1.) <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> oncnawen were; deo &thorn;e on &yogh;eferredenne be litlum &amp; be ea&thorn;um &thorn;ingum beon ma&yogh;e, &thorn;anci&yogh;e heo &thorn;&aelig;s Gode &amp; heo ne<NOTE PLACE="foot">9-10. be ea&thorn;um] bea&thorn;um, &thorn; <I>aus</I> &yogh; <I>corrig. Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eunrotsie, &thorn;eah man mare do odrum, &thorn;e furdor behofad; seo &thorn;e be maran &thorn;in&yogh;an beon scule for hwylcere licamlicere tyd|dernesse,<NOTE PLACE="foot">be] beo <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; scule] sculo <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eeadmede hi&yogh; for heora untrumnesse &amp; heo na on|hebbe on &that;, swylce hit for earnun&yogh;um odde &yogh;e&thorn;in&yogh;dum &yogh;edon sy, &thorn;at man for mildhertsumnesse dide: &amp; swa ealla &thorn;a lima beod on sibbe.</P>
<P>Toforan eallum &thorn;in&yogh;um we myne&yogh;iad, &that; n&aelig;fre nanre ceorun&yogh;e yfelnes for &aelig;ni&yogh;um worde odde &yogh;etacnun&yogh;e &yogh;eswute|lod<NOTE PLACE="foot">yfelnes] &yogh;efelnes <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> weorde; gyf hwa on &thorn;am un&thorn;&aelig;awe onfunden sy, hi&yogh; man<NOTE PLACE="foot">man <I>aus</I> mam <I>radirt Hs.</I></NOTE> mid stydrum &thorn;relum &yogh;ewilde.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="35" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXV. BE KICENAN &THORN;ENYN&YOGH;SWUSTREN.<MILESTONE N="96b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Se swustre heom betweone &yogh;emenelice &thorn;enian, &amp; nan ne sy beladod fram &thorn;&aelig;re kycenan &thorn;enun&yogh;e, buton hwa mid untrum|nesse odde mid odre byse&yogh;um ofsett sy, &that; heo hit don ne<NOTE PLACE="foot">ofsett] ofsect <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ma&yogh;e; durh &thorn;o &yogh;em&aelig;nan &thorn;enun&yogh;e &thorn;isse hyrsumnysse byd seo meste lufe Godes &amp; manne &yogh;estrined. Beo fultume &yogh;eseald &thorn;am<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;esead <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> wacmodum &amp; &thorn;am unstran&yogh;um, &that; hy&yogh; mid unrotnesse &thorn;a hyr|sumnysse<NOTE PLACE="foot">unrotnesse] unrodn. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ne don, ac habbe ealle fultum and frofer be &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eferr&aelig;denne mycelnesse &amp; be &thorn;&aelig;re stowe stadole &amp; &yogh;eset|nysse. Gyf &thorn;e &yogh;eferreden micel byd, sy &thorn;eo hordestre 
<PB REF="00000107.tif" N="79"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="59,2-60,13"> aspelad of &thorn;&aelig;re cycene &thorn;enun&yogh;e, &amp; eac swa &thorn;a, &thorn;e mid myce|lum byse&yogh;um ofsette syn; elles &thorn;a odre ealle heom &yogh;emune|lice<NOTE PLACE="foot">ofsette] <I>Zwischen</I> of <I>und</I> sette <I>ein Buchst. radirt, wie es scheint</I> t.</NOTE> betweone on &thorn;isse &thorn;enun&yogh;e &thorn;eowian.</P>
<P>&ETH;&aelig;re cycenen wucedenestre on &thorn;one seternesd&aelig;&yogh; &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e fatan &thorn;wean, &yogh;e w&aelig;tercladas waxan, &thorn;e hy heore honde<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;wean] &thorn;eawan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; fet mid wipodan; &thorn;wean on &thorn;am sylfan d&aelig;&yogh;e ealre &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eswustre fet, &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re wucan wicdenestre, &yogh;e &thorn;ere<MILESTONE N="97a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;&yogh;der] &aelig;&yogh;de <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> towerdan. Heora &thorn;eningfata cl&aelig;ne &amp; hale &thorn;ere hord&aelig;stre betecen; deo hordestre eft &thorn;&aelig;re towerdan wucan wicdenum &thorn;a ylcan &thorn;&aelig;nigfate b&aelig;tece, &amp; wite &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e hwet heo underfon &yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">underfon &yogh;e] under|fonge <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hw&aelig;t heo bet&aelig;ce. &ETH;a wicdenestre anre tide &aelig;r &thorn;am &yogh;emenum<NOTE PLACE="foot">wicdenestre] <I>danach</I> coces <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ereorde &yogh;an to hlafe &amp; sume &aelig;nlypi&yogh;e sydde drincan, &amp; &that; sy toforan &yogh;esettan bi&yogh;leofan, &thorn;&aelig;t hi &thorn;e gladlicor butan &yogh;e|dyrfe &amp; mycele &yogh;eswince here &yogh;eswustra on &aelig;tes timan &thorn;enian<NOTE PLACE="foot">here] hero <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> m&aelig;&yogh;e; deahhw&aelig;dere freolstydum beon butan &thorn;am hlafgan&yogh;e &amp; drence, odd&aelig;t hi&yogh; m&aelig;ssan habban. Sunnada&yogh;um &thorn;a wuc|denestre, &yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re &aelig;rran wucan &yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re toweardan, sona &aelig;fter d&aelig;&yogh;redsan&yogh;e innan cyrican betyrnan hi&yogh; wid ealre &yogh;eferena cneowa, swa biddenda, &that; heom fore&yogh;ebeden sy. &ETH;eo &thorn;e &thorn;a &aelig;rran wicdenun&yogh;a &yogh;eendod habbe, &thorn;onne heo ut of &thorn;&aelig;re wuce|denunge<NOTE PLACE="foot">of <I>f. Hs.</I></NOTE> fare, cwede &thorn;is fers &thorn;us &thorn;anciende: "Gebletsod &thorn;u eart, drihten &aelig;lmihti&yogh;, &thorn;e me on &thorn;issere &thorn;enun&yogh;e &yogh;efultumedest &amp; &yogh;efrefradest"; dis fers sy &thorn;riwa &yogh;ecweden, &amp; swa mid blet|sun&yogh;e fara. &AElig;fterfyli&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re toweardan wucan wic&thorn;en &amp; &thorn;us cwede: "Be&yogh;yn &thorn;u, God, me to fylste, efst &thorn;u, drihten, me to fultume"; &amp; &thorn;&aelig;t sylfe fers sy &yogh;eedl&aelig;ht &thorn;riwa fram ealre &thorn;&aelig;re<MILESTONE N="97b" UNIT="folio"> &yogh;eferr&aelig;denne, &amp; swa mid bletsun&yogh;e heore wicdenun&yogh;e be&yogh;inne.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="36" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXVI.<NOTE PLACE="foot">SEOCEN] scocen <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> BE SEOCEN &YOGH;ESWUSTREN.</HEAD>
<P>Untrumre manna &yogh;emen is to healdenne toforan eallum &thorn;ingum &amp; ofer eallum &thorn;ingum, &that; heom swa &yogh;e&thorn;enat sy, swa<MILESTONE N="98a" UNIT="folio"> swa man Gode sylfan wolde, fordi &thorn;e he sylf cwed: "Untrum 
<PB REF="00000109.tif" N="81"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="60,13-61,17"> ic w&aelig;s, &amp; &yogh;e &yogh;eneosedan me", &amp; "&that; &yogh;e anum &thorn;am l&aelig;stam dydan,<NOTE PLACE="foot">w&aelig;s <I>aus</I> &thorn;&aelig;s <I>radirt.</I> &Verbar; &amp; &that;] &amp; <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; dydan] <I>aus</I> dydam <I>rad.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e mine synd, &that; &yogh;e didon me". Witan eac &thorn;a sylfan untruman,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Witan <I>aus</I> &thorn;itan <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> &that; heom for Godes arwirdnesse &yogh;ehyrsumod &amp; &yogh;e&thorn;enod sy, &amp; hi&yogh; mid hyre oferflowennesse ne &yogh;edrefen &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre, &thorn;e heom &thorn;eniad. Sy eornostlice seo meste ho&yogh;u &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse,<NOTE PLACE="foot">Sy] S <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &that; hi&yogh; foryymeleasode ne syn.<NOTE PLACE="foot">foryymeleasode] forsymel. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Sy &thorn;am untruman &yogh;eswustre synderlice an hus &yogh;eset &amp; to &thorn;an anum b&aelig;teht; se &thorn;enestre, &thorn;e &thorn;enad &thorn;am seoce, sy carful,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;e <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> God lufiende &amp; ondredende. Badu notu &thorn;am untruman, swa oft swa hit fremi&yogh;e, sy &yogh;eboden; halum &amp; huru &thorn;am &yogh;eon&yogh;um sy seldor &amp; lator &yogh;etidod. Fl&aelig;sc&aelig;t &thorn;am untrumam &amp; &thorn;am wanhalan for edstadelun&yogh;e sy &yogh;e&thorn;afod; sona swa hi&yogh; &yogh;eedhwur|fede beod &amp; &yogh;estrangode, &thorn;am fl&aelig;sc&aelig;te forhabban &aelig;fter &yogh;e|wunelicum &thorn;eawe.</P>
<P>Habbe &thorn;eo abbodesse mycelene &yogh;eomene, &that; &thorn;a untruman fram &thorn;are hordestre &amp; &thorn;am &thorn;eningmannum ne syn for&yogh;eme|leasode, fordi eall heo mot andstundian, swa hwet swa fram<NOTE PLACE="foot">mot] mod <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hyre &yogh;ingrum foryymeleasod byd.<NOTE PLACE="foot">foryymel.] forsymel. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="37" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXVII.<MILESTONE N="98b" UNIT="folio"> BE SWY&ETH;AN EALDAN MANN&AElig; AND BE &YOGH;EON&YOGH;E CYLDEN.<NOTE PLACE="foot">EALDAN] eanldan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eah hit &yogh;ecundelic sy on m&aelig;nniscum &yogh;ewunan, &that; man mildheortnesse cyde &thorn;am oferealdan &amp; &thorn;am &yogh;eon&yogh;um cilde,<NOTE PLACE="foot">mildheortnesse, <I>das</I> t <I>fehlt, doch zwischen</I> heor <I>und</I> nesse <I>Zeilenschluss.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;ahhwedere ne sculon hi&yogh; beon butan reo&yogh;ele, &thorn;at is lifes rihtinge. Sy &aelig;fre &yogh;esceawod on heom heora untrumnesse &amp; nateswon &thorn;&aelig;s reo&yogh;eles strece &yogh;ehealdon on heora bi&yogh;leofan; &amp; sy mildheortnes on heom acyded, &amp; mid heore &thorn;i&yogh;ene forra|dian<NOTE PLACE="foot">mildheortnes, <I>das</I> t <I>fehlt, doch zwischen</I> heor <I>und</I> nes <I>Zeilenschluss.</I></NOTE> &thorn;a re&yogh;ollican tida.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="38" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000111.tif" N="83"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="62,1-63,11">
<HEAD>XXXVIII. BE &THORN;&AElig;RE WUKCE REDESTRE &AElig;T &THORN;AN METE.<MILESTONE N="99a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Geswustre &yogh;ereord &aelig;t heora mysum ne sceal beon butan<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ereord, -or <I>auf Rasur, unter</I> o <I>scheint</I> r <I>gestanden zu haben.</I></NOTE> hali&yogh;re redinge. Ne nan ne &yogh;edyrstlece, &that; heo furlice boc &yogh;e|l&aelig;cce &amp; &thorn;&aelig;r butan foresceawunge o&yogh;ynne to r&aelig;denne; ac &thorn;&aelig;re wucan r&aelig;destre on &thorn;one sunnand&aelig;&yogh; mid bletsunge hit be&yogh;inne. Seo &thorn;onne &aelig;fter messan &amp; husel&yogh;an&yogh;e &yogh;ewilni&yogh;e, &that; hi&yogh; ealle<MILESTONE N="99b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">Seo &thorn;onne, -eo &thorn;on- <I>auf Rasur, nach</I> s <I>scheint ursprgl.</I> y <I>gestanden zu haben.</I></NOTE> heore &yogh;ebiddan, &that; God almihti&yogh; upahafenesse gast fram hyre ado, &amp; sec&yogh;e &thorn;is fers &thorn;riwa &amp; ealla &thorn;a odra &that; ylce fers &thorn;riwa segge: "Drihten, &yogh;eopena &thorn;u mine lippe, &amp; minne mud bodi&yogh;e &thorn;in lof"; &amp; &thorn;us mid bletsun&yogh;e be&yogh;inne to redenne.</P>
<P>Sy heahlic swie &aelig;t &thorn;am &yogh;ereorde, &that; nanes mannes stefne<NOTE PLACE="foot">swie] <I>zwischen</I> i <I>und</I> e <I>Rasur cines Buchstaben, es scheint</I> d.</NOTE> ne reorung &thorn;&aelig;rinne &yogh;ehyred ne sy, butan &thorn;&aelig;re r&aelig;destre ane.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;&aelig;rinne] &thorn;&aelig;rmyne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> Gyf hi&yogh; etende odde drincende hwylcra &thorn;inge behofian, &that; sy mid sumre &yogh;etacnun&yogh;e &yogh;ebeden &amp; na mid m&aelig;nniscre stefene;<NOTE PLACE="foot">mid, d <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> ne furdon heora nan ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;ce, &that; heo be &thorn;&aelig;re sylfan r&aelig;din&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;rinne &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; ahsi&yogh;e, odde be &aelig;ni&yogh;um odrum &thorn;ingum, &thorn;il&aelig;s &thorn;e &aelig;ni&yogh; inca &yogh;eseald sy, butan hit &thorn;&aelig;t sy, &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;il&aelig;s] &thorn;ilces <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> seo ealdor w&aelig;t sceortlice of &thorn;&aelig;re r&aelig;din&yogh;e to hyra gastlican<NOTE PLACE="foot">w&aelig;t] h&aelig;t, <I>das</I> h <I>oben radirt Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;etymbrun&yogh;e &yogh;ereccan wylle.</P>
<P>&THORN;&aelig;re wucan r&aelig;destre gan&yogh;e to hlafe &amp; drince, &aelig;rdan &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;rdan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> heo be&yogh;inne to r&aelig;denne, for d&aelig;s hal&yogh;an husles &thorn;i&yogh;ene &amp; &that; heore to lan&yogh;sum, ne to hefityme heore festen ne &thorn;ynce to<NOTE PLACE="foot">hefityme <I>bis</I> festen <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> &thorn;olienne; ete heo eft &aelig;fter heore redinge mid &thorn;am &thorn;eni&yogh;|mannum.</P>
<P>Ne r&aelig;dan &thorn;a &yogh;eswustra na be nanre &aelig;ndebyrdnisse, ac &thorn;a &thorn;e hit wel don cunnan &amp; odre &yogh;etymbrian ma&yogh;on.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;etymbriam <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="39" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XXXIX. BE M&AElig;LES &YOGH;EMETEN.<MILESTONE N="100a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">B. m. &yogh;. <I>danach in gleicher Weise vom Rubricator</I> De la mesura de mangers.</NOTE></HEAD>
<P>We &yogh;elifad, &thorn; &yogh;enoh sy to d&aelig;i&yogh;hwamlice &yogh;ereorde, swa to mid&aelig;&yogh;e swa to nona, twa &yogh;esodene sufla for mystlicra manna 
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="85"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="63,11-64,20"> untrumnesse; gyf hwa for wylcere cisnesse &thorn;&aelig;s anes brucan<MILESTONE N="100b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">gyf] <I>in der Hs. nur</I> Gy <I>u. zw. radirt.</I> &Verbar; &thorn;&aelig;s anes <I>zweimal ge|schrieben.</I></NOTE> ne ma&yogh;e, brucu huru &thorn;es odres. Eornostlice, twa ysodene sufla<NOTE PLACE="foot">twa] wa <I>u. zw. aus</I> &thorn;a <I>rad. Hs.</I></NOTE> sy &yogh;enoh ealle &thorn;am &yogh;eswustre. Gyf man &aelig;ple habbe odde hwylces odres cynnes eordw&aelig;stmas, sy &that; to &thorn;riddan sufle. Sy<NOTE PLACE="foot">sy, s <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> anes pundes &yogh;ewicte hlaf to &aelig;allum d&aelig;&yogh;e. Gyf hy on twa m&aelig;l etad, sy &yogh;ehealden &thorn;&aelig;s pundmetan hlafes fr&aelig;m &thorn;&aelig;re hordestre swa &thorn;ridda d&aelig;l to &thorn;am &aelig;fen&yogh;yfle to &yogh;efenne. Gyf<NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;fen&yogh;yfle <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> hi mid weorces &yogh;eswince to &thorn;am swde ofersette beod, &thorn;&aelig;t hi<NOTE PLACE="foot">swde] syde <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> swilces eacan behofian, standa se eaca on &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse dome, &that; &thorn;onne swa sy foresceawod, swa &that; &thorn;&aelig;r n&aelig;fre oferfull ne fyli&yogh;e, fordi nis cristenum mannum nan &thorn;in&yogh; swa wider|weardlice &amp; hefityme swa swa oferfyll, be &thorn;am se helend sylf &thorn;us clypad: "Warniad, &that; eowere heortan ne syn ofersymede<NOTE PLACE="foot">&that; <I>bis</I> he- (<I>von</I> heortan) <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> mid oferfylle".</P>
<P>Geon&yogh;e m&aelig;idene ne sy &yogh;eseald bi&yogh;leofa by &thorn;am ylcan<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eseald] &yogh;esead <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;emete, ac lesse &thorn;onne &thorn;am maran, &that; forhefednes &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e on ylde &yogh;e on &yogh;eo&yogh;ode &aelig;fre &yogh;ehealden sy.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e] se <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Ealle endemest fram fl&aelig;sc&aelig;te eallum &yogh;emete hi forhabben,<NOTE PLACE="foot">eallum] eallec <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> buton &thorn;am wanhalum &amp; &thorn;am le&yogh;erf&aelig;stum.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="40" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XL. BE DRENCES &YOGH;EMETEN.<MILESTONE N="101a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Anra &yogh;ehwylc h&aelig;fd syndrie &yogh;yfe fram Gode, sume furdor &thorn;one sume, &amp; fordi &thorn;onne ic mid tweonin&yogh;um odrum mannum bi&yogh;leofan &yogh;esette; we &thorn;eah manna untrumnesse &amp; tyddernesse besceawiende &yogh;elyfad, &thorn;at &yogh;enoh sy &aelig;lcere mynechene to<NOTE PLACE="foot">besceawiende, e <I>in</I> &mdash; wien &mdash; <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> de&yogh;es drence &thorn;&aelig;s wynes &yogh;emet, &thorn;e is emina &yogh;ehaten. Wytan<MILESTONE N="101b" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;&aelig;ah &thorn;a, &thorn;e mid &yogh;e&thorn;ylde fram wine forhabbed, &that; hi &aelig;t Gode<NOTE PLACE="foot">wine <I>aus</I> &thorn;ine <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> mycele &amp; a&yogh;ene mede habbod. Gyf &thorn;one &thorn;&aelig;re stowe neod odde &yogh;edeorf odde sumorh&aelig;te hwylces eacan behofi&yogh;e, sy &that; on &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse dome, &amp; &thorn;one eacan swa foresceawi&yogh;e, swa &that; hi&yogh; n&aelig;fre myd oferfylle undersmo&yogh;ene &amp; beswicene ne weordan.
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="87"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="64,21-66,10"></P>
<P>We &thorn;eah r&aelig;dad, &thorn;&aelig;t mynecene eallun&yogh;a to windrence naht ne belimpe, ac fordi &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;t mynecene on urum tyman &yogh;elered beon ne m&aelig;&yogh;, we &thorn;a &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;e &thorn;es drences on &thorn;a wisan dod,<NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;t] &thorn;&aelig;r n&aelig;fre seo fyll be fullum ne weorde, ac sy &aelig;fre on<NOTE PLACE="foot">be] beo <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;re &thorn;i&yogh;ene forh&aelig;fodnes, &that; is &that; heo l&aelig;sse nime &thorn;one hyre lyste, for&thorn;am win &yogh;eded, &that; furdon witan oft misfod &amp; fram rihtum &yogh;eleafan bu&yogh;ad. &ETH;&aelig;r &thorn;e byd wana &thorn;urh &thorn;&aelig;re stowe h&aelig;uenleaste, &that; man &that; fulle wynes &yogh;emet habban ne mei, ac mycele lesse odde eallun&yogh;e n&aelig;nne del, bletsian &thorn;a heora drihten, &thorn;e &thorn;er wunian, &amp; hi na fordi ne ceorian, ne mid mode ne besar&yogh;ian; toforan eallum &thorn;ingum we myne&yogh;iat, &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;e &yogh;eswustre syn butan ceorun&yogh;e.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="41" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XLI. ON HWYLCE TIDE SCULON &YOGH;ESWUSTREN ETAN.<MILESTONE N="102a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Fram &thorn;am hal&yogh;an eastrum od pentecosten etan &yogh;eswustran on twa m&aelig;l, &that; is &aelig;rest on &thorn;&aelig;re syxtan tyde &amp; eft on &aelig;fen. Fram pentecosten ofer ealle sumer f&aelig;stun twe&yogh;en da&yogh;es on &thorn;ere wucan, &that; is wodnesd&aelig;&yogh; &amp; fri&yogh;ed&aelig;&yogh;, butan hi ofermicel &yogh;eswinc habban, odde swydlic h&aelig;te &thorn;&aelig;s sumeres deri&yogh;e; odrum d&aelig;&yogh;um etan on twa mel, &that; is to midd&aelig;i&yogh;es &amp; eft on<MILESTONE N="102b" UNIT="folio"> efen. Gyf hi&yogh; ut on &aelig;cere weorc habban, odde &thorn;&aelig;s sumeres<NOTE PLACE="foot">hi&yogh;, <I>das &yogh; radirt.</I> &Verbar; sumeres <I>das zweite</I> S <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile.</I></NOTE> wylm to swy&thorn;lic beod, &thorn;&aelig;s midded&aelig;&yogh;es &yogh;ereord is singallice<NOTE PLACE="foot">swy&thorn;lic] swilic <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> to onletenne, &that; &thorn;onne sy on hyre abbodesse forescewunge.<NOTE PLACE="foot">forescew., <I>das</I> C <I>auf Rasur</I> (<I>darunter</I> W?).</NOTE> Heo ealle &thorn;ing swa &yogh;emete&yogh;i&yogh;e &amp; &yogh;edihte, &that; hure sawla &yogh;e|healde beo &amp; &that; &that; &yogh;eswustre weorcean, wyrcean &that; buton ceorunge. Fram idus septembris od l&aelig;ntenes an&yogh;inne hi on an m&aelig;l to nones &yogh;ereordian. Ofer eall l&aelig;n&yogh;ten od eastren hi od &aelig;fen f&aelig;sten. And se &aelig;fen beo swa &yogh;ediht, &that; hi candeles leoctes &aelig;t &thorn;am &yogh;ereorde ne behofian, ac ealle &thorn;ing be d&aelig;i&yogh;es leohte &yogh;efyllede beon. On &aelig;lcene timan swa beo &yogh;efadod, swahw&aelig;|&thorn;&aelig;r hit sy an mel swa twa, &that; ealle &thorn;ing be d&aelig;&yogh;es leohte &yogh;een|doden syn.
</P>

