<DIV2 N="43" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XLIII. BE &THORN;AN &THORN;E CUME&ETH; TO LATA TO GODES &THORN;ENUN&YOGH;E AND TO &THORN;AN BORDE.<MILESTONE N="104b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Sona swa &that; beacn &thorn;&aelig;s belhringes &yogh;ehyred bid, &thorn;&aelig;rrihte forlete &aelig;&yogh;hwylc swa hw&aelig;t swa heo on handa h&aelig;fd, &amp; mid 
<PB REF="00000119.tif" N="91"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="68,1-69,8"> ofste &thorn;one tidsan&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;re godcundan &thorn;enunge &yogh;esece, onette &thorn;eah mid st&aelig;ddi&yogh;nesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">st&aelig;ddi&yogh;nesse] sc&aelig;ddi&yogh;nesse <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; na mid hi&yogh;eleaste, ne yrne heo, &thorn;el&aelig;s &thorn;e heo mid &thorn;&aelig;s rynes ed&yogh;un&yogh;e hwylcne wlettan &amp; so&yogh;edan on heore heortan astyri&yogh;e. Ne sy nan &thorn;ing &yogh;eset toforen &thorn;am Godes weorce, ne nan &thorn;ing swa beosorh, &thorn;&aelig;t heo heore tid|san&yogh;<NOTE PLACE="foot">heo <I>f. Hs.</I></NOTE> forlete.</P>
<P>Se &thorn;e to &thorn;es utsan&yogh;es an&yogh;ynne ne cume, &aelig;r &thorn;&aelig;s feower|andhundny&yogh;onti&yogh;odan sealmes glorian sy &yogh;esun&yogh;an, &that; is "Uenite<MILESTONE N="105a" UNIT="folio">exultemus domino", &thorn;one we eac fordi on &thorn;an son&yogh;e l&aelig;n&yogh;ed, ne stande heo na on chore on hyre stede &amp; endebyrnesse, ac stande heo ealre ytemest, odde on &thorn;am stede, &thorn;e &thorn;eo abbo|desse swa &yogh;ymeleasum manum to stealle on sundrum b&aelig;teht h&aelig;fed, sa &that; heo sy &yogh;esewen fram &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse &amp; fram<NOTE PLACE="foot">sa <I>davor Rasur eines Buchstaben.</I></NOTE> eallum hyre &yogh;eferum, &amp; &yogh;eendedum tidsan&yogh;e openlice hreosiende bete, &that; is astrecce hi&yogh; &aelig;t &thorn;&aelig;s tidsanges ende &amp; mid &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;esewenlicen dedbote heora &yogh;emeleste eadmodlice &yogh;ebete. We<NOTE PLACE="foot">ded|bobote <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> for&thorn;i tehton, &thorn;&aelig;t hi uteweardan odde on sundrum standan,<NOTE PLACE="foot">hi <I>von sp&auml;trer Hand zu</I> heo <I>corrigirt, dsgl. &uuml;ber</I> utew. <I>ein</I> on <I>geschrieben.</I></NOTE> &that; hi for &thorn;ere sceame &amp; for &yogh;ewande &thorn;&aelig;re, &thorn;e him onlokiad,<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>an</I> hi <I>ein</I> o <I>angesetzt von ders. sp&auml;tern Hand.</I> &Verbar; him] hyre <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ebeterede syn &amp; eft cafran to Godes &thorn;eoudome. Witodlice,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ebeterede] &yogh;ebetere, <I>dazu v. d. sp&auml;tr. Hd. &uuml;b. d. Z.</I> de.</NOTE> &yogh;yf heo widuten &thorn;&aelig;re cyrcan belifd for &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;emeleste, wen is, &thorn;&aelig;t sume odde sleaclice la&yogh;on &amp; slepon, odde sittende<NOTE PLACE="foot">odde (1.)] ddde <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mid idelre spellunge deofle to micelre forwyrdes intin&yogh;an &yogh;ese|alde; ac heo gan&yogh;e in, &that; hire se tidsang eallun&yogh;e ne losi&yogh;e, &amp; &that; heo on &thorn;am an&yogh;inne for&yogh;emeleosode, &yogh;efylle &amp; &yogh;ebete&middot; On &thorn;am d&aelig;&yogh;licum tidum, &thorn;eo &thorn;e to &thorn;am an&yogh;inne &thorn;&aelig;s tidsanges ne cume, &aelig;r &thorn;am &thorn;e se gloria &thorn;&aelig;s forman sealmes sy &yogh;esungen,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;esungen, u <I>&uuml;b. d. Z. zu</I> i <I>corrig.</I></NOTE> stande uteweardan,<NOTE PLACE="foot">uteweardan] <I>davor</I> on <I>von der sp&auml;tern Hand a. d. Rande.</I></NOTE> eallswa we &aelig;r cwedon; ne heo ne &yogh;edurst|leche, &thorn;at heo<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>ne &yogh;edurstl. &that; heo</I> auf den Rand von der sp&auml;teren Hand.</NOTE> &thorn;am chore &yogh;eneahl&aelig;ce, odde on heora ende|byrdnesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e|neahl&aelig;ce, <I>das &yogh; auf Rasur, worunter</I> n <I>gestanden zu haben scheint.</I></NOTE> stande, buton &thorn;eo abbodesse hyre &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;e mid leafa sylle; sy &thorn;eah &thorn;eo leafa on &thorn;a wisan, &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;&aelig;r &thorn;eo<MILESTONE N="105b" UNIT="folio">fores&aelig;d bot fylye &amp; hi mid &thorn;am eadmodlice scyldi&yogh;e &yogh;es|wuteli&yogh;e.
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="93"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="69,9-70,16"></P>
<P>Seo &thorn;e to &thorn;am beodferse ne cume, ac for sumen undeawa odde &yogh;ymeliste &yogh;emenelice mid &yogh;eswustre hyre drihten, &thorn;e is ealra &yogh;ereorda &yogh;yfend, mid herun&yogh;e ne &thorn;ancad, sy hyra twuwa mid wordum &yogh;estyred. Gyf heo be &thorn;isse steore betan nelle,<NOTE PLACE="foot">wordum, w <I>auf einem radirten</I> f <I>von ders. Hd.</I></NOTE> ne sy heora &yogh;em&aelig;ne &thorn;i&yogh;en mid &thorn;am &yogh;eswustrum &yogh;e&thorn;afod, ac heo ana &yogh;ereordie, ascyred fram hyre &yogh;eswustre, &amp; beo heo wines bed&aelig;led &amp; drince water, odd&aelig;t heo &thorn;&aelig;s &yogh;yltes &yogh;emeleste &yogh;ebete. On &thorn;as ycan wisan &thorn;oli&yogh;e and &yogh;ebete &thorn;eo, &thorn;e &aelig;t &thorn;am ferse ne byd, &thorn;e man &aelig;fter &yogh;ereorde cwyd.<NOTE PLACE="foot">cwyd] cyd <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Ne &yogh;edyrstlice nan, tofore &yogh;esettere tide ne &aelig;fter, nan &thorn;in&yogh; to &thorn;i&yogh;ene, ne on &aelig;te ne on w&aelig;te. Gyf hwam fram hyre<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;in&yogh; to, &thorn;in&yogh; t- <I>auf Rasur.</I> &Verbar; on &aelig;te] on <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> ealdre &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; &yogh;eboden sy to &thorn;i&yogh;ene, &amp; heo hit mid &yogh;ebel&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">heo <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> forsace, ne sy hyre to &yogh;ewilnedum m&aelig;le nanre odre &thorn;i&yogh;ene &yogh;etidod, buton &thorn;&aelig;s ylcan, &thorn;e heo &aelig;r forsoc, od&thorn;&aelig;t heo hit mid rihtre d&aelig;dbote &yogh;ebete.</P>
</DIV2>
