<HEAD>XLVIII. BE &AElig;LCES DA&YOGH;ES HAND&YOGH;EWEORCE.</HEAD>
<DIV3 TYPE="division">
<P>Efre byd idelnes &thorn;&aelig;re sawla fend, fordi &thorn;onne sculon &thorn;a<MILESTONE N="109a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">sawla, <I>das</I> 1. a <I>&uuml;b. d. Z. Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eswustre hwiltidum beon abyse&yogh;ode mid heora hand&yogh;eswince, hwiltidum mid hali&yogh;re r&aelig;din&yogh;e. We &thorn;onne fordi &yogh;elyfad, &that;<NOTE PLACE="foot">We <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> mid &thorn;issere fadun&yogh;e &aelig;&yogh;dres weorces tima m&aelig;&yogh;e beon &yogh;eende|byrd: &that; fram eastran od kalendas octobris, &that; is exaltatio <I>sancte</I> crucis, sona swa hi fram primsange &yogh;an&yogh;en, wyrcan hw&aelig;t &thorn;onne neod beo, od hit sy forneah an tid ofer undern; &aelig;fter<MILESTONE N="109b" UNIT="folio"> 
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="99"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="73,10-74,18"> &thorn;an r&aelig;den heore beec oddet hit beo neah midde&yogh;i. &AElig;fter midd&aelig;&yogh;e, syddon hi&yogh; &yogh;e&yogh;etene habben, gan to hire resta mid<NOTE PLACE="foot">midd&aelig;&yogh;e] midd- <I>auf Ras.</I> &Verbar; habben, <I>das</I> n <I>theilwcise zu &thorn; corrig. doch dies nicht vollendet, also</I> n <I>geblieben.</I></NOTE> ealre stilnesse; gyf &aelig;ni&yogh;re &thorn;onne leofre sy, &that; heo r&aelig;de, &thorn;onne<NOTE PLACE="foot">2-3. mid ealre stiln.] mid <I>bis</I> st- <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> heo r&aelig;ste, r&aelig;de &thorn;onne swa, &thorn;at heo mid &yogh;ehlyde &thorn;a odre ne drecce. Sy &thorn;e non &yogh;ehradod &amp; sy &yogh;erin&yogh;od, &thorn;onne &thorn;eo eahtode tid byd healf agan; &amp; wyrcan sydan, &that; neod sy, od &aelig;fen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">healf] heaf <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> Gyf &thorn;onne swa mycel &thorn;earf &thorn;&aelig;re stowe beo, &that; hy silfe scullon heore corn &amp; anlifene gaderian, &amp; hi on &thorn;am abise&yogh;ode beon, ne beo hi&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;ah &yogh;eunrotsod, fordan &that; beod &thorn;onne riht myne|cene,<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eunrotsod] <I>danach ein</I> e <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> &yogh;yf hi libbad be &thorn;am &yogh;eswince heora a&yogh;enra handa, swa swa ure f&aelig;deres &amp; &thorn;a apostoles didon. Beo hit &thorn;&aelig;ah eall mid &yogh;emette &yogh;edon for &thorn;am wacmodan.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="division">
<HEAD>TOD &AElig;LUN&YOGH;.<MILESTONE N="109b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">TOD &AElig;LUN&YOGH;] to d&aelig;lun&yogh; <I>vom Rubricator.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Fram kalendas octobris, &that; is fram &thorn;&aelig;re hali&yogh;e rode d&aelig;i&yogh;e od lenten, r&aelig;dan &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre heore becc, odd&aelig;t hit beon fullice an tid toforan undern. And &thorn;onne undern &yogh;esungen, wyrcan sydan od non le hwet me heom bitece. Sydon hi &thorn;one<NOTE PLACE="foot">hwet, h <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> forman cnyl to none &yogh;ehyren, &yogh;an hi ealle fram heore weorce &amp; don hi &yogh;earwe, &thorn;&aelig;t hi ma&yogh;on to cyrce gan, &thorn;onne man eft<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;earwe] earwe <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> cnille. &ETH;onne eft &aelig;fter hire nonmete r&aelig;dan hi eft on heore bec, odde syngon heore sealmes.</P>
</DIV3>
<DIV3 TYPE="division">
<HEAD>DIUISIO.<NOTE PLACE="foot">DIUISIO] Diuisio <I>vom Rubri|cator.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>On l&aelig;nctenf&aelig;sten r&aelig;den &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre heora bec, fram<MILESTONE N="110a" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;rne mor&yogh;en od heahne undern &amp; wurcan sydan &thorn;&aelig;t neod|&thorn;earf beo ane tid ofer non. Underfo heora &aelig;lc on formelen|tenes dei&yogh;e sume boc of &thorn;&aelig;re bibliotecan, &that; is of &thorn;am almeri&yogh;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">almeri&yogh;e] almri&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; r&aelig;de &thorn;a fram ende to odre. Beon &yogh;esette an odde twa ealde swustre, wise an(d) ripe, &thorn;e &that; mynster &yogh;eond&yogh;an&yogh;en &amp; &thorn;as<NOTE PLACE="foot">an(d)] an <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;yman, &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;&aelig;r nan swuster embe ydelnesse &amp; unnitte spece<NOTE PLACE="foot">unnitte, -itte <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> beo &amp; ne beo ymbe yre redinge, &thorn;e wile &thorn;e &thorn;a odre redan; &thorn;eos ylce sodlice ne byd heo na &that; an hyre sylfe unnitte, ac<NOTE PLACE="foot">unnitte, -itte <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000129.tif" N="101"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="74,18-76,18"> eac &thorn;a odra to &thorn;am tiht. Gyf &thorn;er &thorn;onne &aelig;ni&yogh; byd &yogh;efunde &thorn;us donde, swa hit na &yogh;ewurde, &thorn;onne styre man hyre &aelig;ne and odre syde; gyf heo hit &thorn;onne ne &yogh;ebete, underfo heo &thorn;&aelig;re<NOTE PLACE="foot">and] an <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> re&yogh;ollicen styre, swa &thorn;eah, &that; &thorn;a odre &thorn;e maren ei&yogh;e habben.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&that; <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> Ne nan swuster nabbe nane &yogh;e&thorn;eodr&aelig;dene to odre, ne on tocnun&yogh;e ne on spece on unrihtne time. Sunnumd&aelig;&yogh;um r&aelig;den hi ealle hali&yogh;e bec, butan &yogh;if wilc &aelig;ni&yogh;e wice h&aelig;fd.</P>
<P>Gyf &thorn;ar &thorn;onne &aelig;ni&yogh; swuster &yogh;efunde beo swa &yogh;emelas &amp; swa asolce, &that; heo nelle, odde ne ma&yogh;e hali&yogh;e bec smea&yogh;an odde r&aelig;dan, beo heore sum weorc b&aelig;teht, &thorn;&aelig;t heo ealles unnytt ne beo.</P>
<P>&ETH;am untruman &yogh;eswustre &amp; &thorn;am mearewum &amp; &thorn;am unweorc|heardum<NOTE PLACE="foot">mearewum] nearew. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> beo heom bet&aelig;ht sum weorc odde cr&aelig;ft, &that; nan ne beo idel on Godes huse, ne hi&yogh; mid nanes weorces un&yogh;emete<MILESTONE N="110b" UNIT="folio"> odde stidnesse ofsette ne sin; d&aelig;re abbodesse is &aelig;fre to be|hawienne heore wanhalnes.<NOTE PLACE="foot">15-16. behawienne, w <I>auf Rasur von 2 Buchst. nicht sicher ob von sp&auml;trer oder derselben Hand.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV3>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="49" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>XLIX. HU MAN SCEALL LENCTEN HEALDAN.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Zwischen</I> le- <I>und</I> -nct. <I>ein</I> c, <I>doch unterpunktirt.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eah mynecene on eallum tidum l&aelig;ntelic lif healden sculle<MILESTONE N="111a" UNIT="folio"> &amp; to feawa manna &that; lif swa stidlice healt, &thorn;&aelig;ahhwedere ealra swydest healdan hi&yogh; forhefednesse clensun&yogh;e on l&aelig;ntenfestene, swa &that; hi &thorn;onne on &thorn;am hal&yogh;um d&aelig;i&yogh;um &yogh;efille &that;, &that; hi mid &yogh;emeliste &aelig;r on oder time forlete. &ETH;&aelig;t &thorn;onne byd rihtlice &yogh;ediht, &yogh;yf hi fram eallum synnum &amp; undeawa hi sylfe heal|dad; beon hi fordi &yogh;eornfulle on gastlice redin&yogh;e &amp; on hali&yogh;e &yogh;ebede &amp; onbrirdnesse heora heortan.</P>
<P>Geycen hi&yogh; on &thorn;isum da&yogh;um sum &thorn;ing to heora &thorn;am &yogh;e|wunelice &thorn;eoudome, &that; is, widteo heora lichame of mete and drence, &that; &aelig;lc hyre a&yogh;enes willes Gode &aelig;lmihti&yogh;e sumne d&aelig;l bringe mid blysse &thorn;&aelig;s hal&yogh;en gastes of dam bufan &yogh;ecwedenan &yogh;emete hyra andlifene, &amp; be&yogh;an hi &yogh;eornlice syndri&yogh;e &yogh;ebede &amp; forhefednesse healdan, &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e on &aelig;te, &yogh;e on w&aelig;te, &yogh;e 
<PB REF="00000131.tif" N="103"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="76,18-79,16"> on slepe, &amp; hi &yogh;eorne bewerian, &yogh;e nu, &yogh;e on &yogh;elce time wid leohtbl&aelig;nesse idelre worde &amp; unnitte sp&aelig;cc &amp; &thorn;y leas leaslice<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;y leas] hy leas <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;&aelig;bere, &that; hi &thorn;a eastretid onbidon mid blisse &thorn;&aelig;re gastlican &yogh;ewilnun&yogh;e. &THORN;a &thorn;in&yogh;, &thorn;e hi heom sylfe widteod, don hit be &thorn;ere abbodesse leafe &amp; &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;e &amp; mid heora &yogh;ebede, for&thorn;am<NOTE PLACE="foot">leafe] leofe <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> swa hwet swa hi buten hire leafa dod &amp; hyre &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;e, &that; bid swidor to &yogh;ymelyste &amp; idel &yogh;ylpe to tellenne, &thorn;onne to &aelig;lmessan. &THORN;erfore &aelig;lc &thorn;&aelig;re &thorn;inge &thorn;e hi&yogh; don, don hit bi &thorn;ere<MILESTONE N="111b" UNIT="folio"> abbodesse leafa.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="50" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>L. BE &THORN;AM &YOGH;ESWUSTRE &THORN;E SWINCED FEORR FRAM MYNSTRE AND &THORN;AM &THORN;E BEO&ETH; ON WE&YOGH; ONFAREN.<NOTE PLACE="foot">WE&YOGH; ONFAREN] &thorn;e&yogh; on faren <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;a &yogh;eswustre &thorn;e feor synd on &yogh;eswince &amp; for &thorn;am fyrlene on &yogh;edafenlicum timum heora cyrcan &yogh;esecan ne m&aelig;&yogh;on &mdash; &yogh;if<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;edafenlic.] <I>aus</I> &yogh;edafeml. <I>rad.</I></NOTE> &thorn;eo abbodesse on&yogh;it, &that; hit swa sy &mdash; &yogh;efyllan hi&yogh; heora &yogh;etida<NOTE PLACE="foot">on&yogh;it, &yogh; <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;rrihte &thorn;&aelig;r hi&yogh; weorcan, &amp; mid Godes ei&yogh;e heora cneowa<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;&aelig;r] &that;, <I>danach</I> &aelig;r <I>radirt Hs.</I></NOTE> eadmodlicen &yogh;ebi&yogh;en.</P>
<P>Eallswa&yogh;elice don &thorn;a, &thorn;e on ferelde synd, &amp; hi na ne for&yogh;eman &thorn;a &yogh;esetten tida, ac &aelig;lcne tidsang &yogh;efulle, swa hi<NOTE PLACE="foot">&aelig;lcne, c <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> selost ma&yogh;on, &amp; &thorn;a &yogh;ewunelice w&aelig;&yogh;e heore &thorn;eoudomes ne for weorces bys&yogh;um, ne for ferelde on nane wise ne for&yogh;ymeleasian.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="51" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LI. BE &THORN;AM SWUSTRE &THORN;E NE FARAD FEORR AC<MILESTONE N="112a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">FARAD] fareid <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> CUMA&ETH; SONE.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;a &yogh;eswustre, &thorn;e for hwilcere neode utfared &amp; on &thorn;am<NOTE PLACE="foot">hwilcere, h <I>aus</I> w <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> ylcan d&aelig;i&yogh;e to mynstre cuman ma&yogh;on, ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;cen hi&yogh;, 
<PB REF="00000133.tif" N="105"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="79,16-83,7"> &that; hi&yogh; on eni&yogh;e stede ut of mynstre etan, &thorn;eah hi &aelig;ni&yogh; &yogh;eor|fedlice bidde, buton &thorn;eo abbodesse heom habben &yogh;ehaton. Gyf hi&yogh; hit oderlicer do, beon hi&yogh; amansumod.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="52" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LII. BE &THORN;&AElig;RE CYRCAN.</HEAD>
<P>Gebedhus sy to &thorn;am anum, &thorn;e hit &yogh;ecweden is, &thorn;&aelig;t is, &that; &thorn;&aelig;r nan &thorn;ing elles &yogh;eworuht ne sy odde &yogh;efadod butan &thorn;am anum weorce, &thorn;e to Gode belimped, &thorn;&aelig;t is &yogh;ebedreden. &AElig;t<MILESTONE N="112b" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;lces tidsanges endunge gan hi ut ealle mid micelre swi&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">ealle, a <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> &mdash; &amp; sy God &aelig;lmihti&yogh; &yogh;earwurdod &mdash; &thorn;&aelig;t seo swuster, &thorn;e hi&yogh; sunderlice to Gode &yogh;ebiddan wille, ne sy &yogh;elett odde &yogh;e|hremmed mid &aelig;ni&yogh;re odre onrope. Gyf hwylc heora eft<NOTE PLACE="foot">mid <I>fehlt Hs.</I> &Verbar; onrope] onwope <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> onsundran dih&yogh;lice &yogh;ebiddan hi wille, mid stilnesse anfealdlice heo ingange &amp; hi &yogh;ebidde, naht mid hludre st&aelig;fene, ac mid<NOTE PLACE="foot">in|gange &amp; hi, -e &amp; h- <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> teare &amp; mid wope &amp; mid heora heortan onbryrdnesse &amp; ealles &yogh;e&thorn;ances &yogh;emene. Eornestlice, &thorn;a &thorn;a &thorn;illic weorc &thorn;&aelig;rinne wyrcean nellad, ne sy hyre nan wunun&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;rinne &yogh;e&thorn;afod &aelig;fter &thorn;&aelig;s tidsanges &yogh;eendunge, &thorn;yl&aelig;s &thorn;e &thorn;a &yogh;elette beo, &thorn;e &thorn;a syn|derlice<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;yl&aelig;s] &thorn;yles, <I>zwischen</I> l <I>und</I> e <I>ein</I> c <I>radirt Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ebede lufiad.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="53" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LIII. HU MAN SCEALL CUMAN UNDERFON.<MILESTONE N="113b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Ealle cumen &thorn;e to mynstre cumad, syn hi onfangene, swilc hit Crist sylf sy, fordi &thorn;e he sylf &thorn;us cwyd on &thorn;am hali&yogh;e godspelle: "Ic wes gyst, &amp; &yogh;e me underfengen"; sy heom ealle &yogh;e&thorn;afenlice weordmynt &yogh;e&yogh;earewod, &thorn;eah swidost &thorn;am riht|&yogh;elifedum<NOTE PLACE="foot">weordmynt, d <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> urum husum &amp; &thorn;am forwrecenum &aelig;l&thorn;eodo&yogh;um.</P>
<P>Fordi eornostlice, sona swa se coma &yogh;ecyd sy, &thorn;eo priore<NOTE PLACE="foot">Fordi] Fodi <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; swa] <I>fehlt Hs.</I></NOTE> ga hire to&yogh;eanes, odde &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre, mid ealra &thorn;enun&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;re sodan lufe, &amp; &aelig;rest hi &yogh;ebidden heom &amp; swo syn on sodre sybbe &yogh;eferl&aelig;hte. Ne sy sybbecos heom &yogh;eboden, &aelig;rdam &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000135.tif" N="107"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="83,7-85,20"> hi to Gode &yogh;ebiddan &amp; bletsun&yogh;e underfon, for mystlicum deofles &yogh;ebismerungum. On &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;emenan gretinge sy eal eadmodness<MILESTONE N="114a" UNIT="folio"> &yogh;eboden &amp; &yogh;e&yogh;earowed eallum gystum, &thorn;e to mynstre cumad odde fram mynstre farad: anlute heom eadmodlice mid &thorn;am heafede, odde ealle &thorn;ane licamen on eordan astrecce, and Crist sy swa mid eadmodnesse &yogh;ebeden, &thorn;e &aelig;fre on cuman anfan&yogh;en beod. Syn hi to cyrecan &yogh;el&aelig;dde to &yogh;ebede; &amp; sydan hi&yogh; underfan&yogh;ene beod, sitte heora &aelig;fter &thorn;am &thorn;e priore mid, odde &thorn;eo, &thorn;e heo hate. Sy beforan &thorn;am cuman &yogh;er&aelig;d &thorn;eo god|cunda<NOTE PLACE="foot">cuman <I>aus</I> cumam <I>rad.</I></NOTE> &aelig; &amp; lar, &that; hi syn &yogh;etrimed to Godes willan; &aelig;fter &thorn;am beo heom &yogh;e&yogh;earewod &yogh;ehi&thorn;lice eall mennisclic fremfulnes.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ehi&thorn;lice] &yogh;ehihlice <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> Abrece se priore hire f&aelig;sten for cumena &thorn;inge, buten hit swilc heahlic f&aelig;stende&yogh; si, &thorn;e man abrecan ne &thorn;urre; &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre healdan &thorn;&aelig;ahhwedere heore festen &aelig;fter &yogh;ewunan. Geote &thorn;e abbodesse w&aelig;ter cuman to handum; dwean ealra gystene fett, ealswa wel &thorn;eo abbodesse ealswa eall &thorn;eo &yogh;eferreden; &aelig;fter &thorn;&aelig;re fettweascun&yogh;e sy &thorn;is fers &yogh;ecweden: "We onfen&yogh;on<NOTE PLACE="foot">-weas|cun&yogh;e] weascu&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> drihten, &thorn;ine mildheortnesse on &thorn;am midle &thorn;ines temples." &ETH;a<NOTE PLACE="foot">mildheortn.] t <I>f. Hs.</I></NOTE> heane &amp; &thorn;a pilegrimes ealre &yogh;eornest beon underfangene, fordam &thorn;e Crist on heom swidest byd anfangen; dere ricre manna<NOTE PLACE="foot">anfangen] unf. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ei&yogh;e &amp; ho&yogh;a &yogh;emyne&yogh;ad, &that; heomen sylfum weordlice sy<NOTE PLACE="foot">weordlice, o <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> &yogh;e&thorn;enod &amp; wyrdmynt &yogh;enoh &yogh;eboden, ac Godes ei&yogh;e ana myne|&yogh;ad,<MILESTONE N="114b" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;&aelig;t man &thorn;earfum &amp; &aelig;l&thorn;eodo&yogh;um mannum &yogh;e&thorn;ensum sy.</P>
<P>Sy &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse kicene &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re comena &aelig;tre onsundre, &that; &thorn;a &yogh;eswustra ne beo &yogh;eunstilde, &thorn;onne gystas f&aelig;rlice to mynstre cumed on uncude tyde; seldehwenne odde n&aelig;fre mynster buten<NOTE PLACE="foot">seldehwenne, h <I>auf Rasur, ob von ders. Hd. nicht sicher.</I></NOTE> comen byd. To &yogh;eares face twa &yogh;eswustre into gyste kicenan &yogh;an, &amp; &thorn;a syn swilce, &thorn;e wel &thorn;enian cunnen &amp; &thorn;a &thorn;enunge wyrdlice wel &yogh;efullan. Sy heom fultum &yogh;eseald, &yogh;yf hi &thorn;&aelig;s behofiad, &that; hi &thorn;urh &thorn;es fultumes frofer buten ceorunge &thorn;enian; eft &thorn;onne hi lessa bisega habbod, faran to swilcen weorce &amp; hyrsumnysse, swilce heom beboden sy. &ETH;es foresceawun&yogh; sy 
<PB REF="00000137.tif" N="109"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="85,20-87,20"> &yogh;ehealden na on &thorn;issum anum, ac on eallum mynstres &thorn;enunge, &that; is &thorn;onne hi behofian, sy heom fultum &amp; frofer &yogh;eseald, &amp; eft &thorn;onne hi byse&yogh;a on heora wicum nabban &amp; emti&yogh;e syndon, hyrsumian hi on swilcum &thorn;ingum, swilce heom man beode. Sy cumena hus swilcere swuster beteht to bewitenne, &thorn;e fulne Godes e&yogh;e h&aelig;bbe &amp; hyre sawle &yogh;eahni&yogh;e; beon &thorn;&aelig;r &aelig;fre bed &yogh;eno&yogh;e &amp; eac oferspredde, &that; Godes hus wislice fram witum sy fadod.</P>
<P>On nane wise heora nan wid cuman hi ne &yogh;eferl&aelig;ce odde<MILESTONE N="115a" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;ni&yogh;e spece wid hi ne a&yogh;e, buten &thorn;&aelig;re anre, &thorn;e hit beboden byd; gyf hi hwilcne cuman &yogh;emetan, greten hine eadmodlice on &thorn;a wisan, &thorn;e we &aelig;r cwedon, &amp; bletsunge hine bidde &amp; heo swa ford&yogh;an&yogh;e, sec&yogh;ende, &thorn;&aelig;t hyre alyfed nis, wid cuman to sp&aelig;cenne.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="54" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LIV. &THORN;&AElig;T MYNECENE NE SCULON WRITE OD&ETH;E LAC <NOTE PLACE="foot">MYNECENE] <I>das</I> 1. e <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I> &Verbar; WRITE] wwite, <I>das</I> 2. w <I>theilweise zu</I> r <I>corrig. Hs.</I></NOTE> UNDERFON.</HEAD>
<P>Ne sy on nane wyse mynecene alyfed, &that; heo &aelig;ni&yogh; &yogh;ewrit sende, odde heom betweonan underfon odde syllan, butan &thorn;are abbodesse hese. Gyf w&aelig;t heore &yogh;ehwylce asend byd fram<NOTE PLACE="foot">w&aelig;t] &thorn;&aelig;t <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hyre ma&yogh;um, ne &yogh;edyrstlece heo hit na to underfonne, &aelig;r hit &thorn;&aelig;r abbodesse &yogh;ecuded sy. Gyf &thorn;onne &thorn;eo abbodesse hit underfon hate, stande hit an hyre dome, hwan hit &yogh;yfe scule<MILESTONE N="115b" UNIT="folio"> beon; &amp; &thorn;eo swuster, &thorn;e swilc lac to asend w&aelig;s, ne beo nan &thorn;ing sari&yogh;, &thorn;el&aelig;s &thorn;e heo deofle &thorn;urh &thorn;&aelig;t &aelig;ni&yogh;e intin&yogh;an sylle, &amp; to michele blisse on hyre unrotnesse habbe. &ETH;e &thorn;e oderlicor <NOTE PLACE="foot">unrotnesse] unro|nesse <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;edyrstlice to donne, underfonge heo &thorn;&aelig;re re&yogh;ollice stere.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="55" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000139.tif" N="111"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="89,1-91,7">
<HEAD>LV. BE SWUSTRUM &YOGH;ESCRUDE.<MILESTONE N="116a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>SANCTE BENEDIHT &YOGH;&THORN;Y&ETH; MUNECE CULE AND YE|SETTE&ETH;<NOTE PLACE="foot">BENEDIHT &YOGH;&thorn;Y&ETH;] benedihit &yogh;ywd <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> MANTEL TO&YOGH;EANES &THORN;&AElig;RE CULE, AND HALI&YOGH;|RAFT,<NOTE PLACE="foot">3-4. YESETTE&ETH;] wesecced <I>Hs.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">MANTEL, <I>das</I> -an- <I>nicht deutlich.</I></NOTE> FOR&THORN;AN &THORN;E HIT NIS LA&YOGH;A &thorn;AT MUNECENE<NOTE PLACE="foot">4-5. HALI&YOGH;RAFT, <I>das</I> r <I>aus</I> e <I>corrig., nicht deutlich.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">NIS] isis <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> HABBEN CULE; HODES HI MA&YOGH;ON HABBAN, &YOGH;YF HI<NOTE PLACE="foot">HODES] hoder <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> WILLEN, FOR WURHCE AND EAC &THORN;ANNE HI FARE&ETH; UT,<NOTE PLACE="foot">WILLEN] willem <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &YOGH;YF HI SWA WYLLE&ETH;.</P>
<P>Sy &thorn;am &yogh;eswustre reaf &yogh;eseald be swylcnesse &amp; stadole<MILESTONE N="116b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">swylcnesse] smyltnesse <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;re stowe, &thorn;e hi onwuniad &amp; be &thorn;&aelig;s eardes odde &thorn;&aelig;re lyfte &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;ewidere; on cealde earde behofad mare, on wearme l&aelig;ssen. &ETH;eos foresceawun&yogh; belid to &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse.</P>
<P>We &thorn;eah &yogh;elyfad, on medeme stede &that; &yogh;enoh beo &aelig;lcere<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;enoh] <I>vor &yogh; ein unvollst&auml;ndiges</I> e <I>oder</I> c <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mynecene, &that; heo habbe anne mantel &amp; &aelig;nne curtel; sy on wintre se mentel of &thorn;icce hr&aelig;&yogh;ele, on sumere beon &thorn;ynne odde eald awerod, &amp; hod mid to wyrcenne; habben hi&yogh; eac haliref; habban hi to fot&yogh;ewedum hosa &amp; meon. Ne cide na &thorn;a myne|cene ymbe &thorn;a dea&yogh;e odde greatnesse hyre reafe; ac habben hi swilce reaf, swilce me finde ma&yogh;e on &thorn;am earde, &thorn;e hi on|wuniad, odde swilce me undyrest bic&yogh;en ma&yogh;e. Besceawie &thorn;eo abbodesse &amp; hate besydian &thorn;&aelig;re reafe &yogh;emet, &that; hi ne beon sceorte, ac &yogh;em&aelig;te &thorn;am, &thorn;e hi notiad.</P>
<P>A&yogh;yfen &aelig;fre &thorn;a ealden, &thorn;onne me heom niwe reaf sylle, &amp; to hr&aelig;&yogh;lhuse bet&aelig;cen, &thorn;earfum to delenne. Genoh is myne|cene &amp; full&yogh;enihtsum, &that; heo habbe twe&yogh;e mentles &amp; tweie cyrtles for &thorn;&aelig;re nyhtwara &amp; for &thorn;es riefes wesce; idel and oferfloend byd eal, &that; toforan &thorn;isum is, &amp; &yogh;yf mare byd, hyt sy &yogh;ewanod. Swa oft swa hi ador odde meon odde &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;ing niwen underfon, a&yogh;yfen hi &aelig;fre &thorn;&aelig;t ealde.
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="113"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="91,8-93,7"></P>
<P>&THORN;a &thorn;e on ytin&yogh;e ahwider farod, nimen hi reaf of hr&aelig;&yogh;lhuse,<MILESTONE N="117a" UNIT="folio"> &amp; swa hi ham cuman of &thorn;am f&aelig;relde, a&yogh;yfen hi a&yogh;ean. Sy eac on hr&aelig;&yogh;lhuse &yogh;ehealden &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e mentles &yogh;e cyrtles sumed&aelig;le beteran &thorn;onne &thorn;a, &thorn;e hi &yogh;ewunelice weried; &amp; notian &thorn;&aelig;re, &thorn;e for hwilcere neode on ytin&yogh;e farad, &amp; &thorn;a eft &thorn;ere hr&aelig;&yogh;l&thorn;enestre bet&aelig;ce, swa hi ham cuman.</P>
<P>To bedreafe &yogh;enoh is to habbenne meatta &amp; hwitel &amp; bedfelt &amp; pyle. &ETH;eahhw&aelig;dere &thorn;eo abbodesse sceall &yogh;elomlice scewian &thorn;a bedd &amp; asecean for syndrium &aelig;htum. Gyf hi hwa habbe, odde on hyre bedde funden sy, &that; heo fram hire abbodesse ne onfen&yogh; &amp; &thorn;urh hyre &yogh;yfe, ne leafa, ne &thorn;afun&yogh;e n&aelig;fde, underlic&yogh;e &thorn;eo &thorn;&aelig;re hefe&yogh;estan &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re stidesten disce|pline.<NOTE PLACE="foot">hefe&yogh;estan] <I>davor steht</I> hefestan, <I>ist aber durchstrichen.</I></NOTE> To&thorn;i &that; &thorn;&aelig;s leahter syndrie &aelig;hte mid ealle &yogh;ewanod beo &amp; adile&yogh;od sy fram heom ealle, syn &yogh;esealde fram &thorn;ere<NOTE PLACE="foot">adile|&yogh;od] adi&yogh;elod <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> abbodesse ealle neodbehefe &thorn;in&yogh;, &that; is mentel, cyrtel, meon hose, gyrdel, seax, greffe, nedle, sceat, weaxbrede, &thorn;&aelig;t &aelig;lcere neode beladun&yogh; sy adile&yogh;od, &that; hi &thorn;urh neode nane tale to<NOTE PLACE="foot">adile&yogh;od, -ile&yogh;od <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> syndre &aelig;hte nabban. Efre sceal beon fram &thorn;are abbodesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">fram] <I>danach nochmals</I> fram, <I>doch ausgestrichen.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eornlice bescewod &amp; behealden &thorn;e cwyde, &thorn;e awriten is on<NOTE PLACE="foot">behealden, -heal- <I>auf Ras.</I> &Verbar; cwyde] cyde <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;ere becc, &thorn;e is &yogh;ehaten "Actus apostolorum", &that; is, &aelig;&yogh;hylcum w&aelig;s &yogh;eseald, swa swa heo behofede &amp; nyde h&aelig;fde. Swa eac &thorn;eo abbodesse foresceawi&yogh;e swide &yogh;eorne &thorn;&aelig;re seocnesse, &thorn;&aelig;re<MILESTONE N="117b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eorne, &yogh; <I>auf Rasur.</I> &Verbar; seocnesse, c <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> &thorn;e mare healpes behofiad, &amp; na on hire neode wandie for dam yfelam willan nydfulran manna; be&thorn;eance heo Godes ed|lean<NOTE PLACE="foot">manna] manmanna <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> on ealle hyre dome, &that; is &that; hyre bid &aelig;t Godes dome<NOTE PLACE="foot">ealle] <I>zweimal geschrieben Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eleanod, be &thorn;am &thorn;e heo &aelig;r worhte.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="56" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LVI. BE &AElig;BBADESSE MYSE.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;&aelig;re abbodesse bord sceal beon &yogh;emene &thorn;earfum &amp; &aelig;l|&thorn;eodu&yogh;um mannum. &THORN;onne heo lyt cumena habbe, ladi&yogh;e hyre to swilce &yogh;eswustre, swilce heo wille; stonda in heore dome, hwilce &thorn;a syn; l&aelig;te &thorn;eahhwedere ane odde twa of &thorn;am yldeste mid &thorn;am &yogh;eswustre, &thorn;e hyre &thorn;eawa be&yogh;yman.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="57" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000143.tif" N="115"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="95,1-97,13">
<HEAD>LVII.<MILESTONE N="118a" UNIT="folio"> BE MYNSTRES CR&AElig;FTI&yogh;E MAN.</HEAD>
<P>Gyf cr&aelig;fti&yogh;e menn on mynstre syn, be&yogh;an hi hire creft mid ealre eadmodnesse and &yogh;eornlice wyrcan, &yogh;yf hit &thorn;eo abbodesse &yogh;e&thorn;afod. Gyf eni&yogh; hire for &thorn;es cr&aelig;ftes &thorn;ingon hi&yogh; to&thorn;unden|lice onhef&thorn; &amp; modi&yogh;ad for hyre cr&aelig;fte, for&thorn;am &thorn;e heo bed&aelig;le<NOTE PLACE="foot">onhef&thorn;] onhefh <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;re stowe mid hyre crefte fremed, sy heo ascyred fram &thorn;am cr&aelig;fte &amp; na l&aelig;n&yogh; &thorn;ene creft ne do, buton heo mid micelre eadmodnysse &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse unnan bi&yogh;ite.</P>
<P>Gyf man hwet becypan sculle, &thorn;es &thorn;e &thorn;a cr&aelig;fti&yogh;e menn on mynstre wyrcad, locian &thorn;a, &thorn;e &thorn;one ceape drifad, &that; hi nan &thorn;ing facenlices on &thorn;am ceape ne don; gemunan hi&yogh; &aelig;fre Ananiam &amp; Safiram, &thorn;el&aelig;s &thorn;e hi&yogh; &thorn;one dead on hyre sawle &thorn;olian, &thorn;e hi licamlice &thorn;oledan, &aelig;lc &thorn;&aelig;re &thorn;e on &thorn;isum odde on eni&yogh;um odrum mynstres &thorn;ingum &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; facenlices ded. &ETH;eo yfele &yogh;ytsun&yogh;e on &thorn;am wyrde ne beo &aelig;tywed, ac sume<MILESTONE N="118b" UNIT="folio"> dele sy hit &yogh;eseald undyrer, &thorn;onne oddre woruldmen dod, &thorn;&aelig;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">oddre, r <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> God &aelig;lmihti&yogh;es lof on eallum &thorn;ingum stonde.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="58" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LVIII. BE &THORN;AM NIWAN SWUSTRAM HU ME SCEALL HI&YOGH;<NOTE PLACE="foot">NIWAN] ni&thorn;an <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> UNDERFON.</HEAD>
<P>Gyf hwa&middot; niwan to mynstres drohnun&yogh;e &yogh;ecyrren wile, ne<MILESTONE N="119b" UNIT="folio"> sy hyre na &yogh;edelice &thorn;es infares &yogh;etidod; ac do man ealswa swa se apostol cwed, &that; is &that; me &yogh;yrnlice fandi&yogh;e, hwader hi&yogh; mid Godes gaste afyllede syn. Gyf heo &yogh;e&thorn;ildelice forbyrd &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e hosp &yogh;e edwite, &amp; on &thorn;ere weorne &thorn;eah &thorn;urhwunad &amp; eadmodlice bitt, &thorn;&aelig;t me heore inf&aelig;res tidi&yogh;e, sy heo under|fonge embe ane feower d&aelig;&yogh;as odde fifi &amp; wuni&yogh;e on gystehuse<NOTE PLACE="foot">feower, w <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> ana feawa d&aelig;&yogh;es.</P>
<P>Sydde beo heo on nicumenre manne huse, &amp; heo &thorn;er ete<MILESTONE N="120a" UNIT="folio"> &amp; reste &amp; embe hyre &yogh;astlice &thorn;earfa smea&yogh;e. And an gastlic 
<PB REF="00000145.tif" N="117"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="97,13-101,3"> ealdor &amp; wis hyre habbe &yogh;emenne, &thorn;e wel sawla Gode cunne &yogh;estrinan, deo &yogh;eorne beho&yogh;ie &amp; &yogh;elomlice &yogh;yme, hw&aelig;der heo<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;estrinan, i <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> mid fulre anbrirdnesse &amp; arwurdnesse God &aelig;lmihti&yogh; sece, &amp; hwed&aelig;r heo carfull beo &amp; sceot to Cristes weorc&aelig; &amp; to &yogh;e|hyrsumnesse, &amp; hw&aelig;d&aelig;r heo mid &yogh;e&thorn;ylde t&aelig;lun&yogh;e edwite &thorn;olien wille. Sy heora &yogh;esceawod &amp; &yogh;ebodod eall &thorn;eo stidnesse &amp; &thorn;eo earfodnesse, &that; to Godes rice &thorn;a &thorn;olobyrde &yogh;el&aelig;tt. Gyf heo &thorn;onne beh&aelig;tt sta&thorn;olfeste &thorn;urhwuniunge, &aelig;fter twam mon&thorn;e sy &thorn;es re&yogh;ol toforen hyre eall &yogh;ered, &amp; sy heore &thorn;us to &yogh;ecweden: "Her is seo &aelig;&macr;, &thorn;e &thorn;u under hyre tecinge winnan wilt &amp; cam|pian; gyf &thorn;e onha&yogh;i&yogh;e, &that; &thorn;u hit healden ma&yogh;e, far &thorn;e inn; &yogh;yf &thorn;e na onha&yogh;i&yogh;e, far &thorn;e fri, &thorn;ider &thorn;e &thorn;u wille". Gyf heo &thorn;onne &yogh;yt &thorn;urhwunad, sy heo &yogh;el&aelig;d eft to nicumra manna husa, &amp; hyre me &yogh;eorne fondie, hwader heo &thorn;olomod sy &amp; &yogh;e&thorn;yldi&yogh;. Eft embe syx mondas sy hyre &yogh;er&aelig;d eall &thorn;es reo&yogh;el fram forewerdon ende to oder, &that; heo &yogh;eorlice understonde, hwet hit sy, &thorn;e heo tofundad. Gyf heo &thorn;onne &yogh;yt &thorn;urhwunad,<MILESTONE N="120b" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;fter feor mon&thorn;e sy hyre &aelig;ft &thorn;&aelig;s ylce re&yogh;el &yogh;ered. Gyf heo &thorn;onne by hyre a&yogh;ene dome behet, &that; heo ealle &thorn;ing healden wille &amp; ealle &thorn;&aelig;s re&yogh;ules bebode mid eadmodnesse &yogh;eornlice &yogh;efyllon, sy heo underfangen on &thorn;ere &yogh;eferredenne; wite heo eac, &thorn;&aelig;t heo is mid &thorn;es re&yogh;eles bende swo &yogh;eti&yogh;ed &amp; &yogh;est&aelig;|&thorn;elod, &thorn;&aelig;t heo fr&aelig;m &thorn;em dai&yogh;e of &thorn;am mynstre fare ne mot,<NOTE PLACE="foot">of] on <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ne heore sweren ascacan ne ascyrian fram &thorn;am &yogh;eoce &thorn;es<NOTE PLACE="foot">ascyrian] acyrian <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> halgan re&yogh;ulam, &thorn;onne heo moste er ode &yogh;echeson odde awerpen on swa langsume fyrste.</P>
<P>Sydan heo underfangen sy &amp; innan cyrcan &yogh;ebroht, behate he beforan ealre &yogh;eferedenne Gode &amp; eallum his hal&yogh;um, &that; heo stad&aelig;lf&aelig;st on mynstre wunian wylle &amp; hyre &thorn;eawes to Gode ealle wille &yogh;eweman &amp; on hyrsumnysse &thorn;urhwunian; gyf &thorn;onne &aelig;fr&aelig;hwenne &thorn;is behat abrecd, wite heo, &thorn;&aelig;t heo byd &yogh;enidered &amp; &yogh;ehined, &that; is ascirod fram &aelig;lmihtium drihtene, &thorn;e heo &yogh;ebismerod. Be hyre behate sette heo festnun&yogh;e mid<NOTE PLACE="foot">behate, be <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ewrite to &thorn;are hal&yogh;ene name, &thorn;e hyre reliquie, &that; is heora ban, on &thorn;&aelig;re stowe rested, &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse name on &thorn;am write 
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="119"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="101,3-103,11"> beo &yogh;eset. Write heo &thorn;eo f&aelig;stnun&yogh;e hyresylf mid hyre agenre hande, &yogh;yf &thorn;onne write ne cunne, bidde odere, &thorn;e writen cunnen,<MILESTONE N="121a" UNIT="folio"> &that; hi aspelie, &amp; heo sylf on &thorn;am &yogh;ewrite roden tacn mearcie &amp; hi&yogh; swa f&aelig;stniende mid hyre a&yogh;ene hande uppan &thorn;&aelig;t altare alec&yogh;e. Sona swa heo &that; &yogh;ewrit uppan &thorn;&aelig;t altare lec&yogh;e, be|&yogh;ynne &thorn;is fers &amp; &thorn;us cwede: "Suscipe me, <I>Domine, secundum</I> eloquium tuum, et uiuam; et ne confundas me ab expectatione<NOTE PLACE="foot">expectatione] expectione <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mea". "Drihten, onfoh me &aelig;fter &thorn;inre behese, &amp; ic libbe; &amp; ne &yogh;escend &thorn;u me on minre anbidun&yogh;e". &thorn;at ylce fers heo sceal &thorn;riwa cwedan, &amp; eall &yogh;eferreden &thorn;riwa mid &thorn;an ylce ferse andswarian and &thorn;arto &thorn;eodan: "Gloria patri". &ETH;eo sylue<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;eodan] &yogh;eodan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> minecene swuster, syddan hit &yogh;edon bid, &yogh;efealle to &aelig;lcere swuster fote &amp; &thorn;&aelig;s wilnie, &that; hi for hyre &yogh;ebiddan; of &thorn;am d&aelig;&yogh;e sy heo swuster &yogh;eteald on &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eferreddenne.</P>
<P>Gyf heo hwilce &aelig;hte habbe, odde heo hi &thorn;earfe dele, odde heo hi&yogh; arwurdlice mid hyre sylfre &thorn;am mynstre &yogh;yfe &amp; na &thorn;ing mid hyre sylfre to sundrium &aelig;hte ne healde; sodlice, of<NOTE PLACE="foot">sodlice] sodlice mit gode rihte &thorn;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;am d&aelig;&yogh;e ne ah heo fordon hyres a&yogh;enes licaman &yogh;eweald, &thorn;e odre &aelig;hte ne sceolde. Hi man sona unscride &amp; &thorn;a reaf nime, &that; heo &aelig;r notede, &amp; hi&yogh; mid mynstres reafe &yogh;escryde. Healde mon on hre&yogh;lhuse &thorn;a reaf, &thorn;e hyre ofdyde, to&thorn;i, &yogh;yf<MILESTONE N="121b" UNIT="folio"> heo ahw&aelig;nne mid deofles costnunge beswicen byd, &that; heo on &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;e &yogh;&aelig;d, &that; heo hyre &yogh;ehat &YOGH;ode aw&aelig;&yogh;e &amp; &that; mynster forl&aelig;te, &that; na n&aelig;fre ne &yogh;eweorde, sy heo ben&aelig;med &thorn;es &yogh;od|cunden reafes &amp; mid &thorn;am woruldcundum, &thorn;e heo &aelig;r forlett, &yogh;escrid, &amp; swa of mynstre adr&aelig;fod beo. Healde man &thorn;eah|hw&aelig;dere<NOTE PLACE="foot">of, f <I>auf Rasur, wie es scheint ursprgl.</I> n.</NOTE> efre &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ewrit hera festnun&yogh;e on &thorn;am mynstre.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="59" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LIX. BE RICERE MANNA CILDE OD&ETH; UNRICHI HU ME SCEALL<MILESTONE N="122a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">RICERE, <I>aus</I> ricewe <I>corr.</I> &Verbar; MANNA, <I>aus</I> manne <I>corr.</I></NOTE> HI UNDERFON.</HEAD>
<P>Gyf hwilc rice mann &amp; &aelig;&thorn;elboren his bearn Gode on<NOTE PLACE="foot">his bearn, his bear- <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> mynstre &yogh;eoffrien wile, &yogh;yf &thorn;&aelig;t cild &thorn;&aelig;s and&yogh;yttes nabbe, &that; 
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="121"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="103,12-105,20"> heo sylf m&aelig;&yogh;e odde cune hy sylue, &yogh;efestnian hi&yogh; &thorn;a ma&yogh;as mid offrun&yogh;e, &that; is, hi&yogh; bewinde &thorn;&aelig;s cildes hand on &thorn;am weo|fodclade &amp; &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ewrit heore festnun&yogh;e &amp; hi&yogh; swa Gode &yogh;eoffrian<NOTE PLACE="foot">festnun&yogh;e] festnu&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mid offrunge hlafes &amp; wines.</P>
<P>Behaten &thorn;e ma&yogh;es and mid a&thorn;e &yogh;efestnian, &that; hi nefre syndrie &aelig;htan heora ma&yogh;a syllan nellad, ne &thorn;urh hi sylfe ne &thorn;urh n&aelig;nne &yogh;espelian, ne hi nefre n&aelig;nne intin&yogh;an ne secean, hu hi&yogh; hyre to syndrium ehtum &yogh;erimed beo. Gyf hy&yogh; &thorn;onne hwet syllan willan, syllen hi &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;ere hal&yogh;an stowe to rihte &yogh;emenscipe, heom te eacan edleane; &amp; heom sy wenestes &yogh;e|tidad, &amp; swa mid weneste ham cyrran, &yogh;yf &thorn;&aelig;s wilnian.<NOTE PLACE="foot">10-11. &yogh;etidad, -ad <I>aus</I> -at <I>corrig.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">weneste, w <I>aus</I> &thorn; <I>rad.</I> &Verbar; cyrran, -ran <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> Sy ealle &thorn;a &aelig;hte, &thorn;e &thorn;am cilde &yogh;ebyri&yogh;e, swa fordyle&yogh;ode &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ebyri&yogh;e, y <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> todelode, &that; him nan hiht ne &thorn;urfe beon, &thorn;&aelig;l&aelig;s &thorn;e hit losi&yogh;e, &yogh;yf hit his hiht on sundri&yogh;en &aelig;hte beset, &that; na n&aelig;fre ne &yogh;e|wurde;<MILESTONE N="122b" UNIT="folio"> we foroft onfunden, &that; m&aelig;ni&yogh;e reowlice losode &thorn;urh &thorn;one leasa hiht syndri&yogh;e &aelig;hte.<NOTE PLACE="foot">syndri&yogh;e] syndrire <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>Don handswa&yogh;elice be heore beornum, &thorn;a &thorn;e unrice synde &amp; hafenlease &thorn;earfan. Gyf hi nane &aelig;hta mid ealle to syllenne<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Zwischen</I> hafen <I>und</I> lease <I>Rasur von</I> en.</NOTE> nabben, offrie heore bearn anfealdlice on &yogh;ewitnesse riht&yogh;eli|fedra manna.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="60" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LX. BE HALI&YOGH;E EALDRE &THORN;E WUNIA&ETH; ON WORULDLICRE<MILESTONE N="123a" UNIT="folio"> WUNIUN&YOGH;E &THORN;E WYLNIAD INN TO MYNSTRE &THORN;AS WE CLEOPIA&ETH; NUNNE OD&ETH;E OFFESTRE.<NOTE PLACE="foot">CLEOPIA&ETH;, e <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Gyf hwylc abbodesse odde &aelig;ni&yogh; ealdor of hali&yogh;re ende|byrdnisse &yogh;ewilnad, &that; me hi on mynecene mynstre underfo, ne beo heom naht rade &yogh;etidod. Gyf hi &thorn;onne &thorn;urhwunian on<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;urhwunian] &thorn;urhtw. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;ewilnunge, ne sy heom naht forl&aelig;ten of &thorn;am re&yogh;ole for hyre ealdorscypes arwurdnesse, ac underfo heo &yogh;erne &aelig;lcne re&yogh;oles &thorn;eaw &amp; t&aelig;cinge; sy heo &aelig;fter Cristes boce t&aelig;cun&yogh;e &thorn;us &yogh;eaxod: "Freond, to hwam come &thorn;u?" &ETH;&aelig;t is on and&yogh;yte: 
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="123"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="105,20-109,12"> Come &thorn;u mit sybbe &amp; mid sodre lufe, odde mid un&thorn;w&aelig;rnesse &amp; licetun&yogh;e? Sy hyre &yogh;e&thorn;afod, &that; heo stede &aelig;fter &thorn;&aelig;re abbo|desse healde &amp; bletsun&yogh;e sylle, &yogh;yf &thorn;eo abbodesse swa hate;<NOTE PLACE="foot">abbodesse <I>zweimal geschrieben Hs.</I></NOTE> ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;ce heo nane &thorn;enun&yogh;e to be&yogh;ynnen, bute &thorn;&aelig;re abbo|desse hese; sy heo &aelig;fre &yogh;eare to &aelig;lcere steore be re&yogh;oles tecin&yogh;e, &amp; swa mycle ma heo eowi&yogh;e edmodnesse &amp; &yogh;ode forbysne, swa heo furdor on hade &amp; on &thorn;un&yogh;enesse is; bysni&yogh;e heo a ealle eadmodnysse eallum &thorn;am, &thorn;e hyre midwuniad. Gyf heo for hyre ealdorscypes arwurdnesse furdur forl&aelig;ten sy, ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;ce heo on nanre &yogh;efadunge &thorn;urh &thorn;es ealdorscypes<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;efadun&yogh;e] <I>Hs. nur</I> &yogh;e.</NOTE> truwan na furdor, &thorn;onne hyre &yogh;ecyrednesse sy, ac besceawi&yogh;e<MILESTONE N="123b" UNIT="folio"> &aelig;fre &thorn;one steal hyre &yogh;ecyrednesse &amp; heo be &thorn;am &yogh;emedemi&yogh;e, butan hi man for dan ealdorscype fur&thorn;ur forl&aelig;te.<NOTE PLACE="foot">fur&thorn;ur] fuw&thorn;ur <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>&ETH;a &yogh;elereden &yogh;eonge men, &thorn;e mynecenhad wilniad, sy hi&yogh;<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;elereden, <I>das</I> e <I>zw.</I> r <I>und</I> d <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile.</I></NOTE> underfan&yogh;ane on medemum stede, swa &thorn;eah, &that; hi behat don be heora sta&thorn;elf&aelig;stnesse &amp; be ealre &thorn;es hali&yogh;an reogeles &yogh;ymene.<NOTE PLACE="foot">reogeles, <I>das</I> e <I>in</I> reo <I>unten mit Tilgungspunkt versehen.</I></NOTE></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="61" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXI. BE UTCUMENE MENECENE.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eo utcumene mynecene, &thorn;e of uncu&thorn;en earde cymd, &yogh;yf<MILESTONE N="124a" UNIT="folio"> heo on cumene wise wunian wyle &amp; mid nanre oferflowednesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">cumene] <I>aus</I> cuman <I>corrigirt.</I></NOTE> &that; mynster ne dref, ac byd eadhylde &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re stowe &yogh;etricce, sy heo onfan&yogh;en &amp; swa lange wunye, swa hyre sylfe lycie. Gyf heo &yogh;esceadlice mid eadmodnesse &amp; mid sodre lufe eni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; on mynstre t&aelig;le odde t&aelig;ce, underfo &thorn;eo abbodesse &that; mid<NOTE PLACE="foot">on <I>aus</I> om <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> eadmodnesse &amp; smea&yogh;e on hyre &yogh;e&thorn;once, &that; hi God &thorn;ider as&aelig;nde, &that; seo stow &thorn;urh hyre &yogh;egoded &amp; &yogh;eriht were.
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="125"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="109,13-111,14"><MILESTONE UNIT="F" N="140,1-8"></P>
<P>Gyf heo eft on &aelig;ni&yogh;e time hi&yogh; sylfe to mynstres wunun&yogh;e &yogh;ef&aelig;stnian wille, ne sy na hyra &yogh;ewilnun&yogh; onscunod, for&thorn;i &thorn;e me mihte hyre lif oncnawen on &thorn;am fyrste, &thorn;e heo on cuman<NOTE PLACE="foot">lif <I>&uuml;ber der Zeile von etwas sp&auml;trer Hand.</I></NOTE> hiwe on mynstre wunede. Gyf me hy leahterfull on&yogh;yt on<MILESTONE N="124b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">wunede, wu|von <I>etwas sp&auml;terer Hand a. d. Rande</I>, -nede <I>beginnt die n&auml;chste Zeile.</I> &Verbar; hy <I>aus</I> hyre <I>radirt, doch sogleich, da das folgende</I> 1 <I>auf dem</I> e <I>steht.</I></NOTE> &thorn;one time, &thorn;e heo &yogh;ist bid, ne sceal heo a&yogh;en nane &yogh;e&thorn;eode, na&thorn;er ne wid &that; mynster ne wid &thorn;a &yogh;eferredenne, ac me hyre<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eferredenne, &yogh;e- <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> sec&yogh;e mid arwurdnesse, &that; heo &thorn;anan &yogh;ewite, &thorn;eles &thorn;e heo mid hyre yrmde &thorn;&aelig; odre &yogh;eleahtri&yogh;e. Gyf heo &thorn;onne swilc afunde byd on &thorn;&aelig;re cumlidnesse, &thorn;&aelig;t heo ne sy wyrde &thorn;&aelig;re scyriun&yogh;e, &thorn;eah he na ne bidde, myne&yogh;i&yogh;e me hi&yogh; swa &thorn;eah, &that; heo &thorn;&aelig;r wunun&yogh;e healde, to&thorn;i &that; odre &thorn;urh hyre gode bysnun&yogh;e wel &yogh;el&aelig;rede beon &amp; &yogh;ebeterade, fordi &thorn;e on elc&aelig;re stowe is anum drihtene, &thorn;am hefonlican cynge, &yogh;e&thorn;eowod &amp; &yogh;ehyrsumod. Gyf &thorn;eo abbodesse hyre &yogh;eearnunge swilce on&yogh;yte, heo mot hy be sume d&aelig;le furdur wurdian &amp; hire innor stede &amp; setl<NOTE PLACE="foot">setl] <I>daran von etwas sp&auml;terer Hand ein</I> e <I>angeh&auml;ngt. Ueber dem vorhergehenden</I> &amp; <I>eine Rasur von mehreren (nicht deutlich erkennbar wie vielen) Buchstaben, doch nichts erkenntlich.</I></NOTE> t&aelig;cen. Na &that; an be mynecene anum, ac eac swilce arwurde wifmanne, &thorn;e oft cumed to mynecene life, m&aelig;&yogh; &thorn;e abbodesse furdur arwurdian, &yogh;yf heo hyre lifes &yogh;eearnun&yogh;e swilce tocn&aelig;wd.<NOTE PLACE="foot">arwurdian, r <I>in</I> ar- <I>&uuml;ber d. Z. dies. Hand.</I></NOTE></P>
<P>W&aelig;rni&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;ahhwedere &thorn;eo abbodesse, &that; heo nateshwon of nane cude mynstre mynecene ne underfo to wuniunge, bute hyre abbodesse leafe &amp; hyre &thorn;&aelig;s &yogh;ewrit s&aelig;nde mid swutelun&yogh;e, fordi hit is &thorn;us awriten: "Ne do &thorn;u odrum, &that; &thorn;u nelle, &that; &thorn;e sylue &yogh;edon sy".</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="62" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXII. (BE MYNSTRES SACERDUM.)<MILESTONE N="125a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">(BE MYNSTRES SACERDUM)] Be endebyrdnesse &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eferre&aelig;denne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&YOGH;yf hwylc abbodesse &yogh;e&thorn;afad, &that; m&aelig;ssepreost odde diacon<MILESTONE N="125b" UNIT="folio"> into mynstre &yogh;ange, to&thorn;i &that; hi&yogh; m&aelig;sse synge &amp; &thorn;a unasec&yogh;end|lice<NOTE PLACE="foot">unasec|&yogh;endl.] unaseo&yogh;endl. <I>Hs.</I>, a <I>&uuml;ber der Z.</I></NOTE> &amp; &thorn;a dyrwyrdesta &thorn;enunga &yogh;efulle, syn hy swa &yogh;ecorene, &thorn;aet hi bute t&aelig;le beo &amp; presthades &thorn;urh ealle gode cyste wel wirde. Syn hi clen&yogh;eorne, &yogh;e&thorn;yldi&yogh;e &amp; eadmode, scylde hi 
<PB REF="00000155.tif" N="127"><MILESTONE UNIT="F" N="140,8-141,6"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="113,19-115,3"> &aelig;fre &yogh;eorne wid uppahafenesse &amp; wid modinesse; ne &yogh;edyrst|lece hi nan &thorn;in&yogh;, ne n&aelig;nne onti&yogh;e on &thorn;am mynstre n&aelig;bbe butan &thorn;&aelig;re m&aelig;sse anre; ne hi nane sp&aelig;ce wid &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre n&aelig;bbe; ne hi&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;rinne leng ne wunien, &thorn;one &thorn;eo messe &yogh;e|sun&yogh;en beo, ac sone swa &thorn;e m&aelig;sse &yogh;esun&yogh;en beo, hi&yogh; ead|modlice utgan. Warnian &thorn;e &yogh;eswustre, &that; hi nane sundersp&aelig;ce nabbe wid &thorn;a m&aelig;sseprustes, ne wid heore &thorn;enin&yogh;mann. Gyf &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eswustre &yogh;ehwilc hyre di&yogh;ele synne &thorn;an m&aelig;ssepr&aelig;ste and&yogh;etten wille, sy &thorn;et &yogh;edon be &thorn;ere abbodesse leafe inne &thorn;ere cyrecen, na on di&yogh;ele stowe, ac swa, &thorn;&aelig;t &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre hyre onlocien m&aelig;&yogh;en, ealswa hit beboden is &thorn;urh &thorn;a hal&yogh;en f&aelig;deres; gyf heore &yogh;ehwilc &yogh;euntrumod byd, &that; heo to cyricen &yogh;egan ne m&aelig;&yogh;e, do hyre andetnesse on &thorn;an huse, &thorn;e heo on|wunat, on &yogh;esihde hyre swustre. Gyf heore hwilc buten neode &amp; bute &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse h&aelig;se &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;cd, &that; heo &aelig;ni&yogh;e sp&aelig;ce wid hi&yogh; a&yogh;e, eawun&yogh;e odde dearnun&yogh;e, underfo heo swide<MILESTONE N="126a" UNIT="folio"> stide steore. Habbe &thorn;eo abbodesse swa &yogh;ecorene messepreost, &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e diacon &yogh;e subdiacon, &amp; Gode swa &yogh;ecweme &thorn;urh hali&yogh;e drohnunge, &that; heom nan unhlyse ne fyli&yogh;e &thorn;urh &aelig;ni&yogh;e fracodscype, ac heora gode hlyse &yogh;earwurdie &thorn;a, &thorn;e hi&yogh; to<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;earwurdie, -ie <I>auf Ras., danach</I> esse <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> &thorn;ere messe &thorn;enunge &yogh;ecuren.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="63" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXIII. BE ENDEBYRDNESSE &THORN;ARE &YOGH;EFERREDENNE.<MILESTONE N="126b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Elc endebyrdnesse on mynstre sceal beon &yogh;ehealden and<MILESTONE N="127a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">and] <I>auf dem Rande von etwas sp&auml;trer Hand nachgetragen.</I></NOTE> &yogh;efadod be hyre &yogh;ecyrrednesse &amp; be lifes &yogh;eearnunge &amp; be<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ecyrredn.] &yogh;escyrredn. <I>Hs., das eine</I> r <I>&uuml;b. d. Z. v. sp&auml;tr. Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse &yogh;esta&thorn;olun&yogh;e. &ETH;eo abbodesse ne unstille, ne na ne &yogh;edrefe &thorn;a heorde, &thorn;e heora under&thorn;eod is, ne heo nan &thorn;in&yogh; ne misdihte, ne unrihtlice ne &yogh;eend&aelig;berde, swilce heo freolice don mote &that;, &that; heore lici&yogh;e; wite heo, &that; heo &aelig;t Godes dome &yogh;escead a&yogh;yldan sceal &amp; andsware ealre hyre dome &amp; ealre hyre dede. &AElig;fter &thorn;ere endbyrdnysse, &thorn;e &thorn;eo abbodesse &yogh;esta&thorn;elad &amp; &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre heom betweonan healdad, &yogh;a &aelig;lc<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;esta&thorn;elad, <I>in das</I> a <I>von</I> -ad <I>ein</I> o <I>hineincorrigirt, oder das</I> a <I>&uuml;ber ein</I> o; <I>nicht zu erkennen, welches das ursprgl. und welches gelten soll.</I></NOTE> 
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="129"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="115,3-117,13"> &aelig;fter odre to cosse &amp; to husle &amp; be &thorn;am on chore stande &amp; sealmes &amp; &yogh;ehwylce &thorn;enun&yogh;e be&yogh;ynne; on nane stowe ne sy endebyrdnes be nanre ylde &yogh;ediht, ne &thorn;eo yld &thorn;a &yogh;eo&yogh;ude ne for&thorn;rin&yogh;e, fordi Samuel &amp; Daniel cild&yogh;eon&yogh;e for ealdedum preostum demdon. Fordi &thorn;onne, buton &thorn;am anum, &thorn;e for heora leahtrum of hyre endebyrdnysse uttor asceofene syn, odde for hali&yogh;es lifes &yogh;eearnun&yogh;e innor beod &yogh;enumene, &aelig;lc oder, ofer|ylde &amp; &yogh;eo&yogh;ede, healde hyre endebyrdnesse, swa swa hi&yogh; &yogh;e|cyrde, swilce ic &thorn;us cwede: Gyf twa on ane d&aelig;&yogh;e to mynstre &yogh;ecyrrad, sy &thorn;eo furdor on &aelig;lcere endebyrdnesse, &thorn;e on &thorn;&aelig;re forme tide &thorn;&aelig;s d&aelig;&yogh;es com, &thorn;onne &thorn;eo &thorn;e on &thorn;ere odre tyde<NOTE PLACE="foot">forme] forne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> cymd, sy heo on swilcere ylde odde &yogh;e&thorn;incde, swilce heo sy.</P>
<P>&ETH;a &yogh;ingran fordi arwurdan hyra yldran, &amp; &thorn;a yldran lufia<MILESTONE N="127b" UNIT="folio"> heore &yogh;ingran. Ne &yogh;edyrstlece heore nan, &that; heo odre a&yogh;e|num naman synderlice clypie, ac &thorn;a yldre &thorn;a yngre swustre &aelig;fre clypien, &amp; &thorn;a &yogh;yngran nonnas clypien hyre yldre, &that; is: moderlic arwurdfullun&yogh;, odde lief &amp; arwesa. &ETH;eo abbodesse fordi, &that; heo Godes spelia is, sy hl&aelig;fedie &amp; moder &yogh;ehaten, na for hyre a&yogh;ene &yogh;e&thorn;inde, ac for Cristes arwurdnesse &amp; &thorn;&aelig;s lufe, &that; heo spelad. Heo &aelig;fre &thorn;&aelig;ncend beo &amp; hy swilce on hali&yogh;re dro htnun&yogh;e &yogh;e&yogh;earwye, &thorn;at heo sy wurde swa myceles wyrd|scypes. Swa hwar swa &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre hi&yogh; &yogh;emetad, &aelig;fre &thorn;eo &yogh;ingre bletsun&yogh;e abidde fram &thorn;&aelig;re yldre. Gyf &thorn;eo yldre fordga, &thorn;&aelig;r &thorn;eo &yogh;eon&yogh;re sitt, arise &thorn;eo &yogh;eon&yogh;e mid eadmodnesse &amp; &thorn;&aelig;re yldre lufelice ryme to setle; ne &yogh;edyrstlece &thorn;eo &yogh;ingre &that; heo mid &thorn;&aelig;re yldre sitte, bute heo hi hate, &that; &aelig;fre beo &yogh;e|halden, &that; on hali&yogh;um bocum awriten is, &that; is, &that; hi&yogh; heom be|twenan arwurdnesse healden and mid earwurdnesse hi &yogh;emetan.</P>
<P>&ETH;a child &amp; &thorn;eo &yogh;eo&yogh;ad mid styre &amp; &thorn;eowf&aelig;stnesse hyre endebyrdnesse filian, &yogh;e on cyrican &yogh;e on beodderne; beon hi&yogh; &aelig;fre behealdene mid steore &amp; mid michelre heordr&aelig;denne, &aelig;ider &yogh;e inne, &yogh;e ute, &yogh;e &aelig;&yogh;hwer, od &that; hi to and&yogh;ytolre ylde &amp; to fulfremedre &yogh;est&aelig;d&thorn;i&yogh;nesse becumen.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="64" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000159.tif" N="131"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="117,14-119,26">
<HEAD>LXIV. BE ABBODESSE HADUN&YOGH;E.<MILESTONE N="128b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>On abbodesse hadun&yogh;e &aelig;fre is &that; to besceawinne mid micele &yogh;esceade, &that; &thorn;eo beo to abbodesse &yogh;esett, &thorn;e eall &yogh;e|ferreden anum modum &amp; halwendum &yogh;e&thorn;eahte &aelig;fter Godes e&yogh;e<MILESTONE N="129a" UNIT="folio"> &yogh;ecyst; gyf eall &yogh;eferreden &thorn;onne r&aelig;d on &yogh;emenum &yogh;e&thorn;ehte<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;e&thorn;ehte <I>aus</I> &yogh;e&thorn;eahte <I>rad.</I></NOTE> misr&aelig;dad &amp; feawa of &thorn;am wisestam &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eferredenne &thorn;a<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;a] &thorn;e &thorn;a <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> neode forgode wislicor tocnawad, stande &thorn;ere red, &thorn;e mid Godes e&yogh;e &amp; wisdome &thorn;a riht &yogh;eceosad, &thorn;eah heora feawa beo, Ne &thorn;a odre on&yogh;ean &that; ne sacian. &AElig;fter hyre lifes &yogh;eearnunge &amp; &aelig;fter heore wisdomes lare sy &yogh;ecoren seo &thorn;e to abbodesse hade sceal, &thorn;&aelig;ah heo latost to mynstre come &amp; utemest on &thorn;&aelig;re endebyrdnesse &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;esomnun&yogh;e beo. Gyf hit &thorn;onne swa &yogh;etimad, &that; &aelig;all &yogh;eferreden anmode &yogh;e&thorn;eahte &that; to abbodesse &yogh;eceosad, &thorn;e heora leahtrum &yogh;e&thorn;afi&yogh;e &amp; heom on &yogh;ewil &yogh;an&yogh;e. &amp; &that; &thorn;uruh &aelig;&yogh;wfeste menn &amp; riht&yogh;elifede cud byd &thorn;am bi|sceope, &thorn;e &thorn;eo hali&yogh;e stowe on his bisceoprice is, forbeode he &amp; alec&yogh;e &thorn;a &thorn;wyrnesse heora un&yogh;e&thorn;eahtes &amp; mid fultume abbode &amp; abbodessene &amp; riht&yogh;elifedre manna &yogh;esette &thorn;a and dihte &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">riht&yogh;elifedre, d <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> hadi&yogh;e to habbodessen hade, &thorn;e Godes hus wel fadie &amp; on Godes richt gange &amp; na on &thorn;weore manna wille; wite &aelig;&yogh;der<NOTE PLACE="foot">20-21. wel <I>bis inclus.</I> wille <I>von etwas sp&auml;trer Hand auf dem Rande nachgetragen.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">richt] wirht <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;e bisceop &yogh;e riht&yogh;elifede menn, &thorn;&aelig;t hi&yogh; micele mede &aelig;t Gode habbad, &yogh;yf hy swa dod mid Godes e&yogh;e, eac swilce mycele wite, &yogh;yf hi on &yogh;e&thorn;afun&yogh;e gad &amp; for &yogh;emeleste bete hit n&aelig;lled.</P>
<P>&THORN;ence &thorn;eo abbodesse, syddan heo &yogh;ehaded beo, hu mycele byrdene &amp; hu hefityme heo mid &thorn;am hade underfen&yogh;h; wite eac &amp; smea&yogh;e, hu heo swidor &thorn;am sawle fremian ma&yogh;e, &thorn;onne<MILESTONE N="129b" UNIT="folio"> heo embe rictere hyre anwealdes ho&yogh;ian. Eornestlice, hi&yogh; &yogh;e|&thorn;afenad, &that; heo wel &yogh;el&aelig;red beo mid godcundre &aelig;&macr; &amp; to &thorn;am snoter, &that; heo cunne hali&yogh;e spell reccan swide wel, &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e of &thorn;&aelig;re ealdan cydnesse &yogh;e of &thorn;&aelig;re nywan, and heo sylf on &yogh;eearnun&yogh;e swilc sy, &that; me embe hire a&yogh;ene halinesse sodlice specen m&aelig;&yogh;e; sy heo clene &amp; syfer&aelig;te &amp; mildherte, &amp; sy &aelig;fre &thorn;eo mildheortn&aelig;s wyldre &thorn;onne rihte dom, &thorn;&aelig;t heo &thorn;&aelig;t ilce 
<PB REF="00000161.tif" N="133"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="119,26-123,6"> &yogh;emet Godes miltse be&yogh;yte. Hati&yogh;e heo &thorn;a un&thorn;eawas &amp; lufie &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre. Sy heo snoter and wel besceawod on ealle hyre dede &amp; na oferswyde ne &thorn;rea&yogh;e, &thorn;il&aelig;s &thorn;&aelig; &thorn;at rusti&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;il&aelig;s &thorn;&aelig;] &thorn;i &thorn;&aelig; l&aelig;s <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> f&aelig;t mid ealle toberste, gyf heo mid un&yogh;emette sceafd; bescea|wi&yogh;e heo &aelig;fre hyre a&yogh;ene tyddernesse &amp; &thorn;urh &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ebeorh sy, ne forbryte heo na &that; tocwysede hreod. Ne t&aelig;ce we na mid swa &yogh;eradum bysenum &amp; &yogh;ebeorhtlice lare, &that; heo un&thorn;eawes fyrdri&yogh;e odde fridi&yogh;e &amp; weaxe l&aelig;te, ac &that; heo snoterlice &amp; mid sodere lufe hi&yogh; &aelig;fre &yogh;ewani&yogh;e, swa swa heo on&yogh;yte, &that; hit elcere fremian ma&yogh;e hyre underdeoddum, swa swa we &yogh;efyrn<NOTE PLACE="foot">9-10. swa <I>bis incl.</I> underdeoddum <I>auf dem untern Rande von etwas sp&auml;trer Hand nachgetragen.</I></NOTE><NOTE PLACE="foot">we <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> beforan cwedon; wilni&yogh;e heo &amp; &yogh;ecneordl&aelig;ce, &that; me hi lufian ma&yogh;e swidor &thorn;onne ondred&aelig;n. Ne sy heo &yogh;edrefe &amp; an&yogh;mod, ne sy heo to swid &amp; anwylle, ne sy heo &aelig;festi&yogh; &amp; facne, ne andfull ne wenende, fordi &aelig;fre beod unstylle &amp; r&aelig;steleas, &thorn;e mid &thorn;am un&thorn;eaum &yogh;efylled byd. Sy heo efre foregleaw &amp;<MILESTONE N="130a" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;efylled byd, -d byd <I>auf Rasur.</I></NOTE> wel besceawod on hyre bebode; &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e &aelig;fter godcunde &thorn;inge &yogh;e &aelig;fter worulcunde tosceade heo &amp; &yogh;emeti&yogh;e &thorn;e weorc ealle, &thorn;e heo bet&aelig;ce; ge&thorn;ence heo &thorn;a &yogh;esceadwisnesse <I>Sancte</I> Jacobes, &thorn;&aelig;s heahf&aelig;der, &thorn;e &thorn;us cwed: "Gyf ic mine heorde to swide on gange &thorn;rafi&yogh;e &amp; swence, hi&yogh; ealle anes d&aelig;&yogh;es swiltad." Nime hyre &thorn;&aelig;s bysene &amp; odre swilce &thorn;&aelig;s sodan &yogh;esceades, &thorn;e is ealra ma&yogh;ne moder, &amp; swa ealle &thorn;in&yogh; &yogh;eme|te&yogh;i&yogh;e, &that; sy &thorn;onne &yogh;yt on hyre bebode, &that; &thorn;a stran&yogh;en furdur wylnian &amp; &thorn;a unstran&yogh;en ofersymede ne sy, &that; hi hire &thorn;eoudom un&thorn;ances ne forfleon, &amp; huru &thorn;in&yogh;e &thorn;&aelig;s anes beo &yogh;emendi&yogh;, &that; &thorn;ises andweardan regoles &yogh;ebodu o eallum &thorn;in&yogh;um &yogh;ehealdene syn &amp; &yogh;efyllede; &thorn;onne heo wel &thorn;enad &amp; ures drihtenes heorde cwiferlice eal&yogh;ad &amp; to rihte manad, heo onfehd ecce lean &aelig;t<NOTE PLACE="foot">cwiferlice] criferl. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> ure drihtene &amp; blide &yogh;ehyrd, &that; &thorn;e gode &thorn;eowa &yogh;ehyrde, &thorn;e on rihtne tymen hwete &yogh;edelde his efen&thorn;eowum; "Sod is, &that; ic sec&yogh;e, ofer ealle his god he hine to ealdre for his &yogh;edreo&yogh;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">ealdre, d <I>von sp&auml;trer Hand &uuml;ber d. Z.</I></NOTE> &yogh;esette".
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="65" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000163.tif" N="135"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="124,1-125,11">
<HEAD>LXV. BE &THORN;ERE PRIORE.<MILESTONE N="131a" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Foroft hit &yogh;etimed, &thorn;&aelig;t swide hefi&yogh;tyme sace &amp; un&yogh;e&thorn;wer|nessa on mynstra aspringat &thorn;urh &thorn;are priore unryhte dihtun&yogh;e,<NOTE PLACE="foot">unryhte] unnyhte <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> donne hyre sum mid &thorn;es awyri&yogh;eden gastes to&thorn;undennesse swa stide toblawenne, &that; hyre &thorn;ynd, &that; heo sy oder abbedesse, and &thorn;urh &that; heo hysylfe swa gode teld, byd swide sacful &amp; micele<MILESTONE N="131b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">sacful] facful <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> un&yogh;e&thorn;w&aelig;rnesse &amp; mani&yogh;fealde sace on &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eferredenne wyrcd; &thorn;is &yogh;elimpd swidest on &thorn;ere stowe, &thorn;&aelig;r &thorn;e priore on &yogh;emene byd &yogh;esett fram &thorn;am ylcum bisceopum odde &thorn;am ab|bode, &thorn;e &thorn;a abbodessan &yogh;ehadedon &amp; on &thorn;am wirdmynte &yogh;esetten. Eade is to understandenne, of hwylcum antymbre<NOTE PLACE="foot">hwylcum, h <I>aus</I> w <I>corrig.</I></NOTE> &thorn;eos modi&yogh;nes bid asprun&yogh;en: hyre &thorn;incd on hyre &yogh;e&thorn;once,<NOTE PLACE="foot">asprun&yogh;en] aswur&yogh;en <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &that; heo &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse hyre ne &thorn;urfe, for&thorn;am &thorn;e heo hi&yogh; to priore ne sette, ac &thorn;a syluan hyre prauostscyre bet&aelig;hten, &thorn;e &thorn;a abbodesse to hyre hade &yogh;ecuron. &THORN;urh &thorn;is beod awehte ande mid micele sace &amp; tala &amp; herun&yogh;a, un&yogh;e&thorn;w&aelig;rnesse &amp; mis|fadun&yogh;; &thorn;onne &thorn;eo abbodesse &amp; &thorn;e priore un&yogh;erade beod &amp;<NOTE PLACE="foot">un&yogh;erade, r <I>auf Rasur, viell.</I> h <I>darunter.</I></NOTE> heom betweonan winnad &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e heora a&yogh;ene sawla &thorn;urh &thorn;&aelig;s frecednesse losiad &amp; eac swilce &thorn;&aelig;re, &thorn;e heom under|&thorn;eodde synd, &thorn;onne hi sume mid &yogh;efycum &yogh;eolecad &thorn;&aelig;re onre, &amp; lease t&aelig;lun&yogh;e settad sume wid &thorn;a odre Seo frecennes<NOTE PLACE="foot">lease] lea &amp; <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &thorn;ises yfeles belimpd to &thorn;am swydest, &thorn;e hi sylfe ealdras &yogh;e|worhtan on swilcere fadun&yogh;e &amp; endebyrdnesse. Fordi we fore|sceawiad<NOTE PLACE="foot">we] &yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; fremfull tellad to &yogh;ehealsumnesse &yogh;emenre sibbe &amp; sodre lufe, &that; eall &thorn;&aelig;s mynstres dihtun&yogh; &amp; endebyrdnesse on &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse dome &amp; t&aelig;cun&yogh;e &aelig;fre stande. Gyf hit<NOTE PLACE="foot">abbodesse, <I>nach</I> -esse <I>ein</I> n <I>radirt, doch gleich, da das folgende</I> d <I>ganz nahe daran.</I></NOTE> beon m&aelig;&yogh;, swilc notu &thorn;urh decanas, &that; synd teodin&yogh;ealdras,<MILESTONE N="132a" UNIT="folio"> on mynstre &yogh;efadod &amp; &yogh;eendebyrd beo on &thorn;a wise, &thorn;e &thorn;eo abbodesse diht, &that; na nan enlypie ne mode&yogh;ie, ne hi&yogh; na ne<NOTE PLACE="foot">mode&yogh;ie, i <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE> onhebban, &thorn;onne mynstres notu mane&yogh;e beteht byd.
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="137"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="125,12-126,18"></P>
<P>Gyf &thorn;eo stow &thorn;&aelig;s neode habbe &amp; &thorn;eo &yogh;eferreden &thorn;&aelig;s mid<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;&aelig;s (2.) <I>auf Rasur, darunter</I> ne, <I>also stand ursprgl.</I> &yogh;eferre|denne.</NOTE> &yogh;esceade &amp; mid eadmodnesse &thorn;&aelig;s &yogh;ewylni&yogh;e, &amp; hit &thorn;&aelig;re abbo|desse red &thorn;ince, swa hwilce swa &thorn;eo abbodesse &yogh;eceose mid &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;eswustre r&aelig;de, &thorn;e &YOGH;od ondr&aelig;dad, sette hyre &thorn;a to priore.</P>
<P>&ETH;e sylue priore do mid arwyrdnesse eall, &that; &thorn;eo abbodesse hate; ne do hu nan &thorn;ing on&yogh;ean &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse willan and &yogh;e&thorn;afunge, fordi swa micele swa heo furdur on wyrdmynte forleten byd, swa mycele heo sceal &yogh;eornlicor Godes &yogh;erihte<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;eornlicor] &yogh;eornlicon <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> healden &amp; &thorn;as r&aelig;&yogh;oles bebode.</P>
<P>Gyf &thorn;eo priore leahterfull &amp; un&thorn;eauful onfunde byd, odde mid modi&yogh;enesse beswicen, odde &thorn;&aelig;s hali&yogh;en reo&yogh;eles be|bodan forsihd, sy heo &yogh;emine&yogh;od feower syde mid worde. Gyf heo &yogh;ebetan nelle &thorn;urh worda myne&yogh;unge, sy hyre &thorn;reale<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;reale] &thorn;wreale <I>Hs.</I>, r <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> &yogh;eboden be &thorn;es reo&yogh;eles t&aelig;cinge. Gyf heo &thorn;urh &thorn;reale nelle<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;reale] &thorn;wreale <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hi sylfe &yogh;erihtlece, sy heo aworpen ut of &thorn;&aelig;re priorwyce, &amp; sy oder &thorn;&aelig;r on&yogh;esett, &thorn;e &thorn;&aelig;s wyrde beo. Syddan heo bescyrod byd, &yogh;yf heo on &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;ef&aelig;rreddenne &yogh;edefe ne byd &amp; &yogh;ehyr|sum, hi me mid ealle of mynstre adrife. Ge&thorn;&aelig;nce &thorn;eahhwedere &thorn;eo abbodesse, &that; heo God &aelig;lmihti&yogh;e &yogh;escead a&yogh;ylden sceal<MILESTONE N="132b" UNIT="folio"> be eallum hyre d&aelig;dum &amp; domum, &amp; warni&yogh;e, &thorn;&aelig;t heo mid ande ne sy an&yogh;ien &thorn;a priore, &thorn;yl&aelig;s &thorn;e bryne of ande &amp; of<NOTE PLACE="foot">bryne, b <I>auf Ras.</I></NOTE> byternesse heore a&yogh;ene sawla grimlice b&aelig;rne.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="66" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXVI. BE MUNSTRES &YOGH;EATWARDE.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&YOGH;EATWARDE, t <I>&uuml;b. d. Z.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>To &thorn;es mynstres &yogh;eate beo &yogh;esett an eald mynecene &amp; wis, &thorn;e wel cunne andsware &yogh;yfe and underfo, &amp; swa ripe heo beo, &that; heo nelle wori&yogh;e, &amp; scridan ne lyste. &ETH;eo sylfe &yogh;eat|weard<MILESTONE N="133a" UNIT="folio"> 
<PB REF="00000167.tif" N="139"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="126,18-128,7"> sceal hus habban &aelig;t &thorn;am &yogh;eate, &that; &thorn;a &thorn;e cumad, &thorn;e &that; mynster &yogh;eseced, efre &yogh;earowne habban &amp; andsware &thorn;&aelig;re &aelig;rende<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; andsware, &amp; andsw- <I>auf Ras., worunter</I> andswa.</NOTE> underfo. Swa rade se &thorn;e cume cnucie, odde se &thorn;earfe clypi&yogh;e, heo sona cwede: "Deo gratias", &that; is "Gode &thorn;anc", &amp; hine &yogh;eorne bletsie &amp; &yogh;e&thorn;werlice mid Godes ei&yogh;e mid ofste and|swari&yogh;e mid &thorn;am wilme &thorn;&aelig;re sodan lufe. Sy sylfe &yogh;eateward, &yogh;yf heo fultumes behofi&yogh;e, sy hyre an &yogh;ingre swuster bet&aelig;ht, &thorn;e mid hire wicni&yogh;e.</P>
<P>Gyf hit beon mei, &that; mynster beon sceall swa &yogh;estadelod, &that; ealle neodbehefe &thorn;in&yogh; &thorn;&aelig;r bynnen wunian, &that; is w&aelig;ter &amp; mylne &amp; b&aelig;chus &amp; wyrtun &amp; &yogh;ehwylce odre mystlice creftes, &amp; ealle nydbehefe &thorn;ing widinne &thorn;am mynstre beo, &that; &thorn;a<NOTE PLACE="foot">widinne, w <I>aus</I> &thorn; radirt.</NOTE> mynecene nabbe nane neode ut to worienne, fordi &yogh;if hi hit<NOTE PLACE="foot">worienne, i <I>&uuml;ber d. Z.</I> &Verbar; hi] bi <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> dod, hit hearmad heora sawla. We wyllad, &thorn;at &thorn;eos reo&yogh;ele on &yogh;eferredenne sy &yogh;er&aelig;d &yogh;elome, &that; nan swuster of nitennesse hi&yogh; beladian ne ma&yogh;e.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="67" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXVII. BE &THORN;AM &YOGH;ESWUSTRE &THORN;E ME FOR NYDE UT ON<MILESTONE N="133b" UNIT="folio"> WE&YOGH;E S&AElig;NT.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;onne &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre sculen ahwyder faren, bet&aelig;cen hi&yogh; hiselfe &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse &yogh;ebede odde ealra &thorn;&aelig;re swustre, &amp; ta hwile, &thorn;e hi&yogh; on fore beod, syn hi&yogh; on &yogh;emynde, &amp; &aelig;t &aelig;lces tidsan&yogh;es &aelig;nde eall &yogh;eferreden heom fore &yogh;ebiddan. And &thorn;&aelig;s d&aelig;&yogh;es, &thorn;e hi&yogh; ham cumad, astreccen hi&yogh; innen cyricen on midde &thorn;&aelig;re flore &aelig;t &aelig;lces tidsan&yogh;es ende, &amp; hi&yogh; ealle &yogh;em&aelig;n|lice for heom &yogh;ebiddan, &that; heom nan &thorn;ing ne deri&yogh;e, &thorn;&aelig;s &thorn;e hi a&yogh;ilte on &thorn;am farelde, ador od&thorn;e &thorn;urh &yogh;esyhde, odde &thorn;urh<NOTE PLACE="foot">od&thorn;e (1.)] odre <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &yogh;ehlyste &aelig;ni&yogh;es yfeles, odde &thorn;urh ydele spece.</P>
<P>Ne hyre non ne &yogh;edyrstl&aelig;ce, &that; heo odrum telle &aelig;t ham, hwet heo butan mynstre &yogh;eseah odde &yogh;ehyrde, fordi hit is micel m&aelig;&yogh;ene tostencednes. And &yogh;if hit eni&yogh; dyrstlece, &that; heo hit do, underlic&yogh;e heo regolice styre, &that; is discipline; &amp;<MILESTONE N="134a" UNIT="folio"> 
<PB REF="00000169.tif" N="141"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="128,7-129,10"> eallswa, &thorn;&aelig; ged ut of cloystre, odde elles ahwider, odde &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;in&yogh; do, &thorn;eah &thorn;e hit litel &thorn;ince, butan &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse hese.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="68" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXVIII. BE &THORN;AM &YOGH;ESWUSTRE &THORN;E HEFITUME WICE BYD BET&AElig;HT.</HEAD>
<P>Gyf &aelig;ni&yogh; hefityme odde unacumelic &thorn;in&yogh; &aelig;ni&yogh;re swuster bet&aelig;ht byd, underfo heo &thorn;a hese hyre t&aelig;cendes mid ealre man|&thorn;w&aelig;rnesse &amp; mid eadmodre &yogh;ehyrsumnisse; gyf heo &thorn;onne sydde eallunge &yogh;efret, &that; &thorn;&aelig;re byrdene hefinesse oferstihd &that; &yogh;emet hyre str&aelig;ngde, eft on &yogh;e&thorn;afenlice tide hyre m&aelig;&yogh;enleaste hyre ealdre &yogh;ekyde &thorn;onne intin&yogh;e, hwi heo hit do ne me&yogh;, na mid modi&yogh;nesse ne mid widerspece widstande. Gyf syden &thorn;&aelig;s ealdres cwide &thorn;urhwunad &amp; on hyre &yogh;ebod aheardad, wite<MILESTONE N="134b" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;eo &yogh;in&yogh;ra mid &yogh;ewissa, &that; hit heore eall fremad, &amp; mid sodre lufe &thorn;urh Godes truwan &thorn;a hyrsumnesse be&yogh;inne, &thorn;eah hyre nehwon onha&yogh;i&yogh;e.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="69" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXIX. BE &THORN;AM &THORN;AT NAN ON &THORN;AM MYNSTRE NE DYRSTELECE<NOTE PLACE="foot">BE &thorn;AM &thorn;AT NAN] Bet nan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> O&ETH;RE MID WORDE WERI&YOGH;EN.</HEAD>
<P>Swyde is to scunienne, &thorn;&aelig;t on nane wise nan mynecene on mynstre mid worde odre beweri&yogh;e, odde mid &aelig;n&yogh;um an&yogh;inne &yogh;eeal&yogh;i&yogh;e, &thorn;&aelig;h &thorn;e hi beo &yogh;esybbe. Ne sy &thorn;is on nanum &yogh;e|mete &yogh;edyrstleht fram mynecenehades manna, fordi of &thorn;am m&aelig;&yogh; swide mycel saca ydelice arise. Gyf &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;is ofer&yogh;ime &thorn;urh &aelig;ni&yogh;re &yogh;edyrstnesse, beo hyre ealra teartlicost &yogh;estyrod.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="70" TYPE="chapter"><PB REF="00000171.tif" N="143"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="129,11-131,3">
<HEAD>LXX. BE &THORN;AM &THORN;AT NAN NE &YOGH;EDYRSTELICE O&ETH;RE &THORN;RESCE.<MILESTONE N="135b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">BE &thorn;AM &thorn;AT NAN] Bet nan <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>Sy forboden on mynstre &aelig;lcere dyrstinesse intin&yogh;a. We &yogh;e&aelig;ndebyrdad &amp; &yogh;esettad, &that; nan mynecene odre ne amansumian ne &thorn;rescen, butan &thorn;ere abbodesse leafe. &ETH;a &thorn;e misdod, beon eawun&yogh;a &yogh;e&thorn;reade beforan ealre &yogh;eferreddenne, &that; &thorn;&aelig;re odre &yogh;ehwilc &thorn;urh &thorn;&aelig;t &yogh;ee&yogh;esed sy.</P>
<P>Cyld&yogh;eon&yogh;e manna un&thorn;eawa eall &yogh;eferreden styre, &amp; habben hyre micele &yogh;ymene od d&aelig;t fifteode &yogh;ear hyre ylde; &that; &thorn;onne sy &yogh;edon mid ealle &yogh;emete &amp; mid eallum &yogh;esceade. Gyf hwilc heora &thorn;urh dyrstinesse on maran ylde yrsad &amp; &thorn;reale &yogh;ebytt, buten &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse h&aelig;se, odde on &thorn;am sylfum cyldum mid un&yogh;esceade &yogh;ehatheortad, underlic&yogh;e heo re&yogh;ollice steore, for&thorn;i hit is &thorn;us awriten: "&ETH;&aelig;t &thorn;u nelle, &that; &thorn;e sylfe &yogh;edon sy, ne do<NOTE PLACE="foot">sylfe, l <I>auf Ras., wie es scheint</I> f <I>darunter.</I></NOTE> &thorn;u odrum".</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="71" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXXI. &ETH;&AElig;T &THORN;A &YOGH;ESWUSTRE &YOGH;EHYURSUM&YOGH;E HEOM<MILESTONE N="135b" UNIT="folio"> BETWEONAN.<NOTE PLACE="foot">BETWEONAN] betweoran <I>Hs.</I></NOTE></HEAD>
<P>&THORN;eo godnesse of &yogh;ehyrsumnesse naht &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse anre is &aelig;fre to beodenne, ac ealle &thorn;a &yogh;eswustre heom betweone leoflice &yogh;ehyrsume beo; witon hi eac, &that; &thorn;urh hyrsumnysse heom byd we&yogh; &yogh;erimed to Godes myrcde. Sy &aelig;fre on forewearde<MILESTONE N="136a" UNIT="folio"> &thorn;&aelig;re abbodesse hese &yogh;edo &amp; sydde ealdre, &thorn;e fram hyre to &thorn;am &yogh;esett synd, &that; hi&yogh; odrum bebeodan; we elles nane odrum ne &yogh;e&thorn;afiad, &that; heo &yogh;ebod &aelig;fter hese a&yogh;e; elles &aelig;llc odrum hyrsumi&yogh;e mid sodre lufe &amp; mid mycelre embrirdnesse. Gyf hyre hwilc &yogh;eflit&yogh;eorn beo, sy hyre &yogh;estirod.</P>
<P>Gyf &aelig;ni&yogh; swuster for &aelig;ni&yogh;e &thorn;inge l&aelig;sse odde mare fram<NOTE PLACE="foot">odde] oddre <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> hyre abbodesse byd undernumen odde fram &aelig;ni&yogh;e hyre yldrena, odde on&yogh;yt, &that; hyre &aelig;ni&yogh;ere mod wid hi astyred byd, &thorn;eah 
<PB REF="00000173.tif" N="145"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="131,3-132,17"> hit for &yogh;ehw&aelig;de &amp; eadlice &thorn;inge sy, heo &thorn;&aelig;rrihte hisylfe astrecce butan &aelig;lcere elcun&yogh;e &amp; swa lange astreht &aelig;t hyre fote ligge, odd&aelig;t heo hyre yldrene mod &yogh;egladi&yogh;e &amp; hyre bletsunge be&yogh;yte. Gyf &aelig;ni&yogh; &thorn;is forsycd to donne, underfo heo re&yogh;olice styre; gyf heo on to&thorn;undennes &thorn;urhwunad, hy man of &thorn;am<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;urhwunad] &thorn;uwhw. <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> mynstre mid ealle ut adr&aelig;fe.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="72" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXXII. BE &YOGH;ODE ANDE &THORN;E MENECENE HABBEN SCULLEM.<MILESTONE N="136b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<P>Swa swa yfel biternesse ande &amp; &aelig;fst ascyred fram Gode<NOTE PLACE="foot">&amp; &aelig;fst] f&aelig;st <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; l&aelig;t to helle, ealriht swa god ande &amp; heriung ascyred fram synne &amp; leahtrum &amp; let to Gode &amp; to ecan life. Fordi &thorn;onne mynecene &thorn;&aelig;ne &aelig;rran andan awyrpen, &thorn;isne oderne mid hatan<NOTE PLACE="foot">&thorn;&aelig;ne] &thorn;&aelig;re <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> wylme sodre lufe began; &aelig;lc efste myd arwurdnesse &amp; mid &thorn;&aelig;s upplican lifes &yogh;ewilnunge, hu heo odre on hali&yogh;e &thorn;eudome for&thorn;eon ma&yogh;e; hyre seocnesse &aelig;&yogh;der &yogh;e of licaman &yogh;e of &yogh;e|&thorn;ance sibsumlice heom beotwene forbere; &aelig;lc odrum to &yogh;eflites, hu hi swidest ma&yogh;e, hyrsumian; hyre nan ne fily&yogh;e hyre agen wille on &thorn;am &thorn;ingum, &thorn;e heo hyresylfe nytwyrde tali&yogh;e &amp; be|hefe, ac &thorn;am swidost, &thorn;e odrum furdur fremian ma&yogh;e, &thorn;onne hyre sylfe; deo sode lufe, &thorn;&aelig; ealra m&aelig;&yogh;ne m&aelig;st is &amp; ealre hali&yogh;nesse will, wuni&yogh;e &aelig;fre betweone mynecene; Godes e&yogh;e<MILESTONE N="137a" UNIT="folio"> toforen heom &aelig;fre sy, &amp; hyre abbodesse mid clenre &amp; mid eadmodre lufe lufian; nan &thorn;ing hi heom inmedre ne l&aelig;ten, ne besorhre, &thorn;onne hyre drihten, &thorn;e us ealle &yogh;em&aelig;nelice &thorn;urh his myldheortnesse to ece lyfe &yogh;el&aelig;de. Amen.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="73" TYPE="chapter">
<HEAD>LXXIII. BE &THORN;AM &thorn;AT &AElig;ALL RIHTWISNESSE ON &THORN;YSSERE RE&YOGH;OLE<MILESTONE N="137b" UNIT="folio"><NOTE PLACE="foot">RIHTWISNESSE] rihtwissiesse <I>Hs.</I> &Verbar; RE&YOGH;OLE] relo&yogh;e <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> NIS &YOGH;ESTA&THORN;ELOD. EXPLICIT REGULA <I>SANCTI</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">NIS] <I>fehlt. Hs.</I></NOTE> BENEDICTI ABBATIS.</HEAD>
<P>&THORN;as regole we write, &that; we &thorn;urh hyre &yogh;ehealsumnesse on<NOTE PLACE="foot">we write] ewrite, <I>davor ein &yogh; radirt.</I> &Verbar; we <I>aus</I> &thorn;e <I>radirt.</I></NOTE> mynstre sumne del sceawie, &thorn;&aelig;t we habbad arwyrdnesse on &thorn;eawe odde an&yogh;inn of rihtfulle life.
<PB REF="00000175.tif" N="147"><MILESTONE UNIT="A" N="132,18-133,19"></P>
<P>Seo &thorn;e fullfremednesse hali&yogh;ere drohtnun&yogh;e habben wile, &that; synd &yogh;esette to lyfes bysene hali&yogh;era f&aelig;dere lare, &thorn;&aelig;re &yogh;e|mynd &amp; &yogh;ehealdsumnes &yogh;el&aelig;t &thorn;a mynecene to full&thorn;un&yogh;enre fre|mednesse.<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;ehealdsumne <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> La, hwylc lare l&aelig;t &thorn;one mann to re&yogh;olice life, hwylc boc odde sermun of &thorn;&aelig;re ealden &aelig; odde of &thorn;&aelig;re niwe nis swide riht re&yogh;ol to mancynnes life? Odde hwilc boc, &thorn;e ure<NOTE PLACE="foot">re&yogh;ol to] re <I>auf Rasur</I>, &yogh;ol <I>&uuml;ber die Zeile hinaus a. d. Rand, dsgl. das folgende</I> to <I>auf dem Rande vor der nachsten Zeile. Es scheint</I> re&yogh;ol <I>ursprgl. ausgelassen und dann auf</I> to <I>geschrieben worden zu sein.</I></NOTE> lareowas macede, &thorn;e were on rihte &yogh;elafe, &that; ne se&yogh;d, &that; we<NOTE PLACE="foot">&yogh;elafe, f <I>auf ein &yogh; hinaufcorrigirt.</I></NOTE> &thorn;urh rihtne rynolne cume to &thorn;am &thorn;e us &yogh;esceop? Odde &thorn;a collatiuns, &that; Iohannes Cassianus awrat, &amp; &thorn;ere hali&yogh;ere manna lif, &thorn;e on Uitas Patrum is &yogh;eredd &amp; &thorn;e regol ures hali&yogh;es fader Basilies, hw&aelig;t is hit elles bute &yogh;etymbrunge &amp; tol hali&yogh;re manne<NOTE PLACE="foot">tol] to <I>Hs.</I></NOTE> &amp; &thorn;ere mynecene, &thorn;e wel &amp; rihte libbad &amp; &yogh;ehyrsume synde To sceame &amp; to ascyndnesse hi synd us, &thorn;e asolcene synd &amp;<MILESTONE N="138a" UNIT="folio"> yfele &amp; &yogh;ymeleaslice mid unrihte libbad.</P>
<P>Swa hwilc swa onnettende efst to &thorn;am heofonlice &aelig;&thorn;ele &yogh;efremme &aelig;rest &thorn;urh Godes fultum &thorn;isne lytle re&yogh;ol, &thorn;e her awriten is, to an&yogh;inne godre drohtnunge; &amp; swa &aelig;t nyxtan &thorn;urh Godes fultum &thorn;u cymst to mare &yogh;e&thorn;inde godre ma&yogh;ne &amp; lare &thorn;&aelig;re hal&yogh;ene, &thorn;e we bufe embe spece, &that; &acirc; &yogh;ewurde ece lif to leane &amp; wunung mid Gode ealle &thorn;am, &thorn;e &thorn;isse re&yogh;ole blydelice fyliad.</P>
</DIV2>
